00:10:47,239 --> 00:10:48,397
读者群优势
upper-middle class readership.

193
00:10:48,507 --> 00:10:51,099
我们必须在全国奔走呼告 为本杂志集资
So, we have to run around the country raising money for the magazine

194
00:10:51,175 --> 00:10:52,538
不择手段地…
any way we...

195
00:10:56,613 --> 00:10:57,771
怎么啦？
What?

196
00:10:59,149 --> 00:11:01,479
我在想…
Well, I'm thinking that I guess I...

197
00:11:01,717 --> 00:11:03,876
我应该给你提供多点咖啡
That I ought to offer you more coffee.

198
00:11:03,986 --> 00:11:06,714
我没留意到时间，但是…
I hadn't realized the hour, but

199
00:11:07,122 --> 00:11:09,577
我似乎占用了你很多时间
I seem to have taken up a lot of your time.

200
00:11:09,791 --> 00:11:11,484
没关系
Well, that's okay by me.

201
00:11:14,028 --> 00:11:15,914
这种事常发生吗？
Does this happen to you often?

202
00:11:17,097 --> 00:11:18,426
不经常
Not often enough.

203
00:11:19,866 --> 00:11:20,922
那么…
Well?

204
00:11:23,135 --> 00:11:24,828
我们进展迅速
We certainly have come a long way fast.

205
00:11:24,971 --> 00:11:25,924
是的
Yeah.

206
00:11:27,106 --> 00:11:29,368
你想更进一步吗？
Do you want to take it a step further?

207
00:11:30,275 --> 00:11:31,297
好的
Yeah.

208
00:11:33,511 --> 00:11:35,272
如果我要你做件听似有点自私的事…
What would you think if I asked you to do something

209
00:11:35,379 --> 00:11:37,436
你会怎么想？
that might seem a little selfish?

210
00:11:37,815 --> 00:11:39,769
我觉得你大可说出来
Well, I... I think you should.

211
00:11:39,883 --> 00:11:42,406
好的，我想让你看看我的作品
Good. Good, because I'd like you to take a look at my work

212
00:11:42,518 --> 00:11:43,949
发表一下你的看法
and tell me what you think.

213
00:11:44,053 --> 00:11:46,383
我真的很尊重你的观点
You see, I really respect your opinion so much.

214
00:11:46,489 --> 00:11:49,115
真是凑巧，我正想问你…
Well, it's odd, because I was just gonna ask you

215
00:11:49,224 --> 00:11:50,246
有什么东西给我看的
if you had anything I could take a look at.

216
00:11:50,359 --> 00:11:52,689
这有点强人所难 但我真的感激你能过目
I know it's an imposition but I'd be very grateful and you see,

217
00:11:52,794 --> 00:11:54,783
你所写的文章我都看过
I've read everything that you've ever written.

218
00:11:54,895 --> 00:11:56,690
我很乐意这么做…
Well, I'd be happy to do it. So, that's...

219
00:11:56,831 --> 00:11:58,160
谢谢你
Well, thank you.

220
00:11:58,566 --> 00:12:01,362
那我去给你拿外套
Well, then I... I'll get your coat.

221
00:12:02,769 --> 00:12:04,257
希望你不会太客气
Oh, and I hope you won't be gentle with me.

222
00:12:04,504 --> 00:12:05,958
-客气？ -我是个严肃的作家
- Gentle? - I'm a serious writer.

223
00:12:06,072 --> 00:12:07,025
你大可以尖锐点
You can really be tough.

224
00:12:07,172 --> 00:12:08,865
我会的…
No, I will be. No, I will be.

225
00:12:08,974 --> 00:12:10,496
-谢谢 -谢谢
- Thank you. - Thank you.

226
00:12:11,010 --> 00:12:13,670
-你想要我离开？ -不是的，只是我要迟到了
- Do you want me to leave? - Not really, but I'm late.

227
00:12:13,778 --> 00:12:16,870
-清早6点迟到？ -是的，我有个约会
- Late at 6:00 in the morning? - Yes. I have an appointment.

228
00:12:17,215 --> 00:12:18,942
明晚我可以见你吗？
Well, could I see you tomorrow night?

229
00:12:19,050 --> 00:12:20,242
我明晚很忙
I'm busy tomorrow night.

230
00:12:20,350 --> 00:12:22,714
-第二天我就要出城了 -真是遗憾
- Because I'm leaving town the next day. - Gee, I'm sorry.

231
00:12:22,819 --> 00:12:24,375
你若有时间的话，请告知我你的看法
So, if you have time, let me know what you think,

232
00:12:24,488 --> 00:12:26,750
我会把采访的副本给你
and I'll send you a copy of the interview.

233
00:12:27,156 --> 00:12:28,610
采访？
Some interview, huh?

234
00:12:30,126 --> 00:12:31,614
有时间看看
Take a look sometime.

235
00:12:32,827 --> 00:12:36,215
好的，我明白
Yeah. Yeah, yeah. Okay, I understand.

236
00:12:36,364 --> 00:12:37,556
-拜 -拜
- Bye. - Bye.

237
00:12:46,773 --> 00:12:49,433
杰克，你还记得哈迪森先生吗？
Jack, dear, do you remember Mr. Hardison?

238
00:12:49,542 --> 00:12:52,429
曾在山上的第一长老教堂待过
Used to be at the First Presbyterian Church, up the hill.

239
00:12:52,543 --> 00:12:55,669
他现在在西雅图的普利茅斯大教堂
He's in Seattle now at the big Plymouth church.

240
00:13:00,283 --> 00:13:02,772
是什么风把你吹来的，杰克？
What brings you out here, Jack?

241
00:13:02,986 --> 00:13:05,282
只是回来看你母亲吗？
Just come out to see your mother?

242
00:13:07,289 --> 00:13:11,781
帕洛先生，我是为我撰写的 杂志集资而来
Mr. Partlow, I just... I'm raising money for this magazine that I write for.

243
00:13:11,926 --> 00:13:13,789
-什么？ -我是来为我写的杂志…
- What? - I say, I'm raising money

244
00:13:13,895 --> 00:13:15,849
集资而来
for this magazine that I write for!

245
00:13:15,997 --> 00:13:17,451
-杂志？什么杂志？ -是的，先生
- Magazine? What magazine? - Yes, sir.

246
00:13:17,598 --> 00:13:18,858
《大众》杂志
Well, it's called The Masses.

247
00:13:18,965 --> 00:13:20,692
-什么？ -《大众》
- The what? - The Masses!

248
00:13:20,801 --> 00:13:22,255
-《大众》 -大众
- The Masses. - Masses.

249
00:13:22,669 --> 00:13:25,591
杰克，你还记得珀森先生的妹妹吗？
Jack, do you remember Mr. Potterson's sister?

250
00:13:25,705 --> 00:13:27,034
一条胳膊残废了的那个？
The one with the bad arm?

251
00:13:27,139 --> 00:13:29,594
-是宗教方面的吗？ -不是的，先生
- Is that religious? - Oh, no, sir. No, sir.

252
00:13:29,709 --> 00:13:31,800
你记得她的，杰克 她叫梅莉安
Oh, you remember her, Jack. Her name was Miriam.

253
00:13:31,910 --> 00:13:32,863
她从不吃肉
She didn't eat meat.

254
00:13:32,977 --> 00:13:34,567
有点宗教味道
Sounds religious.

255
00:13:34,679 --> 00:13:36,736
记得那个向她求爱的家伙吗？
You remember the fellow that was courting her?

256
00:13:36,815 --> 00:13:40,169
卖线轴的，常围着尤金转悠
Sold spool thread. Came from down around Eugene.

257
00:13:40,284 --> 00:13:42,512
-不是宗教的？ -不是，先生
- Not religious, huh? - No, sir.

258
00:13:42,653 --> 00:13:45,950
-他叫什么名字，杰克？ -我不记得名字了
- What was his name, Jack? - I don't think I remember the name.

259
00:13:46,055 --> 00:13:48,977
我不了解你们这些人 但我真的饿了
Well, I don't know about you people, but I'm starved.

260
00:13:49,225 --> 00:13:50,588
帕洛太太，我…
I don't know, Mrs. Partlow. I...

261
00:13:50,693 --> 00:13:52,989
杰克，听说昨晚在自由主义俱乐部…
Jack, I heard you made a few people a little unhappy

262
00:13:53,095 --> 00:13:54,390
你让一些人感到不悦了
down at the Liberal Club last night.

263
00:13:54,496 --> 00:13:56,587
卡尔，我们是来这里开心的
Oh, Carl, we're here to have a good time,

264
00:13:56,698 --> 00:13:58,357
不要谈那个话题
let's not go into that.

265
00:13:58,466 --> 00:14:00,227
他叫什么名字，杰克？
What was his name, Jack?

266
00:14:00,368 --> 00:14:02,459
-你们来了 -我不记得…
- Here you are! - I can't...

267
00:14:02,570 --> 00:14:04,024
欢迎，真开心
Welcome. So happy...

268
00:14:04,137 --> 00:14:05,762
-你好，杰克 -你好
- Hello, Jack. - Hello.

269
00:14:05,872 --> 00:14:07,599
你气色真好
Oh, you look wonderful.

270
00:14:12,778 --> 00:14:14,641
阿尔玛，这是路易丝・楚林杰
Alma, this is Louise Trullinger.

271
00:14:14,780 --> 00:14:18,600
阿尔玛・波尔 这位尼德・波尔和杰克・雷德
Alma Boyle. This is Ned Boyle and Jack Reed.

272
00:14:18,716 --> 00:14:21,239
杰克，路易丝是个女权改革派
Jack, Louise is quite a progressive in her own right.

273
00:14:21,386 --> 00:14:22,373
帕洛先生
Mr. Partlow.

274
00:14:22,520 --> 00:14:25,282
-你好，雷德先生 -你好
- How do you do, Mr. Reed? - How do you do?

275
00:14:26,189 --> 00:14:28,985
帕洛先生，帕洛太太 这是路易丝・楚林杰
Oh, Mr. Partlow, Mrs. Partlow, this is Louise Trullinger.

276
00:14:29,092 --> 00:14:30,819
-幸会 -幸会
- Pleased to meet you. - Pleased to meet you.

277
00:14:30,926 --> 00:14:33,154
你是保罗・楚林杰的妻子？
Are you Paul Trullinger's wife?

278
00:14:34,263 --> 00:14:36,024
是的
Yes. Yes, I am.

279
00:14:36,132 --> 00:14:37,995
够了不起的
Well, isn't that something?

280
00:14:38,099 --> 00:14:39,985
弗罗兹大桥就是他设计的
He did Frank Rhodes' bridge.

281
00:14:40,101 --> 00:14:43,728
楚太太，你丈夫是全波特兰最好的牙医
Oh, Mrs. Trullinger, your husband's the finest dentist in all of Portland.

282
00:14:43,804 --> 00:14:45,895
-过奖了 -是嘛？
- Thank you very much. - Really?

283
00:14:46,039 --> 00:14:48,164
他还给葛洛夫叔叔做了个盘子
And I think he did a plate for Uncle Grover.

284
00:14:48,308 --> 00:14:50,604
不等哈瑞和玛莎了，我快饿扁了
Oh, we won't wait for Harry and Martha. I could eat a horse.

285
00:14:50,743 --> 00:14:51,730
好，我们就座吧
All right, let's go in.

286
00:14:51,878 --> 00:14:53,366
保罗没来真是可惜
What a shame Paul couldn't come tonight.

287
00:14:53,513 --> 00:14:54,671
-有急事？ -是的…
- An emergency? - Yes...

288
00:14:54,814 --> 00:14:55,767
希望不是因为要做盘子
Not Uncle Grover's plate, I hope.

289
00:14:55,882 --> 00:14:58,508
不是，那个盘子还很新
- No. Uncle Grover's plate's like new. - Oh, well...

290
00:14:59,551 --> 00:15:02,040
格林威治村开始自由恋爱了？
Did free love start in Greenwich Village?

291
00:15:03,320 --> 00:15:04,808
上等的红酒，卡尔
Very good wine, Carl.

292
00:15:04,922 --> 00:15:08,742
-还要吗，杰克？ -不了，谢谢
- More, Jack? - No, no. No, thank you.

293
00:15:10,026 --> 00:15:11,514
真的很美味
It's just delicious, really.

294
00:15:11,628 --> 00:15:13,788
你不觉得吗，楚太太？
Don't you think so, Mrs. Trullinger?

295
00:15:14,130 --> 00:15:15,926
是的，很美味
Yes, it's just delicious.

296
00:15:15,998 --> 00:15:17,191
谢谢你，路易丝
Thank you, Louise.

297
00:15:17,299 --> 00:15:19,323
-杜邦，我想是 -杜邦
- Dupont, I think. - Dupont.

298
00:15:20,569 --> 00:15:21,865
是杜邦对吗，哈瑞？
It is Dupont, isn't it, Harry?

299
00:15:22,004 --> 00:15:25,268
母亲不想你让杰克开谈婚姻的话题
Mother doesn't want you to get Jack started on the subject of marriage.

300
00:15:25,406 --> 00:15:27,669
你有孩子吗，楚太太？
You got any children, Mrs. Trullinger?

301
00:15:27,842 --> 00:15:29,468
暂时没，雷德先生
Not yet, Mr. Reed.

302
00:15:29,576 --> 00:15:31,372
-叫我杰克 -我已经结婚14年了
- Call me Jack. - I've been married 14 years now.

303
00:15:31,478 --> 00:15:34,139
别把我牵扯进自由恋爱的争论
Don't get me in any arguments about free love.

304
00:15:34,247 --> 00:15:35,474
外面正在变冷
It's getting cold outside.

305
00:15:35,581 --> 00:15:37,104
我叫你路易丝
I'll just call you Louise.

306
00:15:37,216 --> 00:15:39,911
乔治・沃杜，没错 是乔治・沃杜！
George Waldorf. That's it! George Waldorf!

307
00:15:40,019 --> 00:15:41,417
过去是卖线轴的
Used to sell spool thread.

308
00:15:41,520 --> 00:15:44,852
-乔治・沃杜的情况呢？ -他死了
- What about George Waldorf? - Well, he died.

309
00:15:45,857 --> 00:15:48,222
我无法相信 竟然没人陪你出来散步，路易丝
I couldn't think of letting you walk unescorted, Louise.

310
00:15:48,292 --> 00:15:49,417
跟我说说…
Tell me something.

311
00:15:49,526 --> 00:15:53,052
楚先生介意你花这么多时间 在工作室吗？
Does Dr. Trullinger mind your spending so much time at your studio?

312
00:15:53,163 --> 00:15:55,858
大家都要给对方一点自由空间
People have to give each other a little freedom.

313
00:15:56,199 --> 00:15:57,961
自由吗，楚太太？
Freedom, Mrs. Trullinger?

314
00:15:58,668 --> 00:16:00,760
我很想知道你对自由的看法
I'd like to know what your idea of freedom is.

315
00:16:00,903 --> 00:16:03,325
拥有自己的工作室？散步在…
Having your own studio? Walk...

316
00:16:10,144 --> 00:16:12,941
我很想看看你脱掉裤子的样子 雷德先生
I'd like to see you with your pants off, Mr. Reed.

317
00:16:37,601 --> 00:16:39,932
勇往直前
Marching and shuffling along

318
00:16:55,549 --> 00:16:57,072
我没注意到时间
I didn't realize the time.

319
00:16:57,184 --> 00:17:00,209
如果你不介意，那里有李子蜜饯
So, if you like, there's some very nice damson preserves.

320
00:17:00,319 --> 00:17:02,707
可以用来做烤面包
And you can make toast out of that, if you want.

321
00:17:02,855 --> 00:17:05,015
那么，再见
So, bye.

322
00:17:05,157 --> 00:17:06,248
你去哪？
Where you going?

323
00:17:06,391 --> 00:17:07,652
你去哪？
Where you going?

324
00:17:07,759 --> 00:17:10,420
如果你要赶2:45的车 那就得赶紧的了
If you're catching the 2:45, I mean, you don't really have that much time.

325
00:17:10,529 --> 00:17:12,894
-你要收拾的话… -路易丝，现在才8:45
- I'm sure you're gonna want to pack... - Louise, it's 8:45, only.

326
00:17:12,997 --> 00:17:14,054
才8:45
It's 8:45.

327
00:17:14,164 --> 00:17:15,994
我知道你在纽约非常忙
Listen, I realize that you're very busy in New York,

328
00:17:16,100 --> 00:17:17,555
但如果你花点时间写点 对我作品的评价
but I'd be grateful if you could take the time

329
00:17:17,668 --> 00:17:19,294
我会感激不尽
to write a few words to me about my work.

330
00:17:19,402 --> 00:17:20,561
好的…
Oh, yes. Oh, yes.

331
00:17:20,670 --> 00:17:23,160
如果要把我的文件包送回来 可以邮寄这个地址
If you'll just send my portfolio back. You can mail it to this address...

332
00:17:23,273 --> 00:17:25,900
等等，路易丝 为什么要走得这么急？
Louise, wait a minute. What are you just walking out like that for?

333
00:17:26,008 --> 00:17:28,430
请上楼来和我谈谈好吗？
Will you come upstairs, please, and just talk to me for a minute?

334
00:17:31,246 --> 00:17:32,439
谢谢
Thank you.

335
00:17:33,114 --> 00:17:34,944
-听着… -什么事？
- Listen... - What is it?

336
00:17:37,618 --> 00:17:38,675
你不来吗？
Why don't you come?

337
00:17:38,818 --> 00:17:40,182
-什么？ -来纽约
- What? - Come to New York.

338
00:17:40,287 --> 00:17:41,947
你不是想写作吗？ 那就来作家云集的地方
You wanna write? Come where the writers are.

339
00:17:42,055 --> 00:17:44,443
如果你有自由 那就去拥有自由的地方
If you wanna have freedom you gotta go where the freedom is, don't you?

340
00:17:44,558 --> 00:17:46,422
你去波特兰是种浪费，来纽约吧
You're gonna go to waste in Portland. Come to New York.

341
00:17:46,525 --> 00:17:48,389
-你应该待在纽约 -多谢了
- You ought to be in New York. - Thank you very much.

342
00:17:48,494 --> 00:17:49,517
我会记得的
I'll remember that.

343
00:17:49,628 --> 00:17:51,686
-什么？ -我会记得你的建议
- What? - I'll remember your advice.

344
00:17:53,097 --> 00:17:54,825
请和我一起去
Please come with me.

345
00:17:55,133 --> 00:17:56,827
好吧，等等 我就直接说吧
All right, wait a minute. Let me get this straight.

346
00:17:56,935 --> 00:17:59,027
你想我和你一起去纽约
You want me to come with you to New York.

347
00:17:59,136 --> 00:18:00,397
是的
Yeah.

348
00:18:00,504 --> 00:18:02,368
以什么身份？
What as? What as?

349
00:18:02,439 --> 00:18:04,030
-什么意思… -以什么身份？
- What do you mean, what... - What as?

350
00:18:04,141 --> 00:18:06,597
-你的女友？ -什么意思？
- Your girlfriend? - What does that mean?

351
00:18:06,709 --> 00:18:07,970
以什么身份？你的女友…
What as? Your girlfriend,

352
00:18:08,110 --> 00:18:11,101
情人，情妇，还是姘妇？
your mistress, your paramour, your concubine?

353
00:18:11,379 --> 00:18:12,970
为什么一定要以某种身份？
Why does it have to be as anything?

354
00:18:13,114 --> 00:18:14,842
因为我不想卷进那种…
Because I don't wanna get into some kind

355
00:18:14,950 --> 00:18:18,282
情感的漩涡中，我无法…
of emotional possessive involvement where I'm not able to...

356
00:18:19,787 --> 00:18:21,617
我想知道是什么身份
I want to know what as.

357
00:18:21,722 --> 00:18:25,054
感恩节快到了 就以火鸡的身份如何？
Well, it's nearly Thanksgiving. Why don't you come as a turkey?

358
00:18:27,093 --> 00:18:31,119
我一直以为她是那种 非常认真的女孩
I always thought she was a very earnest girl who went away.

359
00:18:31,229 --> 00:18:35,619
可能那个牙医除了牙齿外 对别的都一无所知
Probably the dentist knew nothing except about teeth,

360
00:18:36,034 --> 00:18:38,866
有趣的是…
and was mainly interested...

361
00:18:38,970 --> 00:18:42,166
那个时候她遇到这个能干的…
And then she had this wonderful journalist

362
00:18:42,306 --> 00:18:44,569
可以与她海阔天空的记者
who could talk about all sorts of things.

363
00:18:44,708 --> 00:18:47,733
我从德国带了件大衣
I had a coat I brought from Germany.

364
00:18:47,877 --> 00:18:50,140
她想要那件大衣
And she wanted that coat

365
00:18:50,280 --> 00:18:54,238
并游说了我良久
and made me all kinds of propositions.

366
00:18:54,516 --> 00:18:56,142
但我也想要它
But I wanted it, too.

367
00:18:57,485 --> 00:18:59,975
不过最后我还是让给了她
But finally I gave in and gave it to her.

368
00:19:00,488 --> 00:19:02,375
我还有其他大衣
I had other coats.

369
00:19:03,757 --> 00:19:08,682
这就是她的处世方式
So that's how she operated.

370
00:19:11,864 --> 00:19:14,991
她跟随他去了，她得到了他
She went after him. As I say, she got him.

371
00:19:15,334 --> 00:19:17,426
她一点都不笨
So she wasn't any dummy.

372
00:19:18,903 --> 00:19:22,998
但这件事在过去的波特兰 引起了不小轰动
But it was something to happen in little old Portland.

373
00:19:23,173 --> 00:19:25,094
那时你听不到性这个词
You didn't hear the word "sex."

374
00:19:25,209 --> 00:19:27,073
听不到女同性恋这个词
You didn't hear the word "lesbian."

375
00:19:27,177 --> 00:19:29,440
听不到男同性恋这个词
You didn't hear the word "homosexual."

376
00:19:30,046 --> 00:19:32,502
也听不到流产这个词
You didn't hear the word "abortion."

377
00:19:32,649 --> 00:19:33,945
那些东西你都听不到
You didn't hear those things.

378
00:19:34,350 --> 00:19:35,748
男人尊重女人
Men respected women.

379
00:19:35,852 --> 00:19:39,116
男人帮助女人穿外套，为女人开门
They helped them on with their coats, they opened the doors for them.

380
00:19:39,221 --> 00:19:41,518
男人和女人相互求爱
And the man and woman who courted each other,

381
00:19:41,623 --> 00:19:42,953
两厢情愿
they married each other.

382
00:19:43,024 --> 00:19:45,184
我最大的感触就是…
You know something that I think,

383
00:19:45,559 --> 00:19:50,188
那时和现在简直可以说是判若两样
that there was just as much fucking going on then as now.

384
00:19:50,530 --> 00:19:54,454
只有现在，才会产生不正当的品质
Only now, it has a more perverted quality.

385
00:19:54,868 --> 00:19:58,291
现在不会再有什么爱了
Now there's no love whatever included.

386
00:19:58,437 --> 00:20:01,234
在那时，人间处处都有温情在
Then, there was your heart, a bit of heart in it.

387
00:20:01,340 --> 00:20:03,330
那就是格林威治村
Greenwich Village was there,

388
00:20:03,708 --> 00:20:05,436
被纽约城包围着
and New York was around it.

389
00:20:05,543 --> 00:20:09,433
纽约其他地方和格林威治村完全不同
And the rest of New York did not act the way Greenwich Village did, exactly.

390
00:20:09,780 --> 00:20:11,940
村子是异议的中心…
It was sort of a center of dissent

391
00:20:12,315 --> 00:20:16,205
在美国人的生活中生活了很久
and had been for a long time in American life.

392
00:20:16,352 --> 00:20:18,842
全国各地的人来到这里
People from all over the country came there.

393
00:20:19,822 --> 00:20:23,609
他们被当作是吉普赛人 他们的生活方式没有规律
They were regarded as bohemian. Their ways of life were irregular.

394
00:20:24,225 --> 00:20:25,885
他们的穿着…
The way they dressed

395
00:20:26,161 --> 00:20:27,650
还有他们的思维方式
and certainly the way they thought

396
00:20:27,796 --> 00:20:30,559
与美国的主流生活格格不入
was outside the mainstream of American life.

397
00:20:30,664 --> 00:20:32,221
根据我的回忆…
And as I recollect it,

398
00:20:32,332 --> 00:20:35,220
婚姻在格林威治村并不重要
marriage was not important in Greenwich Village.

399
00:20:35,334 --> 00:20:38,825
我记得杰克对别人说过一句话
I remember hearing a line Jack said to somebody

400
00:20:38,938 --> 00:20:40,893
他想引诱女人上床
he was trying to lure into bed.

401
00:20:41,007 --> 00:20:45,296
女人非常卖弄风情 然后他说“你难道不够异教吗？”
She was being very coy, and he said, "Aren't you pagan enough?"

402
00:20:46,245 --> 00:20:47,507
哈罗？
Hello?

403
00:20:56,789 --> 00:20:58,654
哈罗，杰克？
Hello, Jack?

404
00:21:08,735 --> 00:21:10,726
《大众》

405
00:21:11,738 --> 00:21:14,730
“大工会联盟”

406
00:21:22,749 --> 00:21:24,705
“周五乘列车在6号站台到达”

407
00:21:24,751 --> 00:21:28,744
“我自己能找到路，路易丝”

408
00:21:41,534 --> 00:21:43,695
如果散发节育小册子是违法的…
If it's illegal to hand out pamphlets on birth control,

409
00:21:43,803 --> 00:21:45,134
那我也为罪犯而骄傲
I'm proud to be a criminal.

410
00:21:45,238 --> 00:21:48,401
没人跟你争执坐牢权利的问题，埃玛
No one is arguing with your inalienable right to go to jail, Emma.

411
00:21:48,508 --> 00:21:50,635
我只是说因为节育而坐牢…
All I'm saying is that this is not the right time

412
00:21:50,743 --> 00:21:52,108
在时间上不合时宜
to go to jail for birth control.

413
00:21:52,211 --> 00:21:54,133
因节育而坐牢有合适的时间吗？
Oh, there's a right time to go to jail for birth control?

414
00:21:54,247 --> 00:21:56,374
《大众》现在管制起道德良心来了？
The Masses is governing conscience now?

415
00:21:56,449 --> 00:21:58,679
很快你就无法区别出《纽约时报》了
Soon you'll be indistinguishable from The New York Times.

416
00:21:58,785 --> 00:22:01,379
埃玛，我只是说反战运动…
Emma, all I'm saying is that you are too valuable

417
00:22:01,521 --> 00:22:03,113
-对你来说代价太高 -你错了
- to the anti-war movement. - You're wrong.

418
00:22:03,256 --> 00:22:06,783
-不，他说得没错，如果卷入战争… -你也错了
- No, he's right. If we get into this war... - And you're wrong.

419
00:22:06,926 --> 00:22:09,952
-你让我说完好吗？ -没必要说完
- Will you let me finish my sentence? - Your sentence is not worth finishing.

420
00:22:10,096 --> 00:22:12,758
成千上万的美国妇女过度操劳，营养不良
Thousands of American women, overworked, underfed,

421
00:22:12,865 --> 00:22:16,926
产下的贫血孩子连一年都活不了
are dying, giving birth to anemic children who can't last out a year.

422
00:22:17,036 --> 00:22:19,834
她们的生命难道就没美国男人重要？
Are their lives any less valuable than thousands of American boys'?

423
00:22:19,939 --> 00:22:22,601
-星期二我要收回 -我不是说，你认为…？
- I want those back Tuesday. - I'm not saying... Do you think?

424
00:22:22,909 --> 00:22:24,740
-该死 -完全正确
- Oh, shit. - Exactly.

425
00:22:24,844 --> 00:22:26,004
晚安
Good night.

426
00:22:26,112 --> 00:22:28,034
-要咖啡吗？ -“蔡斯桑博牌”的？
- You want some coffee? - Chase and Sanborn?

427
00:22:29,315 --> 00:22:31,772
-我没咖啡了 -又没了？我走了
- I'm out of coffee. - Again? I'm leaving.

428
00:22:32,718 --> 00:22:35,448
不，谈话结束了 你是个记者，杰克
No, the conversation is over. You're a journalist, Jack.

429
00:22:35,588 --> 00:22:37,681
等你成为革命者时 我们再考虑优先问题
When you're a revolutionary, we'll discuss priorities.

430
00:22:37,824 --> 00:22:39,052
希望咖啡真的没了
Hopefully over coffee.

431
00:22:39,192 --> 00:22:42,423
-很晚了，我送你回家吧 -为什么？我不会伤害任何人
- It's late, I'll walk you home. - Why? I won't hurt anybody.

432
00:22:50,269 --> 00:22:51,429
对了…
Well...

433
00:22:52,939 --> 00:22:53,997
没错
Yeah.

434
00:22:54,540 --> 00:22:56,167
今晚是周五晚
It's Friday night.

435
00:22:56,409 --> 00:22:57,933
很高兴见到你
I'm so glad to see you.

436
00:22:58,044 --> 00:23:00,239
真的，见到你很高兴
Really, I'm so glad to see you.

437
00:23:03,317 --> 00:23:05,581
我看完你的文章了，写得非常好
I finished your articles. They're very good.

438
00:23:05,686 --> 00:23:08,985
铁路文章，我认为还需要推敲润色
The railroad piece, I think, is... Needs polishing.

439
00:23:09,323 --> 00:23:11,314
-内容有重复，但是… -但是经过深思熟虑
- It's repetitious, but... - But that's deliberate.

440
00:23:11,458 --> 00:23:12,891
我是通过重复发表观点
I'm using repetition to make a point.

441
00:23:12,993 --> 00:23:14,324
我不希望它润色过度
I don't want it to seem too polished.

442
00:23:15,506 --> 00:23:16,466
Oh.

443
00:23:17,497 --> 00:23:19,624
我认为你会喜欢纽约的
Well, I think you're gonna love New York.

444
00:23:19,733 --> 00:23:21,428
埃玛…
Emma, Emma, Emma.

445
00:23:21,535 --> 00:23:23,594
全名应该是埃玛・高柏
I think it was Emma Goldberg.

446
00:23:23,704 --> 00:23:24,693
我觉得是
I think so.

447
00:23:24,805 --> 00:23:26,466
我从未忘记埃玛・高曼
I never forgot Emma Goldman.

448
00:23:26,573 --> 00:23:29,428
她启发我达到很深的思想深度
She inspired me to the very depths.

449
00:23:29,610 --> 00:23:32,465
麦斯・伊斯曼是大家都喜欢的人
And Max Eastman was a beloved man.

450
00:23:32,646 --> 00:23:35,501
思想激进，崇尚自由灵魂
The real radical, a free spirit.

451
00:23:35,682 --> 00:23:39,311
他和埃玛・高曼是一个组的
He was in that same group with that Emma Goldman.

452
00:23:39,419 --> 00:23:42,752
她应该姓高曼，不是高柏
That was her name. Goldman, not Goldberg.

453
00:23:42,890 --> 00:23:44,551
弗洛伊德・戴尔是其中一员
Floyd Dell was one of them.

454
00:23:44,691 --> 00:23:46,818
他写过小说，很优秀的小说
He wrote novels, beautiful novels.

455
00:23:46,994 --> 00:23:50,657
激进分子包括世界产业工人组织
The radicals included people like the IWWs

456
00:23:50,764 --> 00:23:52,288
还有比尔・海沃
and Bill Haywood.

457
00:23:52,399 --> 00:23:54,594
还有沃特・李普曼
And there were Walter Lippmann,

458
00:23:54,735 --> 00:23:57,568
林肯・史蒂芬和伊莎多拉・邓肯
and Lincoln Steffens and Isadora Duncan

459
00:23:57,671 --> 00:23:59,559
以及埃娜・圣文森特・米莱
and Edna St. Vincent Millay.

460
00:23:59,673 --> 00:24:01,368
埃弗德・史蒂里茨
Alfred Stieglitz...

461
00:24:01,508 --> 00:24:03,100
玛格丽特・桑格
Oh, and Margaret Sanger.

462
00:24:03,210 --> 00:24:05,508
天哪，我保护过她
My Lord, I picketed for her.

463
00:24:05,612 --> 00:24:08,137
当然，伟大的作家尤金・奥尼尔…
And, of course, the great writer Eugene O'Neill

464
00:24:08,215 --> 00:24:09,443
也是出自那里的
came from down there.

465
00:24:09,549 --> 00:24:13,178
至今我仍认为 没有人可以企及奥尼尔
I don't think there's anybody who can touch O'Neill today.

466
00:24:13,520 --> 00:24:17,684
我认为，要成为艺术家 必须具有一点叛逆精神
You have to be a bit of a rebel to be an artist of any kind, I believe.

467
00:24:18,292 --> 00:24:21,250
格林威治村民都有点叛逆
And everybody in Greenwich Village was a bit of a rebel.

468
00:24:29,903 --> 00:24:31,700
-你是做什么的，路易丝？ -写文章
- What do you do, Louise? - I write.

469
00:24:31,805 --> 00:24:34,069
很好嘛，可以把面包递给我吗？
Good for you. Could you pass the bread, please?

470
00:24:34,174 --> 00:24:35,368
-谢谢 -对中产阶级的美国人而言…
- Thanks. - Because to the middle-class American,

471
00:24:35,475 --> 00:24:37,670
左派的人都是一样的 无政府主义者，社会主义者…
everyone on the left is the same. An anarchist, a socialist...

472
00:24:45,752 --> 00:24:47,811
把面包递给我好吗？
Would you pass the bread, please?

473
00:24:48,555 --> 00:24:50,318
-你是做什么的，路易丝？ -写文章
- What do you do, Louise? - I write.

474
00:24:50,457 --> 00:24:52,482
不错，舒曼・汉克夫人…
Good. Madame Schumann-Heink...

475
00:24:52,626 --> 00:24:55,959
杰克说你是写文章的，拜伦小姐 你写的是哪类文章？
Jack tells me you write, Miss Bryant. What do you write about?

476
00:24:57,230 --> 00:24:58,458
什么都写
Everything.

477
00:24:59,533 --> 00:25:00,864
什么都写？
You write about everything?

478
00:25:02,169 --> 00:25:04,933
是的，什么都写，无所不写
Everything. Yes. Everything, nothing...

479
00:25:06,073 --> 00:25:07,301
只是…
Just...

480
00:25:09,209 --> 00:25:10,335
我明白了
I see.

481
00:25:12,579 --> 00:25:15,275
戴维斯和斯隆，他们辞职了？
Now, about Davis and Sloan, have they quit?

482
00:25:15,349 --> 00:25:16,338
还没，不过他们…
Not yet, but they...

483
00:25:23,790 --> 00:25:27,248
我认为他们不该这样坐在这里 这样太残酷
I don't think they should sit here like this. I don't. I think it's cruel.

484
00:25:27,828 --> 00:25:29,489
-只是… -组织，对吧？
- It's just... - Organization, right?

485
00:25:29,596 --> 00:25:31,552
资本家是做什么的？
Look, what does a capitalist do?

486
00:25:31,665 --> 00:25:33,656
请允许我问你这个问题，麦克？ 告诉我
Let me ask you that, Mike. Huh? Tell me.

487
00:25:33,767 --> 00:25:35,291
他们除了赚钱之外还干什么？
I mean, what does he make, besides money?

488
00:25:35,402 --> 00:25:37,996
我不知道 所有工作都是工人做的，不是吗？
I don't know what he makes. The workers do all the work, don't they?

489
00:25:38,105 --> 00:25:39,538
如果工人都被组织起来呢？
Well, what if they got organized?

490
00:25:39,639 --> 00:25:41,470
我是说所有的工人 不仅仅是水管工人…
I mean, all the workers. Not just the plumbers,

491
00:25:41,575 --> 00:25:43,634
还有木匠，雪茄师傅
and the carpenters and the goddamn cigar makers.

492
00:25:43,744 --> 00:25:45,109
世界上所有的工人
But all of them, all over the world?

493
00:25:45,212 --> 00:25:47,737
不仅仅是一个国家的 给他瓶啤酒好吗？
Not in just one country. Give him a beer, will you?

494
00:25:47,848 --> 00:25:49,281
如果他们都被组织起来呢？
What if they all got organized?

495
00:25:49,349 --> 00:25:51,806
难道你不认为他们可以… 可以改变社会秩序
Don't you think they could... They could change society overnight.

496
00:25:51,918 --> 00:25:53,078
他们可以把社会 变成他们喜欢的模式
They can make it into anything they wanted.

497
00:25:53,186 --> 00:25:55,609
杰克，可否给我5块钱？我没钱了
Jack, can I tap you for $5? I'm flat.

498
00:25:55,857 --> 00:25:59,088
别跟这个自命不凡的家伙要钱
Well, don't ask this pretentious son of a bitch for money.

499
00:25:59,360 --> 00:26:01,920
如果你需要5块钱，我可以给你
If you need $5, I'll give it to you.

500
00:26:04,799 --> 00:26:05,891
给我4块5好吗？
Let me have $4.50, will you?

501
00:26:06,000 --> 00:26:07,763
-公平是什么？ -明白我的意思吗？
- What isn't fair? - You see what I'm saying?

502
00:26:07,869 --> 00:26:10,599
如果全世界所有工人 都属于一个大公会
If all the workers in the world belonged to one big union,

503
00:26:10,705 --> 00:26:12,730
-那就不会有战争了，是吗？ -你在听我说吗？
- there wouldn't be a war, would there? - Are you listening to me?

504
00:26:12,840 --> 00:26:14,205
拜伦小姐
Miss Bryant.

505
00:26:14,842 --> 00:26:17,174
你守着那瓶啤酒已经一个小时了
You've been nursing that beer for an hour.

506
00:26:17,278 --> 00:26:18,870
要不要给你来杯红酒？
Can I get you a glass of wine or something?

507
00:26:18,980 --> 00:26:20,971
不用了，谢谢，我没事
No, thank you. I'm fine. Thank you, anyway.

508
00:26:21,082 --> 00:26:23,710
-啤酒就好 -你是个亲切的人
- Beer's fine. - You are an amiable person.

509
00:26:23,985 --> 00:26:25,612
听说也是个好画家
And a very good painter, I hear.

510
00:26:26,754 --> 00:26:27,948
我是作家
I write.

511
00:26:38,099 --> 00:26:39,555
看过杨
Read Jung!

512
00:26:39,901 --> 00:26:42,267
看过弗洛伊德，看过杨 看过恩格斯，麦斯
"Read Freud, read Jung." Read Engels, read Marx!

513
00:26:42,370 --> 00:26:45,362
天哪，你不能把弗洛伊德 加入到经济范筹
My God, you can't interpret Freud in an economic context.

514
00:26:45,473 --> 00:26:47,304
你知道出租车在等你吗？
You know you got a taxi waiting?

515
00:26:47,408 --> 00:26:49,638
索斯玛代表了宗教堕落
Zosima represents the corruption of religion.

516
00:26:49,744 --> 00:26:50,699
你这观点是错的
I tell you you're wrong.

517
00:26:50,812 --> 00:26:53,940
-杨是个神秘的… -但你真的认为…
- And Jung is a mystic... - But do you seriously believe...

518
00:26:55,750 --> 00:26:59,675
-他们要赖多久才走？ -不知道，应该快走了
- How long are they going to stay? - I don't know. They'll get out in a while.

519
00:26:59,787 --> 00:27:02,813
-我只离开一天而已 -你可刚从波士顿回来
- I'll only be gone for a day. - You just got back from Boston.

520
00:27:02,957 --> 00:27:04,356
你何不和我一起去巴尔的摩？
Hey, why don't you come with me to Baltimore?

521
00:27:04,459 --> 00:27:06,620
真的？我应该以什么身份去？
Really? What am I supposed to come to Baltimore as?

522
00:27:06,761 --> 00:27:08,058
什么身份？
What as?

523
00:27:08,162 --> 00:27:10,494
杰克，出租车在等你呢
Jack, you know, you got a taxi waiting.

524
00:27:11,699 --> 00:27:13,155
出租车在等呢，杰克
Taxi's waiting, Jack.

525
00:27:14,235 --> 00:27:15,532
明天见
See you tomorrow.

526
00:27:23,277 --> 00:27:25,700
我们努力了两年
We've been trying for two years.

527
00:27:25,813 --> 00:27:29,112
资本家们可随时根据 自己的意愿让国家卷入战火
Capitalists can take this country into war any time they damn well please.

528
00:27:29,183 --> 00:27:31,310
你唯一能施加影响的地方就是街道
The only impact you can make is in the streets.

529
00:27:31,419 --> 00:27:32,443
当然，可是…
Of course, but...

530
00:27:32,553 --> 00:27:34,509
可是，埃玛，你难道不认为…
But don't you think, Emma,

531
00:27:35,690 --> 00:27:38,352
如果戴布斯获得很多选票 这会否强化这种印象？
that if Debs gets a lot of votes, it'll strengthen that image?

532
00:27:38,493 --> 00:27:41,291
不，不会的，我认为选举 是这个国家的鸦片
No, I don't. I think voting is the opium of the masses in this country.

533
00:27:41,395 --> 00:27:43,260
每4年就要遭受这样的痛苦
Every four years, you deaden the pain.

534
00:27:43,364 --> 00:27:44,524
是的，但是…
Yeah, but...

535
00:27:46,367 --> 00:27:47,493
你不认为…
Don't you think...

536
00:27:47,602 --> 00:27:50,560
我已经很清楚地 表达了自己的想法，拜伦小姐
I just made it very clear what I think, Miss Bryant.

537
00:27:50,705 --> 00:27:52,866
别这样，埃玛，不要这么独断
Come on, E.G. Don't be so goddamn dogmatic.

538
00:27:52,974 --> 00:27:55,932
-路易丝有她自己的看法 -我突然变得独断了？
- Louise has a point. She says... - Suddenly I'm dogmatic.

539
00:27:56,043 --> 00:27:58,932
为何我每次身份改变 你就会带一个新的女人来，杰克？
Why does my status change every time you get a new woman, Jack?

540
00:27:59,046 --> 00:28:02,243
伯尼，可以给我来点红酒吗？ 路易丝，你要吗？
Bernie, could I have the red wine? Louise, would you like a glass?

541
00:28:02,316 --> 00:28:04,307
她有点…她有点烦我
She's just... She's upset with me.

542
00:28:04,418 --> 00:28:07,216
这跟你没关系，和你无关
It's got nothing to do with you. Nothing to do with you.

543
00:28:07,321 --> 00:28:09,983
谢谢，这话很舒心
Thank you. It's a great comfort.

544
00:28:10,391 --> 00:28:12,882
你离开后屋子里都挤满了人
The house is completely filled with people when you're gone.

545
00:28:13,027 --> 00:28:14,858
他们简直把它当会议室了
They use it as if it was a meeting hall or something.

546
00:28:14,962 --> 00:28:17,157
-我根本没法工作 -那就赶他们走
- I can't get any work done. - Just throw them out.

547
00:28:17,265 --> 00:28:18,926
-怎么赶？ -直接赶走
- How am I supposed to throw them out? - Just kick them out.

548
00:28:19,033 --> 00:28:20,091
叫他们离开
Tell them to leave.

549
00:28:20,201 --> 00:28:21,634
我不会叫麦斯・伊斯曼离开
I'm not going to say to Max Eastman, "Leave."

550
00:28:21,736 --> 00:28:23,169
-只管赶他们走 -杰克？
- Just throw them out. - Jack?

551
00:28:23,271 --> 00:28:26,035
杰克，是你吗？ 见到你太高兴了
Jack, is that you? Jack, it's very good to see you.

552
00:28:26,140 --> 00:28:28,597
-贺瑞斯，近来好吗？ -很高兴见到你
- Hello, Horace. How are you? - Very good to see you.

553
00:28:30,044 --> 00:28:32,672
-认识路易丝・拜伦吧？ -你好
- You know Louise Bryant? - Yes, hello. How are you?

554
00:28:32,780 --> 00:28:34,805
-很高兴见到你 -你好
- Very nice to see you. - How do you do?

555
00:28:34,916 --> 00:28:35,974
幸会
Great pleasure.

556
00:28:36,050 --> 00:28:38,006
-嗨，麦斯，你好吗？ -你好，贺瑞斯
- Hi, Max. How are you? - Divine, Horace.

557
00:28:38,119 --> 00:28:39,950
-幸会，弗洛伊德 -你好，贺瑞斯
- And Floyd, good to see you. - Hello, Horace.

558
00:28:40,121 --> 00:28:42,043
牢狱之灾还是不断吗，杰克？
Still getting arrested, Jack?

559
00:28:42,190 --> 00:28:43,282
试试吧
I try.

560
00:28:45,493 --> 00:28:46,517
你呢，拜伦小姐？
How about you, Miss Bryant?

561
00:28:46,661 --> 00:28:48,617
你也想尝试被捕吗？
Are you trying to get arrested, too?

562
00:28:48,763 --> 00:28:50,219
不，不想
No, not really.

563
00:28:52,166 --> 00:28:55,294
-你是做什么的，拜伦小姐？ -写文章
- What do you do, Miss Bryant? - I write.

564
00:28:55,836 --> 00:28:59,897
写文章？可否说一下都写些什么吗？
You write? Now, may I ask, what are you working on?

565
00:29:01,809 --> 00:29:04,004
无法形容
It's impossible to describe.

566
00:29:04,111 --> 00:29:05,510
无法形容？
It's impossible to describe?

567
00:29:05,613 --> 00:29:06,637
她刚刚写了篇文章
She just did a hell of a piece

568
00:29:06,747 --> 00:29:08,977
在纽约军械库展上反响很大 你应该读读
on the influence of the Armory Show and you ought to read it.

569
00:29:09,050 --> 00:29:11,245
那我真的要读一读了
Well, you know, I very much would like to read that.

570
00:29:11,786 --> 00:29:14,209
何不打电话到《大都会》找我？
Why don't you give me a call at The Metropolitan?

571
00:29:14,455 --> 00:29:17,253
或是周二我们出来喝两杯如何？
In fact, even better, why don't we have a drink on Thursday?

572
00:29:17,391 --> 00:29:20,019
-好吧 -我们可以聊聊纽约军械库展
- Fine. - We can talk about the Armory Show.

573
00:29:20,161 --> 00:29:21,389
-就这么约定了 -好吧
- It's a date, then. - Well, all right.

574
00:29:21,495 --> 00:29:22,951
太好了
That's wonderful. Fine.

575
00:29:23,064 --> 00:29:24,292
杰克！
Jack!

576
00:29:27,201 --> 00:29:29,726
别再被逮进去了，好吗？
Now, you stay out of the slammer, now, okay?

577
00:29:32,073 --> 00:29:34,701
再见，见到你很高兴
Goodbye. Goodbye. Goodbye. It's nice to see you.

578
00:29:36,744 --> 00:29:38,575
-杰克，不要这样做 -什么？
- Jack, please don't do that. - What?

579
00:29:38,679 --> 00:29:40,806
他是《大都会》的编辑 我认识他好几年了
He's the editor of Metropolitan. I've known him for years.

580
00:29:40,915 --> 00:29:43,941
-杰克，我可以为自己辩护 -你的文章也可以
- Jack, I can speak for myself. - So can your work.

581
00:29:44,018 --> 00:29:45,451
-我不想你这样做… -出租车在等着了，杰克
- I don't want you to do that... - Taxi's waiting, Jack.

582
00:29:45,553 --> 00:29:47,475
出租车在等着了，杰克
Oh. Taxi's waiting, Jack.

583
00:29:52,193 --> 00:29:53,319
杰克
Jack...

584
00:29:54,629 --> 00:29:57,052
周末见，好吗？
I'll see you at the end of the week, okay?

585
00:29:58,599 --> 00:29:59,657
-好吗？ -等等
- Okay? - Wait. Wait.

586
00:29:59,767 --> 00:30:02,156
或许我周四会给他电话
Maybe I will call him about Thursday.

587
00:30:02,270 --> 00:30:04,898
好的，周四给他电话
Yeah, call him about Thursday. Yeah, yeah.

588
00:30:05,006 --> 00:30:06,667
-再见，各位 -再见，杰克
- See you, boys. - Bye-bye, Jack.

589
00:30:06,774 --> 00:30:08,605
-再见，杰克 -再见
- Bye-bye, Jack. - See you.

590
00:30:09,443 --> 00:30:11,001
再见，杰克
See you, Jack.

591
00:30:17,018 --> 00:30:19,282
“铁路延伸到新的国境”
"The railroad's opening new frontiers,

592
00:30:19,654 --> 00:30:22,418
“所有的铁路交叉纵横”
"and crisscrossing it all are the railroads.

593
00:30:22,556 --> 00:30:24,786
“铁路延伸到新的国境”
"The railroad's opening new frontiers,

594
00:30:24,959 --> 00:30:27,223
“依次地，这些国境…”
"and in turn, these frontiers...

595
00:30:27,528 --> 00:30:29,758
“依次地，这些国境…”
"And in turn, these frontiers..."

596
00:30:29,864 --> 00:30:31,058
哦，天哪
Oh, God.

597
00:30:34,168 --> 00:30:35,658
这是重复
It is repetitious.

598
00:30:39,407 --> 00:30:41,466
我们不是人，我们是商品
We're not human beings, we're a commodity.

599
00:30:41,575 --> 00:30:43,202
-一周工作多少天？ -七天
- And how many days a week? - Seven days.

600
00:30:43,311 --> 00:30:44,437
-每天工作？ -他们说了…
- Every day? - They said,

601
00:30:44,545 --> 00:30:47,776
如果你周日不来上班 周一就不要来了
"If you don't come to work on Sunday, don't come on Monday."

602
00:30:47,882 --> 00:30:49,873
-一小时工钱是多少？ -20美分
- What do you make an hour? - 20 cents.

603
00:30:49,950 --> 00:30:52,646
因为工作不熟练，他们有多少次…
How many times have they slammed the door on your face

604
00:30:52,753 --> 00:30:55,210
让你们吃闭门羹？
because the labor you do is called unskilled?

605
00:30:55,356 --> 00:30:56,414
没事的，比尔
That's right, Bill.

606
00:30:56,557 --> 00:30:58,889
世界产业工人组织 不会因你们技术不熟练…
Well, the IWW's not gonna turn you down

607
00:30:58,993 --> 00:31:00,654
-就把你们拒之门外 -听他的，乔治
- because you're unskilled. - Listen to him, George.

608
00:31:01,095 --> 00:31:04,553
肤色不限，黑色，白色，黄色都行
Or skilled. Or black or white or yellow.

609
00:31:04,699 --> 00:31:05,961
一周工作7天
Seven days a week.

610
00:31:06,067 --> 00:31:08,092
-一小时工钱是多少？ -10美分
- What do you make an hour? - 10 cents an hour.

611
00:31:08,202 --> 00:31:09,157
一个大工会联盟
One big union.

612
00:31:09,770 --> 00:31:13,467
-所有工人都属于… -都看看，这很重要
- All workers belong... - Listen, read that. That's important.

613
00:31:13,941 --> 00:31:16,774
我在找一个叫 帕斯奎・埃伯迪的车工
I'm looking for a lathe worker named Pasquale Alberti.

614
00:31:16,877 --> 00:31:19,869
他出了工伤事故，腿被压断了 认识他吗？
He had an industrial accident. He got his leg crushed. Do you know him?

615
00:31:19,980 --> 00:31:21,504
当然认识，哈佛
Yeah, sure, Harvard.

616
00:31:21,615 --> 00:31:24,038
这就是他们在格林威治村所报导的？
Is that what they wanna read about in Greenwich Village now,

617
00:31:24,118 --> 00:31:25,278
工伤事故？
industrial accidents?

618
00:31:28,222 --> 00:31:30,053
因此，我们需要权力
And for that, we need power.

619
00:31:30,391 --> 00:31:32,916
只有一种方式才能获得权力
And there's only one way to get power.

620
00:31:33,294 --> 00:31:34,522
组织起来
Organize!

621
00:31:34,628 --> 00:31:36,994
所有工人一条心
All the workers together!

622
00:31:37,098 --> 00:31:38,793
一个大工会！
One big union!

623
00:31:39,133 --> 00:31:43,593
世界产业工人组织需要你们 加入到阶级斗争中来
And the war the IWW wants you to get into is class war!

624
00:31:43,704 --> 00:31:45,399
欧洲没有战争！
Not a war in Europe!

625
00:31:45,539 --> 00:31:47,666
推翻资产阶级！
War against the capitalists!

626
00:31:47,775 --> 00:31:50,164
你们会一无所有
You'll never get anything or anywhere,

627
00:31:50,277 --> 00:31:54,065
除非整个工人阶级属于一个大…
until the whole working class belongs to one big...

628
00:31:54,682 --> 00:31:56,377
好了，先生们
All right, gentlemen,

629
00:31:56,450 --> 00:31:59,339
你们有20秒的时间离开
you've got 20 seconds to vacate the premises.

630
00:32:06,594 --> 00:32:08,687
你们有何授权？
May I ask on what authority?

631
00:32:08,829 --> 00:32:10,353
我的授权
On my authority.

632
00:32:10,598 --> 00:32:12,486
这是非法集会
This is an illegal assembly.

633
00:32:12,600 --> 00:32:15,091
对不起，警官 这些人都是合法集会的
Excuse me, Officer. These men have the legal right to assemble.

634
00:32:15,202 --> 00:32:16,396
这就是他们正在做的事情
That's all they're doing.

635
00:32:16,504 --> 00:32:18,165
我们知道他们做什么
We know what the hell they doing.

636
00:32:18,272 --> 00:32:20,160
-你在这里做什么？ -我？
- What the hell you doing? - Me?

637
00:32:20,274 --> 00:32:21,332
就是你
You.

638
00:32:21,442 --> 00:32:22,898
-我写作 -写作？
- I write. - You write?

639
00:32:23,978 --> 00:32:25,036
你错了
You wrong.

640
00:32:28,916 --> 00:32:30,372
把他带走！
Get him out of here!

641
00:32:35,389 --> 00:32:36,754
就是它们哪
Here they are.

642
00:32:36,891 --> 00:32:38,051
对开的纸，全部作品
The folio. The oeuvre.

643
00:32:41,648 --> 00:32:42,816
Well...

644
00:32:43,798 --> 00:32:45,060
杰克还好吗？
How is Jack?

645
00:32:45,166 --> 00:32:48,590
希望他最近写作最好能小心谨慎点
I do hope he's being more careful about what he's writing these days.

646
00:32:48,702 --> 00:32:50,693
我不想看到他的作品无法出版
I'd hate to see him not able to get into print.

647
00:32:50,805 --> 00:32:52,568
他能应付得来的
Oh, I'm sure he'll do fine.

648
00:32:53,908 --> 00:32:57,435
你告诉他我们在哪里喝酒了吗？
Did you tell him where we were having drinks?

649
00:32:57,611 --> 00:32:59,442
没有，我会的，他出城了
No, I will. He's out of town.

650
00:32:59,547 --> 00:33:02,937
威汉先生，对不起 纽约军械库展的文章在最上面
Mr. Whigham, excuse me, but the Armory Show piece is on the top.

651
00:33:03,017 --> 00:33:04,939
这是军械…
Oh, this is the Armory...

652
00:33:05,052 --> 00:33:08,010
-是的 -是的，当然
- Yes. - Yes. Of course. Here it is.

653
00:33:15,145 --> 00:33:16,438
Well...

654
00:33:16,997 --> 00:33:19,295
我还需要点时间来拜读
I really ought to spend more time on this.

655
00:33:19,400 --> 00:33:20,833
当然可以
Oh, yes, of course.

656
00:33:21,202 --> 00:33:22,533
共进晚餐如何？
What about dinner?

657
00:33:23,604 --> 00:33:25,936
-晚餐？ -杰克不会介意的
- Dinner? - Jack wouldn't mind.

658
00:33:27,074 --> 00:33:29,929
-他为什么要介意？ -当然，我们都是成年人了
- Why would he mind? - Well, we're all grownups, of course,

659
00:33:30,044 --> 00:33:31,909
不过杰克非常的…
but Jack's rather...

660
00:33:32,546 --> 00:33:34,377
他是个非常古怪的家伙
He's rather an odd duck, isn't he?

661
00:33:34,482 --> 00:33:35,710
我一直不知道…
And I've never really known how...

662
00:33:35,783 --> 00:33:37,045
威汉先生，你是说…
Mr. Whigham, are you saying you need

663
00:33:37,151 --> 00:33:39,415
和我约会要获得杰克的许可？
Jack's permission to make a pass at me?

664
00:33:42,456 --> 00:33:43,548
不要为此烦恼
Don't get so upset about it.

665
00:33:43,691 --> 00:33:45,420
老天，我作了两个小小变动
For Christ's sake, I made two little tiny changes...

666
00:33:45,559 --> 00:33:47,015
不要修改我写的，彼得
Don't rewrite what I write, Pete.

667
00:33:47,127 --> 00:33:49,152
你到底是怎么了，杰克？
What the hell's the matter with you, Jack?

668
00:33:49,296 --> 00:33:51,389
世界产业工人组织是赤色份子
The IWW's a bunch of Reds.

669
00:33:51,499 --> 00:33:52,557
拜托
Come on.

670
00:33:52,867 --> 00:33:55,165
世界产业工人组织有赤色份子 村子里有赤色份子
We got Reds in the IWW, got Reds in the Village.

671
00:33:55,269 --> 00:33:56,998
除了赤色份子这里什么都没有
We've got nothing but Reds around here.

672
00:33:57,104 --> 00:33:59,993
老天，你是这里最好的作家
For Christ's sake, you're the best goddamn writer around.

673
00:34:00,107 --> 00:34:01,734
你何必浪费时间和精力…
Now, what the hell you wanna waste your time

674
00:34:01,842 --> 00:34:03,969
来写那些别人不会出版的赤色文章？
with a lot of Red propaganda nobody's ever gonna print?

675
00:34:04,078 --> 00:34:06,000
这是真理，这理由够充分吗？
It's the truth. Does that mean anything around here?

676
00:34:06,113 --> 00:34:07,637
谁说那些东西是真理的？
Well, who the hell's to say what the truth is?

677
00:34:07,748 --> 00:34:09,613
世界产业工人组织的那帮赤色份子？
A bunch of goddamn Reds in the IWW?

678
00:34:09,683 --> 00:34:11,605
你对左派那些人并不公平
You're not being fair to the AF of L.

679
00:34:11,719 --> 00:34:14,517
-快把那篇文章给我 -你要修改我的文章？
- Now, give me the goddamn article... - You're gonna rewrite what I write.

680
00:34:14,622 --> 00:34:16,715
我拿给愿意出版的杂志社
I'm just gonna take it to a magazine that won't.

681
00:34:16,857 --> 00:34:18,449
好吧，拿去给《大众》
Well, fine. Take it to The Masses.

682
00:34:18,592 --> 00:34:19,889
-他们是帮赤色份子 -谢谢
- They're a bunch of Reds. - Thank you.

683
00:34:19,994 --> 00:34:22,053
-谁来支付你的租金？ -这你不用担心，彼得
- Who's gonna pay your rent? - Rent's easy, Pete.

684
00:34:22,196 --> 00:34:25,051
你不要修改我的文章就行，明白吗？
You just don't rewrite what I write. You got that? Don't rewrite what I write.

685
00:34:25,165 --> 00:34:28,259
你这倔驴子，谁来支付你的租金？
You stubborn son of a bitch. Who's gonna pay your rent?

686
00:34:44,351 --> 00:34:45,443
路易丝？
Louise?

687
00:35:03,604 --> 00:35:05,401
我把店里的都买来了
I got every one in the shop.

688
00:35:06,073 --> 00:35:08,029
我们虽然窘迫，但我还是都买下了
We're broke, but we've got them all.

689
00:35:12,246 --> 00:35:13,270
谢谢
Thanks.

690
00:35:17,384 --> 00:35:19,272
-怎么了？ -没什么
- What's the matter? - Nothing.

691
00:35:19,386 --> 00:35:22,116
-怎么了？ -没事，旅途如何？
- What is it? - It's nothing. How'd it go?

692
00:35:22,389 --> 00:35:24,016
比预期的要好多了
A lot better than we thought it would.

693
00:35:24,158 --> 00:35:26,991
-你见到威汉了？ -昨天见了
- You see Whigham? - Yesterday.

694
00:35:27,094 --> 00:35:30,018
-怎么样？ -我们主要还是谈你的事
- How was that? - We mostly talked about you, of course.

695
00:35:30,130 --> 00:35:31,586
他给你提供工作了？
Did he offer you work?

696
00:35:31,699 --> 00:35:33,428
没有，不过他向我大说特说…
No, but he made a big point of telling me

697
00:35:33,534 --> 00:35:36,128
你和他这么多年的友情有多伟大
what wonderful friends you and he have become over the years.

698
00:35:36,236 --> 00:35:38,124
这是次美好会面
It was a fascinating meeting.

699
00:35:39,573 --> 00:35:41,564
你是在生威汉的气还是生我的气？
Are you angry at Whigham or me?

700
00:35:44,178 --> 00:35:45,270
怎么啦？
What is it?

701
00:35:45,579 --> 00:35:47,467
没什么，你说过周二就回的
It's nothing. You said you'd be back Tuesday

702
00:35:47,581 --> 00:35:48,809
今天都周六了
and it's Saturday.

703
00:35:49,049 --> 00:35:50,812
我不是说周末回家吗？
Didn't I say I'd back at the end of the week?

704
00:35:50,918 --> 00:35:53,216
-周末是星期五 -周末是星期五？
- The end of the week is Friday. - The end of the week is Friday?

705
00:35:53,320 --> 00:35:54,753
星期六不是周末了？
Saturday's not the end of the week anymore, huh?

706
00:35:54,855 --> 00:35:56,253
杰克，你说过周二就回的！
Jack, you said you'd be back Tuesday!

707
00:35:56,389 --> 00:35:57,412
这有什么区别？
What difference does it make?

708
00:35:57,557 --> 00:35:58,614
你认为我一直在做什么？
What do you think I've been doing?

709
00:35:58,758 --> 00:36:00,622
到处跑去听自己夸夸其谈吗？
Running around listening to the sound of my own voice?

710
00:36:00,727 --> 00:36:02,682
我怎么知道你去听谁夸夸其谈？
How do I know whose voice you've been listening to?

711
00:36:02,795 --> 00:36:05,285
显然你喜欢它更胜过我！
Obviously you like it a lot better than mine!

712
00:36:16,175 --> 00:36:17,869
天哪，看看我
Look at me. Oh, God!

713
00:36:18,878 --> 00:36:20,276
我就像一个妻子
I'm like a wife.

714
00:36:22,048 --> 00:36:26,973
我就像一个烦人的 粘人的，痛苦的小妻子
I'm like a boring, clinging, miserable little wife.

715
00:36:28,221 --> 00:36:30,711
-谁会想回家看我？ -我！
- Who'd wanna come home to me? - Me!

716
00:36:31,324 --> 00:36:33,120
我受不了了，我再也不能这样做了！
Well, I can't do this! I can't do this anymore!

717
00:36:33,226 --> 00:36:34,681
你不能做什么？
You can't do what?

718
00:36:35,995 --> 00:36:37,450
我就像是生活在你的边缘上
I'm just living in your margins.

719
00:36:37,597 --> 00:36:40,156
我不知道自己在这干嘛 我不知道自己的目标是什么
I don't know what I'm doing here. I don't know what my purpose is.

720
00:36:40,266 --> 00:36:43,462
-告诉我你想做什么 -我不想再需要你！
- Well, tell me what you want. - I want to stop needing you!

721
00:36:43,603 --> 00:36:44,557
还有一件事
I want you to know something.

722
00:36:44,671 --> 00:36:47,093
我问威汉是否可以派我去法国
I asked Whigham if he'd send me to France.

723
00:36:49,542 --> 00:36:52,032
-这就是你想要的？ -没错
- Is that what you want? - That's what I want.

724
00:36:56,382 --> 00:36:58,576
-你要做什么，路易丝？ -我不能在你身边工作
- What are you doing, Louise? - I can't work around you.

725
00:36:58,685 --> 00:36:59,673
你为什么要这样做？
Will you tell me why you're doing this?

726
00:36:59,786 --> 00:37:01,514
你在我身边时，我没法严肃起来
I'm not taken seriously when you're around.

727
00:37:01,621 --> 00:37:02,917
我在你身边你没法严肃起来？
When I'm around you're not taken seriously?

728
00:37:03,056 --> 00:37:04,181
天哪，简直糟透了
Oh, God, this is not good.

729
00:37:04,323 --> 00:37:05,721
你认为我需要更加严肃？
You mean you think I'm taken more seriously?

730
00:37:05,825 --> 00:37:06,779
你是想这样说吗？
Is that what you're talking about?

731
00:37:06,893 --> 00:37:08,484
你难道不认为吗？杰克
Do you mean you're not? Come on, Jack.

732
00:37:08,628 --> 00:37:10,720
你明白我在说什么，你对我一直不坦白
You know what I'm saying. You're not being honest with me.

733
00:37:10,830 --> 00:37:11,818
我不知道你在说什么
I don't know what you're saying.

734
00:37:11,964 --> 00:37:14,523
你对我一直不够坦白 请对我坦白点吧
You're not being honest with me. Please, be honest with me.

735
00:37:14,634 --> 00:37:15,622
我对你非常的坦白
I am so being honest with you.

736
00:37:15,735 --> 00:37:18,498
如果你让自己严肃一点 对方也会这样的
Maybe if you took yourself a little more seriously, other people would, too.

737
00:37:18,604 --> 00:37:20,161
我告诉过你我对军械展文章的看法
I told you what I thought about the Armory piece.

738
00:37:20,273 --> 00:37:21,261
我对此已经很坦白
I was honest about that.

739
00:37:21,374 --> 00:37:23,864
我认为那篇文章很好 但我并没严肃对待它
I think it's very nice, but no, I don't take it very seriously.

740
00:37:23,976 --> 00:37:25,033
-谢谢 -如果你的文章不严肃…
- Thank you. - Why do you even expect

741
00:37:25,144 --> 00:37:28,203
你为什么又期望 别人会严肃对待它们？
to be taken seriously if you're not writing about serious things?

742
00:37:28,281 --> 00:37:29,508
我不明白
I don't understand that.

743
00:37:29,615 --> 00:37:31,741
我给自己找了间公寓，我要自己找一个
I found myself an apartment. I'm looking for one.

744
00:37:31,851 --> 00:37:33,909
我甚至不知道 你所谓的严肃事情是什么
I'm not even sure I know what things you're serious about.

745
00:37:34,020 --> 00:37:35,281
你先是写关于铁路的文章
One day you're writing about the railroads,

746
00:37:35,421 --> 00:37:36,580
但却一直没写完
and you don't even finish the piece.

747
00:37:36,723 --> 00:37:38,644
然后你又要写一篇发生在3年前的…
The next day you're doing a piece on an art exhibition

748
00:37:38,758 --> 00:37:40,190
有关艺术展的文章
that happened three years ago.

749
00:37:40,293 --> 00:37:42,055
为何你什么都要给我看？
Look, why do you give me anything to read, anyway?

750
00:37:42,161 --> 00:37:44,583
如果我提出异议 你就说你喜欢这样写
If I criticize it at all, you tell me you like it the way it is.

751
00:37:44,697 --> 00:37:46,095
当我们和其他人一起出去…
And when we're out with other people,

752
00:37:46,199 --> 00:37:47,961
如果有人没直接问你问题…
if somebody doesn't ask you a direct question,

753
00:37:48,067 --> 00:37:49,397
你就会说你觉得受到了忽视
you tell me you feel ignored.

754
00:37:49,502 --> 00:37:51,526
但是，这样的事情每天都在发生
But with everything that's happening in the world today,

755
00:37:51,637 --> 00:37:53,263
你决定坐下来写文章…
you decide to sit down and write a piece

756
00:37:53,372 --> 00:37:57,102
写有关1913年纽约军械库展的影响
on the influence of the goddamned Armory Show of 1913!

757
00:37:57,210 --> 00:37:58,870
人们应该严肃对待它吗？
Are people supposed to take that seriously?

758
00:37:58,978 --> 00:38:00,205
我真的不在乎！
Well, I don't really care!

759
00:38:00,313 --> 00:38:01,677
-你在乎！ -我真的不在乎！
- You care! - I'm not really... I don't care!

760
00:38:01,781 --> 00:38:03,338
-你在乎 -我不在乎！
- You care! - I don't care!

761
00:38:03,416 --> 00:38:06,475
你那些愚蠢朋友严不严肃对待我…
And I'm not interested in whether your stupid friends

762
00:38:06,586 --> 00:38:08,746
-我并不感兴趣 -他们不会严肃对待
- take me seriously or not! - Well, they don't take it seriously.

763
00:38:08,888 --> 00:38:10,047
这是因为他们并不严肃对待它
That's why they don't take it seriously.

764
00:38:10,189 --> 00:38:12,247
我在休斯顿大街找了一间公寓 我要搬进去
I found an apartment on Houston Street, and I'm moving in.

765
00:38:12,391 --> 00:38:14,881
我再告诉你，杰克・雷德
And I'll tell you something else, Jack Reed.

766
00:38:15,027 --> 00:38:17,358
我认为我们是志不同不相为谋
I don't think we like the same people or the same kind of life.

767
00:38:17,463 --> 00:38:19,418
-我要过自己的生活 -你只管走！
- And I wanna be on my own. - Go ahead, be on your own!

768
00:38:19,565 --> 00:38:21,122
我不在乎，你去过你自己的吧
I don't give a damn! You're on your own anyway.

769
00:38:21,234 --> 00:38:22,825
我知道你不在乎！
Oh! I know you don't give a damn!

770
00:38:22,935 --> 00:38:24,561
你告诉我，我为什么要在乎？
Well, will you tell me why the hell I should give a damn?

771
00:38:24,670 --> 00:38:25,931
你不该在乎！那就不要在乎！
You shouldn't! Don't give a damn!

772
00:38:26,038 --> 00:38:28,562
-我也不在乎 -没错，我不在乎
- I don't give a damn, either! - That's right! I don't give a damn!

773
00:38:28,673 --> 00:38:32,005
-我要离开这里 -好啊，我也离开
- I'm getting out of here! - Good, fine! I'm leaving, too!

774
00:39:19,057 --> 00:39:22,719
亲爱的，我们可否离开纽约？
Honey, can we just get out of New York?

775
00:39:23,962 --> 00:39:26,156
我们去别的地方，写我们想写的东西
Let's go somewhere and just write what we wanna write.

776
00:40:00,165 --> 00:40:05,090
普罗旺斯是个小渔村
Provincetown was just a tiny little fishing village.

777
00:40:05,537 --> 00:40:09,097
那里非常的保守
And it was very, very conservative.

778
00:40:09,574 --> 00:40:13,100
我们每逢夏天 都乘坐蒸汽船去富尔河
We'd take the Fall River steamer up there, I remember, every summer.

779
00:40:13,211 --> 00:40:15,770
为节省费用，都是睡在隔层硬铺
We used to save fares by sleeping in tiers.

780
00:40:15,847 --> 00:40:17,734
我们经常受到臭虫的骚扰
And we always got bedbugs.

781
00:40:17,849 --> 00:40:19,804
在那里喜欢做什么就做什么
You did whatever you pleased up there.

782
00:40:19,918 --> 00:40:23,375
我们还表演一些非常有趣的话剧
And we put on some very interesting plays, experimental plays

783
00:40:23,521 --> 00:40:25,943
那种正规剧院不会严处的话剧
that a commercial theater couldn't possibly do.

784
00:40:26,057 --> 00:40:28,889
苏珊・格拉斯佩的《琐事》
Take Susan Glaspell's Trifles.

785
00:40:29,027 --> 00:40:30,516
整个话剧…
There's a whole play

786
00:40:30,662 --> 00:40:34,051
没有主角，甚至没有舞台
without the protagonist even appearing on the stage.

787
00:40:34,165 --> 00:40:36,587
他们还举行了三场独幕戏
And they gave three one-act plays.

788
00:40:36,835 --> 00:40:38,790
其中一个话剧是由…
One of them was a play by...

789
00:40:38,904 --> 00:40:42,430
我一直认为是 约翰・雷德和路易丝・拜伦扮演的
I always thought it was by John Reed and Louise Bryant.

790
00:40:42,707 --> 00:40:44,401
应该就是由她演的
But I see it's by her.

791
00:40:44,509 --> 00:40:45,532
他们都在剧中
They were in it.

792
00:40:45,644 --> 00:40:48,441
那出话剧很糟糕 而他们表现得更糟糕
The play was terrible, and they were worse.

793
00:40:49,014 --> 00:40:51,971
当然，尤金・奥尼尔是以诗歌着称的
And of course, Gene O'Neill was known as the poet,

794
00:40:52,384 --> 00:40:55,272
不过我喜欢他的话剧 胜过他的诗歌
but I liked his plays better than his poetry.

795
00:40:55,954 --> 00:40:57,011
你怎样才能明白？
Will you never understand?

796
00:40:57,155 --> 00:40:59,714
你是不是愚笨到不明白我的意思？
Are you so stupid that you do not know what I mean?

797
00:40:59,858 --> 00:41:01,485
我把自己献给你
I am offering myself to you.

798
00:41:01,626 --> 00:41:03,548
我跪在你的面前
I am kneeling before you.

799
00:41:03,795 --> 00:41:05,888
我承诺过把身体献给你
I have promised you my body,

800
00:41:05,997 --> 00:41:08,227
男人们都为之迷倒的身体
my body that men have found so beautiful.

801
00:41:08,333 --> 00:41:12,099
我承诺过要爱你，黑人水手
I have promised to love you, a negro sailor!

802
00:41:13,204 --> 00:41:16,264
告诉他们，不要站在月亮后面
Tell them not to stand behind the moon.

803
00:41:16,841 --> 00:41:18,468
不要站在月亮后面
Don't stand behind the moon.

804
00:41:18,777 --> 00:41:20,438
-后面？ -你能退后一点吗？
- Back? - Can you step back a little bit?

805
00:41:21,046 --> 00:41:22,172
因为月亮
'Cause of the moon.

806
00:41:22,247 --> 00:41:23,805
这是月亮
This is the moon here.

807
00:41:24,049 --> 00:41:25,311
-这边？ -是的
- This way? - Yes.

808
00:41:25,583 --> 00:41:27,539
从“我讨厌大海”那段开始
Take it from "I hate the sea."

809
00:41:27,719 --> 00:41:28,811
你怎样才能明白？
Will you never understand?

810
00:41:28,920 --> 00:41:30,945
你是不是愚笨到不明白我的意思？
Are you so stupid that you don't know what I mean?

811
00:41:31,089 --> 00:41:32,784
我把自己献给你
I'm offering myself to you.

812
00:41:32,924 --> 00:41:35,222
我跪在你的面前
I'm kneeling before you.

813
00:41:35,327 --> 00:41:38,160
有多少男人曾经拜倒在我的面前
I... I, who have had so many men kneel before me,

814
00:41:38,263 --> 00:41:40,128
我把我的身体献给你
I'm offering you my body,

815
00:41:40,231 --> 00:41:43,120
男人们都为之迷倒的身体
my body that men have found so beautiful.

816
00:41:43,768 --> 00:41:45,827
我承诺过要爱你
I have promised to love you.

817
00:41:45,937 --> 00:41:47,825
黑人水手
You, a negro sailor.

818
00:41:47,939 --> 00:41:51,431
你让我等待 这难道不是奇耻大辱吗？
Is that not humiliation enough that you must keep me waiting so?

819
00:41:51,710 --> 00:41:53,701
回答我，请回答我！
Answer me, please! Answer me.

820
00:41:53,845 --> 00:41:55,733
请把水给我好吗？
Will you give me that water?

821
00:41:57,182 --> 00:41:59,047
我没有水
I have no water.

822
00:41:59,884 --> 00:42:01,647
老泰迪想打这场战争，对吗？
Old Teddy wants this war, doesn't he?

823
00:42:01,753 --> 00:42:04,313
不知道人们要多久才会 明白他是个疯子
I wonder how long it'll take the public to find out he's a maniac.

824
00:42:04,456 --> 00:42:07,050
泰迪・罗斯福有狂犬病 全体军事训练
Teddy Roosevelt has rabies. Universal military training.

825
00:42:07,192 --> 00:42:08,784
杰克，你的二次演讲完了
Jack, your second speech is out.

826
00:42:08,927 --> 00:42:11,657
其中最讽刺的就是穷人们都爱戴他
And the ironic part of it is that poor people, they love him.

827
00:42:11,763 --> 00:42:14,618
他们当然爱 他们会再次把他拥上圣胡安山
Sure, they do. They'll take him up San Juan Hill again.

828
00:42:14,733 --> 00:42:16,564
你不能碰那个兔装，那是租来的
You can't touch the bunny suit. It's rented.

829
00:42:16,668 --> 00:42:17,965
你有看过大会上那篇文章吗？
Did you read the piece on the convention?

830
00:42:18,069 --> 00:42:20,435
如果左派不防卫威尔逊 休斯总统就遭殃了
If the left doesn't defend Wilson, we're gonna get President Hughes.

831
00:42:20,538 --> 00:42:21,664
我们应该去圣路易斯吗？
Think we ought to go to St. Louis?

832
00:42:21,773 --> 00:42:23,536
我不去圣路易斯保护威尔逊
I am not going to St. Louis to defend Wilson.

833
00:42:23,641 --> 00:42:25,597
-我认为我们应该去 -为什么？这样做有什么好处吗？
- I think we should. - Why? What good would it do?

834
00:42:25,710 --> 00:42:27,575
我不知道 如果你认为休斯不会在几个月内…
I don't know, if you don't think Hughes would have us

835
00:42:27,679 --> 00:42:29,738
让我们卷入战火，那就没任何好处
in a war in a few months, it wouldn't do any good at all.

836
00:42:29,814 --> 00:42:31,441
威尔逊把我们远远地排斥在外
Wilson's kept us out so far.

837
00:42:32,117 --> 00:42:33,846
雷德认为自己是个好诗人
Reed thought that he was a good poet.

838
00:42:33,952 --> 00:42:35,783
他是个糟糕的诗人
He was a terrible poet.

839
00:42:35,987 --> 00:42:38,217
他认为自己可以写出优秀的小说
He thought that he could write good novels.

840
00:42:38,356 --> 00:42:39,516
短篇小说
Short stories.

841
00:42:39,958 --> 00:42:41,391
当然，他是个诗人
Of course, he was a poet.

842
00:42:41,493 --> 00:42:44,951
但不是个伟大的诗人
And not a great poet,

843
00:42:45,397 --> 00:42:47,820
有些诗还是不错的
but some of it was very fine.

844
00:42:48,199 --> 00:42:52,056
但作为一个记者 杰克・雷德远远胜过他们
But, as a journalist, Jack Reed topped them all.

845
00:42:52,570 --> 00:42:54,629
-把这个往上拉 -杰克
- Look. Pull this up. - Hey, Jack.

846
00:42:54,739 --> 00:42:56,502
瞧见没？不错吧
See? That's good.

847
00:42:56,808 --> 00:42:58,400
杰克，你的车来了
Jack, your ride's here.

848
00:42:59,277 --> 00:43:01,973
-对不起，我在外面等 -好的
- Excuse me. I'll wait outside. - Okay. Okay.

849
00:43:03,515 --> 00:43:06,541
-明白我的意思吗？如果… -杰克，出租车在等着呢
- Do you see what I mean? If one... - Jack, the taxi's waiting.

850
00:43:10,588 --> 00:43:12,021
好吧，我该走了
Yeah, I got to run.

851
00:43:15,427 --> 00:43:16,416
再见，亲爱的
Bye, honey.

852
00:43:24,569 --> 00:43:26,594
杰克・雷德想挑起矛盾
Jack Reed wanted to stir up trouble,

853
00:43:26,704 --> 00:43:29,002
他想给资产阶级带来麻烦
he wanted to stir up trouble for the capitalists.

854
00:43:29,107 --> 00:43:32,463
他也想唤醒工人大众…
And he also wanted to arouse the working masses

855
00:43:32,710 --> 00:43:36,168
联合起来争取一些实效
to the necessity of some kind of effective united action.

856
00:43:36,347 --> 00:43:41,205
换句话说，我当他是个爱管闲事的人
In other words, I am accusing him of either being a busybody

857
00:43:41,453 --> 00:43:45,241
或者说是一个胆小鬼
or of being a fraidy-cat,

858
00:43:45,390 --> 00:43:47,620
不想面对自己的未来
not wanting to face things of his own nature.

859
00:43:51,996 --> 00:43:55,454
亲爱的路易丝 圣路易斯现在很热，到处是民主党员
Dear Louise, St. Louis is very hot and very crowded with Democrats,

860
00:43:55,567 --> 00:43:58,422
大家都很开心，戴着纸帽
all having a wonderful time and wearing little paper hats

861
00:43:58,536 --> 00:44:00,367
和预料中威尔逊的任命一样
in anticipation of Wilson's nomination.

862
00:44:00,472 --> 00:44:01,632
我希望这是因为…
I'd like to think it's because

863
00:44:01,739 --> 00:44:03,661
他不想让美国卷入战争
he doesn't want the United States to go into the war,

864
00:44:03,775 --> 00:44:05,606
但谁知道民主党人在想什么呢？
but who knows the mind of a Democrat?

865
00:44:05,710 --> 00:44:08,599
对了，我已经决定摒弃那首百合诗
By the way, I've decided to throw out the poem on white lilies.

866
00:44:08,680 --> 00:44:10,136
诗中的压韵错误了
The rhyming scheme was wrong.

867
00:44:10,248 --> 00:44:12,341
等我回来再重写
Maybe when I get back I can start it again.

868
00:44:12,450 --> 00:44:14,975
政治严重影响了诗歌创作
Politics sure plays hell with your poetry.

869
00:44:15,086 --> 00:44:17,850
我一直都很想见到你，这是最迫切的
I keep thinking I see you. It's the damnedest thing.

870
00:44:17,989 --> 00:44:20,446
我想你，亲爱的 想念一起在沙滩上漫步
I miss you, honey. I miss walking on the beach.

871
00:45:04,969 --> 00:45:07,062
-你好 -威士忌在哪？
- Hello. - Where's the whiskey?

872
00:45:16,481 --> 00:45:18,073
要杯子吗？
Would you like a glass?

873
00:45:27,225 --> 00:45:28,715
别想了
Don't try and decide.

874
00:45:29,527 --> 00:45:30,858
我给你拿
I'll get you one.

875
00:45:36,267 --> 00:45:37,825
我喜欢你的戏
I like your play.

876
00:45:37,936 --> 00:45:40,666
我好想演法官的角色
I only hope I can do the part justice.

877
00:45:41,339 --> 00:45:43,864
我觉得你设计的台词太精彩了 我很喜欢…
I think your dialogue is beautiful. I really do, I love it...

878
00:45:43,975 --> 00:45:46,136
那你为何不站在台上好好演…
Then why the hell don't you just stand still and say it

879
00:45:46,244 --> 00:45:48,337
为何在舞台上梦游？
instead of wandering all over the stage?

880
00:45:48,446 --> 00:45:50,744
你应该寻找你的灵魂 而不是找烟灰缸
You're supposed to be looking for your soul, not an ashtray.

881
00:45:50,815 --> 00:45:52,112
你不希望我在彩排时抽烟吗？
Would you rather I didn't smoke during rehearsals?

882
00:45:52,217 --> 00:45:54,811
我宁愿看到你引火烧身…
I'd rather you went up in flames than put out your cigarette

883
00:45:54,919 --> 00:45:56,807
而不是独角戏演到一半时去抽烟
in the middle of a monologue about birth.

884
00:45:56,955 --> 00:45:57,910
对不起，你批评得对
I'm sorry. You're absolutely right.

885
00:45:58,056 --> 00:45:59,819
你这样做让我想取消整个制作
It makes me wanna cancel the whole production.

886
00:45:59,958 --> 00:46:02,620
我不会再犯错误了，对不起
I won't do it again. Excuse me, I'm sorry.

887
00:46:12,537 --> 00:46:14,926
杯子你留着，我拿酒瓶喝
You keep the glass. I'll take the bottle.

888
00:46:15,440 --> 00:46:16,998
你要走了吗？
Are you leaving?

889
00:46:17,642 --> 00:46:19,098
给我杯子
Give me your glass.

890
00:46:30,488 --> 00:46:31,819
你紧张了？
Are you nervous?

891
00:46:32,824 --> 00:46:36,157
-还是手颤？ -你为何不和杰克去芝加哥？
- Or is that a tremor? - Why aren't you in Chicago with Jack?

892
00:46:36,261 --> 00:46:38,991
为什么要去？ 他有他的事，我有我的事
Why should I be? He has his things, I have mine.

893
00:46:51,175 --> 00:46:53,268
-什么事？ -什么？
- What are they? - What?

894
00:46:56,914 --> 00:47:00,509
你有什么事？
The things that you have that are yours.

895
00:47:00,952 --> 00:47:02,146
到底什么事？
What are they?

896
00:47:04,322 --> 00:47:05,880
我的工作
My work, for one.

897
00:47:06,991 --> 00:47:09,551
他是个工作狂，是不是？
He's a real mean son of a bitch, isn't he?

898
00:47:10,261 --> 00:47:11,592
你什么意思？
What do you mean?

899
00:47:11,696 --> 00:47:13,994
把你留下来做自己的事
Leaving you alone with your work.

900
00:47:14,699 --> 00:47:17,463
-你以为我介意吗？ -你应该介意
- You think I mind? - You should.

901
00:47:18,436 --> 00:47:20,802
有一件事不能留下单独做
It's the one thing we mustn't be left alone with.

902
00:47:20,905 --> 00:47:23,396
-你也许会这样认为，但我不会 -好
- You may feel that way, I don't. - Good.

903
00:47:23,508 --> 00:47:27,467
别让那些乡村激进分子 影响了你的角色
Don't let those village radicals keep you from being what you should be.

904
00:47:28,012 --> 00:47:29,900
什么角色？
What do you think I should be?

905
00:47:30,548 --> 00:47:32,539
众人关注的焦点
The center of attention.

906
00:47:33,618 --> 00:47:36,143
我想你身边一定不少女强人吧
Well, you must have been with some very competitive women.

907
00:47:36,954 --> 00:47:38,683
是占有欲强的女人
Let's just say possessive.

908
00:47:38,890 --> 00:47:41,518
占有欲强？那就另当别论了
Possessive? That's something else.

909
00:47:41,826 --> 00:47:43,282
这是浪费光阴
It's a waste of time.

910
00:47:44,028 --> 00:47:45,222
我不是
I'm not.

911
00:47:46,297 --> 00:47:48,390
杰克也不是
Neither is Jack, for that matter.

912
00:47:48,599 --> 00:47:52,023
我知道，你和杰克各有所爱
Oh, yes. I know. You and Jack have your own things.

913
00:47:52,136 --> 00:47:55,060
他有自由做自己想做的事 我也是一样
He has the freedom to do the things that he wants to and so do I.

914
00:47:55,173 --> 00:47:57,129
如果有谁害怕那种自由…
And I think anyone who's afraid of that kind of freedom

915
00:47:57,241 --> 00:47:59,300
其实他害怕的是空虚
is really only afraid of his own emptiness.

916
00:48:00,912 --> 00:48:02,743
原来你一直在给我下套
Are you making this up as you go along?

917
00:48:04,615 --> 00:48:06,310
请你走吧
I'd like you to go.

918
00:48:08,886 --> 00:48:09,910
为什么？
Why?

919
00:48:10,121 --> 00:48:11,418
因为我不想屈尊就俯
Because I don't want to be patronized.

920
00:48:11,556 --> 00:48:13,547
如果你不相信相互独立性 博爱和尊重…
I'm sorry if you don't believe in mutual independence

921
00:48:13,691 --> 00:48:14,988
那么对不起了
and free love and respect.

922
00:48:15,093 --> 00:48:18,950
别对我鼓吹乡村激进分子的 社会主义理论
Don't give me a lot of parlor socialism that you learned in the Village.

923
00:48:20,164 --> 00:48:24,123
如果你是我的，我不会让别人分享你
If you were mine, I wouldn't share you with anybody or anything.

924
00:48:24,902 --> 00:48:28,463
只有你和我，你会是中心所在
It'd be just you and me. You'd be at the center of it all.

925
00:48:31,110 --> 00:48:33,135
撇下你让你独自工作…
You know, it would feel lot more like love

926
00:48:33,245 --> 00:48:35,543
这不叫爱情
than being left alone with your work.

927
00:48:47,893 --> 00:48:51,420
-希望我没有触怒你 -没有，我感谢都来不及
- I hope I haven't upset you. - Not at all. I'm grateful.

928
00:48:52,030 --> 00:48:54,453
但是好像你要找的东西…
But you seem to be looking for something much more serious

929
00:48:54,566 --> 00:48:56,522
比我所想的要严肃多了
than what I had in mind.

930
00:48:57,136 --> 00:48:59,229
-比你想的严肃多了？ -是的
- Than what you had in mind? - Yes.

931
00:49:00,205 --> 00:49:03,663
杰克和我都能够…
You see, Jack and I are both perfectly capable

932
00:49:03,776 --> 00:49:05,835
坚持自己的信念
of living with our beliefs.

933
00:49:07,279 --> 00:49:10,168
但我认为像你这样浪漫的人 会被他们的信仰摧毁
But I think someone as romantic as you would be destroyed by them.

934
00:49:11,083 --> 00:49:14,905
我可不想看到这种事发生 杰克会很担心的
And I don't want that to happen. It would upset Jack too much.

935
00:49:37,443 --> 00:49:39,832
“你不能来我的院子玩耍”
You can't come and play in my yard

936
00:49:41,046 --> 00:49:43,537
“我再也不爱你了”
I don't love you anymore

937
00:49:44,817 --> 00:49:47,012
“你看到我会难过的”
You'll be sorry when you see me

938
00:49:47,953 --> 00:49:50,342
“关闭我的地窖门”
Sliding down my cellar door

939
00:49:51,590 --> 00:49:54,684
“你不能对着我的雨水桶发牢骚”
You can't holler down my rain barrel

940
00:49:55,127 --> 00:49:58,119
“你不能爬我的苹果树”
You can't climb my apple tree

941
00:50:00,299 --> 00:50:02,790
“我不想在你的院子里玩耍”
I don't want to play in your yard

942
00:50:03,635 --> 00:50:06,263
“因为你对我不好”
If you can't be good to me

943
00:50:40,339 --> 00:50:42,705
“我不想在你的院子里玩耍”
I don't want to play in your yard

944
00:50:43,275 --> 00:50:45,402
“我再也不喜欢你了”
I don't like you anymore

945
00:50:46,044 --> 00:50:48,308
“你看到我会难过的”
You'll be sorry when you see me

946
00:50:48,947 --> 00:50:51,313
“关闭我的地窖门”
Sliding down our cellar door

947
00:50:52,518 --> 00:50:55,112
“你不能对着我的雨水桶发牢骚”
You can't holler down our rain barrel

948
00:50:55,522 --> 00:50:59,034
“你不能爬我的苹果树”
You can't climb our apple tree

949
00:50:59,339 --> 00:51:02,256
“我不想在你的院子里玩耍”
I don't want to play in your yard

950
00:51:02,729 --> 00:51:05,421
“因为你对我不好”
If you won't be good to me

951
00:51:08,752 --> 00:51:10,174
太美妙了！
Wonderful!

952
00:51:27,586 --> 00:51:28,943
弗洛伊德，我期待已久了
Floyd, I've been waiting for this for weeks.

953
00:51:51,843 --> 00:51:53,571
拿出点感觉来
Tap your sensuality.

954
00:52:09,494 --> 00:52:11,519
-美妙的谢幕 -太棒了
- Wonderful close. - Extraordinary.

955
00:52:11,762 --> 00:52:13,524
非常好，太棒了
Very good. Excellent.

956
00:52:15,867 --> 00:52:18,790
-弗洛伊德，你没听过这首歌吧？ -麦斯，你呢？
- Floyd, that's new for you, isn't it? - Max, what about you?

957
00:52:18,904 --> 00:52:19,887
-好了，下一个到谁？ -我刚朗诵完
- Okay. Who's next? - I just recited

958
00:52:20,005 --> 00:52:21,271
我新作的三分之二
two-thirds of my new play.

959
00:52:21,373 --> 00:52:23,601
你们都说它写得很离奇
You said it was a work of uncanny perception.

960
00:52:23,708 --> 00:52:26,332
是吗？我们忘得真快
Oh, did I? How quickly we forget.

961
00:52:43,722 --> 00:52:45,747
-嗨 -杰克，快进来
- Well! - Jack. Come in.

962
00:52:46,358 --> 00:52:47,976
前锋标兵回来了
News from the front.

963
00:52:48,084 --> 00:52:49,102
-你好，杰克 -你好，杰克
- Hello, Jack. - Hello, Jack.

964
00:52:49,245 --> 00:52:50,693
-嗨，杰克 -旅途如何？
- Hi, Jack. - How was the trip?

965
00:52:52,998 --> 00:52:54,430
欢迎回来
Welcome back.

966
00:52:54,866 --> 00:52:56,196
-下一个到谁？ -没人了
- Who's next? - Nobody's next.

967
00:52:57,069 --> 00:52:58,837
让尤金跳舞吧
Let's have a dance out of Gene.

968
00:52:58,943 --> 00:53:01,750
杰克，回来得正好 能看到奥尼尔跳舞
Jack, you're just in time to see O'Neill dance.

969
00:53:02,861 --> 00:53:04,858
给我们跳段爱尔兰舞吧，尤金
Okay. Do something Irish. Come on, Gene.

970
00:53:04,970 --> 00:53:06,567
来一段，尤金
Yeah. Let's have it, Gene.

971
00:53:06,679 --> 00:53:09,010
-跳啊，尤金 -再朗诵你的新作
- Yeah. Go ahead Gene. - Recite something from your new play.

972
00:53:09,114 --> 00:53:10,444
哈奇说新作很棒
Hutch says it's wonderful.

973
00:53:10,549 --> 00:53:13,073
说说大会的情况吧，杰克 威尔逊的演讲怎样？
Tell us about the convention, Jack. How was Wilson's speech?

974
00:53:13,185 --> 00:53:15,977
别提演讲了，说说他的打扮吧
Never mind the speech. What was he wearing?

975
00:53:17,780 --> 00:53:20,901
-威尔逊怎样了？ -对，他怎样？
- What about Wilson? - Yeah. What about Wilson?

976
00:53:22,743 --> 00:53:26,091
我不觉得有何理由相信 他会采取什么措施
Oh, I don't think there's any reason to believe that Wilson's gonna do anything

977
00:53:26,205 --> 00:53:30,018
他只会为维护统治阶级的利益而战
other than support the interest of the ruling class and take us into the war.

978
00:53:30,135 --> 00:53:33,446
但只要他反战，我们就该支持他
But as long as he says he's against it, then I think we have to support him.

979
00:53:33,551 --> 00:53:36,690
至少这几个月内 他不会违背竞选承诺…
Because he'll have to make good on that campaign promise

980
00:53:36,768 --> 00:53:38,800
那样一来我们就有时间…
for at least a few months and that might give us time

981
00:53:38,911 --> 00:53:40,432
巩固反战联盟
to strengthen the anti-war coalition.

982
00:53:40,544 --> 00:53:43,498
但是街上的战前气氛越来越浓了
But there's a lot more pro-war feeling in the streets now than there was before...

983
00:53:59,674 --> 00:54:01,798
还要喝酒吗，尤金？
You want another drink, Gene?

984
00:54:06,505 --> 00:54:07,967
不喝了
I guess not.

985
00:54:23,523 --> 00:54:25,874
-晚安 -晚安
- Good night. - Night.

986
00:54:27,741 --> 00:54:29,203
晚安
Good night.

987
00:54:38,312 --> 00:54:40,490
要不要来杯冰柠檬茶？
Would you like some cold tea with lemon?

988
00:54:40,608 --> 00:54:41,914
不了，谢谢
No, thanks.

989
00:54:43,056 --> 00:54:44,815
不喝我喝
Well, I'll have some, anyway.

990
00:54:57,971 --> 00:55:00,254
-这是什么？ -一首诗
- What's this? - A poem.

991
00:55:01,676 --> 00:55:02,996
可以看看吗？
May I read it?

992
00:55:06,699 --> 00:55:08,359
我还没写完
I didn't finish it.

993
00:55:25,451 --> 00:55:26,747
写完它
Finish it.

994
00:55:33,058 --> 00:55:34,354
写完它？
Finish it?

995
00:55:38,263 --> 00:55:41,754
如果我是个诗人，你会开心吗？
Would that make you happy? If I were a poet?

996
00:55:44,536 --> 00:55:45,839
开心
I'm happy.

997
00:55:56,410 --> 00:55:58,753
-杰克 -快去睡觉吧
- Jack. - Why don't you get some sleep?

998
00:56:00,066 --> 00:56:01,162
杰克
Jack.

999
00:56:03,756 --> 00:56:05,903
有些事我得告诉你
