Not at the moment.

1168
01:08:20,106 --> 01:08:22,495
那你怎么买单？回家吧
Then why the hell should I give you a bill? Go home.

1169
01:08:22,843 --> 01:08:26,370
我坚信社会主义与和平是分不开的
It is my belief that socialism and peace are inseparable.

1170
01:08:26,614 --> 01:08:30,436
我再次重申，社会党坚决反对…
And I reiterate that the Socialist Party will stand firmly behind

1171
01:08:30,551 --> 01:08:33,816
美国参与这场战争！
its resolution to oppose American involvement in this war!

1172
01:08:33,922 --> 01:08:36,288
主席先生，我是波士顿的代表 路易斯・佛拉纳
Mr. Chairman, Louis Fraina, Local Boston.

1173
01:08:36,358 --> 01:08:38,918
主席团承认波士顿的代表
The chair recognizes the delegate from Boston.

1174
01:08:39,029 --> 01:08:40,053
我还是想知道…
And I still want to know

1175
01:08:40,163 --> 01:08:42,961
我们会采取什么具体的行动反战
what specific action we are going to take against the war.

1176
01:08:43,066 --> 01:08:44,590
您的解决方法固然好
Your resolution is all very nice,

1177
01:08:44,702 --> 01:08:47,535
但是它能救命吗？我认为不能
but will it stop even one boy from being killed? I don't think so.

1178
01:08:47,638 --> 01:08:49,902
…被污蔑为不爱国的表现
...stigmatized as unpatriotic.

1179
01:08:50,175 --> 01:08:52,268
摆在我们面前的任务非常艰巨
The task that confronts us is difficult.

1180
01:08:52,377 --> 01:08:54,140
希望我们可以正确对待
Let us hope that we can handle it properly.

1181
01:08:54,246 --> 01:08:55,372
什么意思？
What's that supposed to mean?

1182
01:08:55,480 --> 01:08:56,640
愚蠢！
Stupid!

1183
01:08:57,116 --> 01:09:01,007
我想知道社会党是否会招兵买马
I'd like to know if the Socialist Party is gonna fight conscription or not.

1184
01:09:01,120 --> 01:09:03,975
-我也想知道 -请这位代表自报家门
- That's what I'd like to know. - Will the delegate identify himself?

1185
01:09:04,091 --> 01:09:06,548
我不是代表，主席先生 我叫约翰・雷德
I am not a delegate, Mr. Chairman. My name is John Reed,

1186
01:09:06,694 --> 01:09:08,127
是《大众》杂志的记者
I write for the magazine The Masses,

1187
01:09:08,229 --> 01:09:11,255
我想知道社会党是否会 组织示威游行…
and I want to know if the Socialist Party is gonna organize demonstrations...

1188
01:09:11,332 --> 01:09:13,391
抱歉，雷德先生 您在这里没有发言权
I'm sorry, Mr. Reed. You have no credentials here.

1189
01:09:13,502 --> 01:09:16,562
这里只有代表能发言，记者不能
Now, this floor is reserved for delegates, not journalists.

1190
01:09:16,672 --> 01:09:18,401
主席先生，社会党是否已准备好…
Mr. Chairman, is the Socialist Party prepared

1191
01:09:18,507 --> 01:09:20,168
-上台当政？ -闭嘴！
- to take a position on the draft or not? - Hey, shut up!

1192
01:09:20,277 --> 01:09:22,575
抱歉，雷德先生，您没有发言权
I'm sorry, Mr. Reed. You have no credentials.

1193
01:09:22,679 --> 01:09:23,805
让他说完
Let him speak, will you?

1194
01:09:23,914 --> 01:09:26,337
雷德先生，你想参与政党事务是吗？
Mr. Reed, you're getting into party politics, eh?

1195
01:09:26,451 --> 01:09:28,749
我只是想当好一名记者 主席先生…
I'm just trying to be a journalist. Mr. Chairman...

1196
01:09:28,853 --> 01:09:32,016
托洛茨基也是这样 看看俄国发生的大事吧
So is Trotsky. Let us see what happens in Russia.

1197
01:09:32,157 --> 01:09:35,820
你为何不加入社会党？ 我们需要像你这样的英才
Why don't you join the Socialist Party? We need good people like you.

1198
01:09:35,961 --> 01:09:37,917
俄国发生了翻天覆地的变化
Big things are happening in Russia.

1199
01:09:38,098 --> 01:09:41,522
骇人听闻的是 社会党却支持血雨腥风
As appalling as it may seem to see socialists supporting bloodshed,

1200
01:09:41,634 --> 01:09:44,159
对于战争期间支持政府…
I can understand the necessity of supporting one's government

1201
01:09:44,238 --> 01:09:45,535
我能理解其必要性
during times of war.

1202
01:09:45,639 --> 01:09:48,403
我们所面临的任务异常艰巨！
The task that confronts us is a giant!

1203
01:09:48,844 --> 01:09:51,904
我们必须继续反战！
In that, we must continue our opposition!

1204
01:10:05,830 --> 01:10:09,253
-我们得给狗起个名字 -它有名字
- We have to give this dog a name. - Well, she has a name.

1205
01:10:10,167 --> 01:10:11,997
它的名字怎么了？
What's the matter with her name?

1206
01:10:12,468 --> 01:10:15,664
-家里的东西我都找不到 -我可不想一直叫狗狗
- I can't find anything in this house. - I'm not going to call a dog "Dog."

1207
01:10:15,738 --> 01:10:18,001
要是它是小孩，你总不能叫它“人”吧？
I suppose if she were a baby, you'd wanna call her "Person."

1208
01:10:18,106 --> 01:10:19,970
不是，那就叫它杰克吧
Not really. I think I might wanna call her "Jack."

1209
01:10:20,075 --> 01:10:21,473
不好
No. No. Bad.

1210
01:10:21,576 --> 01:10:23,167
我老是找不到东西
See, now this is why I can't find anything.

1211
01:10:23,279 --> 01:10:24,336
你把东西到处乱放
You put things anywhere.

1212
01:10:24,446 --> 01:10:25,844
狗狗！
Dog! Dog!

1213
01:10:26,047 --> 01:10:27,877
它还没有被驯化
She's still not housebroken.

1214
01:10:27,983 --> 01:10:30,371
要是它趴下，你得把它拉开
You got to grab her when she squats like that,

1215
01:10:30,484 --> 01:10:33,111
把它拉出去，没错
and then take her outside. That's right.

1216
01:10:33,220 --> 01:10:35,983
等它出去之后，你得给它奖品
And then when she goes, you've got to give her a reward.

1217
01:10:36,222 --> 01:10:37,984
好吧，坐好，狗狗
All right. Now, stay, Dog.

1218
01:10:38,124 --> 01:10:40,079
晚餐吃大蒜吗，亲爱的？
Are we having garlic for dinner, honey?

1219
01:10:40,260 --> 01:10:41,214
不…
No, no, no.

1220
01:10:49,100 --> 01:10:52,193
怎么了？我放的大蒜太多了吗？
Why? Why, do you think I'm using too much garlic?

1221
01:10:52,904 --> 01:10:55,292
我觉得沙司里边应该放一点
I thought I'd put a little in the sauce.

1222
01:10:55,405 --> 01:10:57,360
我对大蒜并不反感
Garlic doesn't bother me.

1223
01:11:09,417 --> 01:11:12,943
-那是尤金的信 -对不起，我不是有意的
- That's from Gene. - Sorry. I didn't mean to read it.

1224
01:11:13,887 --> 01:11:15,649
我都没反应过来是什么
I didn't realize what it was.

1225
01:11:22,929 --> 01:11:26,125
他去年10月给的我 之后就没见面了
He gave it to me in October. I haven't seen him since.

1226
01:11:26,231 --> 01:11:27,959
-你不用解释 -我不是解释
- You don't have to explain. - I'm not explaining.

1227
01:11:28,066 --> 01:11:30,454
-我只是想告诉你这已经结束了 -路易丝
- I'm just telling you it's over. - Louise, look.

1228
01:11:30,568 --> 01:11:32,262
我不指望你什么事都告诉我
I don't expect you to tell me everything you do.

1229
01:11:32,369 --> 01:11:34,359
如果要跟我说，就请你说实话
What about if you tell me something, just tell me the truth?

1230
01:11:34,471 --> 01:11:36,267
-杰克，我已经不和他见面了 -别这样，路易丝
- Jack, I haven't seen him. - Don't do that, Louise.

1231
01:11:36,372 --> 01:11:39,295
别跟我说尤金六七个月前给了你 一封情书之后…
Don't tell me that Gene gave you a love poem six or seven months ago,

1232
01:11:39,409 --> 01:11:41,399
你就一直没有和他见面
but you put it in a book and you haven't seen him since.

1233
01:11:41,510 --> 01:11:43,033
我不在乎你见没见他
I don't care whether you've seen him or not.

1234
01:11:43,145 --> 01:11:44,634
-我在乎的是不坦诚 -我明白了
- I just care about dishonesty. - Oh, I see.

1235
01:11:44,746 --> 01:11:46,667
你不在乎我和别的男人有私情
You don't care that I had an affair with another man,

1236
01:11:46,782 --> 01:11:49,170
你只在乎不坦诚？现在是谁不坦诚
you just care about dishonesty? Look who's being dishonest.

1237
01:11:49,283 --> 01:11:50,943
你在乎，太在乎了 甚至都不屑一顾
You care. You care so much, you won't even talk about it.

1238
01:11:51,052 --> 01:11:52,780
-你甚至都不提… -想理论吗？我来跟你理论
- You won't even mention... - Wanna talk? I'll talk about it.

1239
01:11:52,887 --> 01:11:53,944
你想开诚布公吗？
You want to be honest about it?

1240
01:11:54,054 --> 01:11:55,247
要是我不想坦诚的话…
If I didn't wanna be honest about it,

1241
01:11:55,322 --> 01:11:57,050
我会愚蠢到把他给我的情书…
do you think I'd be silly enough to leave a poem he gave me

1242
01:11:57,157 --> 01:11:59,147
藏在沃尔特・惠特曼的书里吗？
lying around in the house in a book of Walt Whitman?

1243
01:11:59,258 --> 01:12:00,315
为什么不行呢？
Why not Whitman?

1244
01:12:00,426 --> 01:12:03,155
相信尤金一定会心安理得的
I'm sure Gene would feel right at home in that company.

1245
01:12:03,262 --> 01:12:04,387
不，你一点都不在乎
Oh, no. You don't care.

1246
01:12:04,496 --> 01:12:06,793
我为什么要在乎你和谁上床？
Why the hell should I care that you slept with somebody else?

1247
01:12:06,898 --> 01:12:07,921
你以为我不在乎？
Do you think I haven't?

1248
01:12:08,032 --> 01:12:09,623
我不赞成每次和别人上床…
I don't think we have to report to each other

1249
01:12:09,734 --> 01:12:12,531
我们都要互相通报，那毫无意义
every time we go to bed with somebody. It doesn't mean anything.

1250
01:12:12,636 --> 01:12:13,932
那不意味着我对你的爱就少一点
It doesn't mean that I love you any less.

1251
01:12:14,037 --> 01:12:16,368
和尤金上床会让你对我的爱少一点吗？
Do you love me any less 'cause you went to bed with Gene?

1252
01:12:20,776 --> 01:12:22,367
这有什么区别？
What difference does it make?

1253
01:12:22,511 --> 01:12:25,070
我不赞成撒谎，仅此而已
I just don't think we should lie about it. That's all.

1254
01:12:25,747 --> 01:12:28,135
-谁？ -什么谁？
- Who? - What do you mean, "Who?"

1255
01:12:28,650 --> 01:12:30,014
-是谁？ -什么是谁？
- Who was it? - Who was what?

1256
01:12:31,352 --> 01:12:32,716
那个人是谁？
Who was it?

1257
01:12:33,287 --> 01:12:35,345
你想要名单吗？这毫无意义
What do you want, a list? It doesn't mean anything.

1258
01:12:46,431 --> 01:12:47,590
路易丝
Louise.

1259
01:12:49,700 --> 01:12:50,859
路易丝
Louise.

1260
01:12:57,340 --> 01:12:59,295
-你干什么？ -不知道
- What are you doing? - I'm not sure.

1261
01:12:59,808 --> 01:13:01,866
-我想知道你要去哪 -不想说
- I wanna know where you're going. - I don't want to talk about it.

1262
01:13:01,977 --> 01:13:04,342
-那我想说 -那你就说个够吧
- Well, I wanna talk about it. - You said it all, Jack.

1263
01:13:04,413 --> 01:13:07,267
什么？难道我们还没说上百次吗？
What? What did I say now that we both haven't said 100 times?

1264
01:13:07,415 --> 01:13:08,847
请把我的来信转到约翰・惠勒…
Please forward my mail to John K. Wheeler,

1265
01:13:08,950 --> 01:13:10,007
惠勒贝尔集团那里
Wheeler Bell Syndicate.

1266
01:13:10,118 --> 01:13:12,506
早上我会叫人来搬我剩下的东西
I'll have someone pick up the rest of my things in the morning.

1267
01:13:12,619 --> 01:13:14,609
难道两个人一起生活…
Didn't we say that people had to give each other freedom

1268
01:13:14,721 --> 01:13:16,813
-不是彼此都有自由吗？ -我们说的东西多了
- if they were gonna live together? - We said a lot of things.

1269
01:13:16,923 --> 01:13:18,446
我还以为我们没有那么霸道
I thought we weren't going to be possessive.

1270
01:13:18,557 --> 01:13:20,319
-我还以为你爱我！ -谁说我不爱你了？
- I thought you loved me! - Who says I don't?

1271
01:13:20,426 --> 01:13:22,381
你只爱你自己！根本不爱我！
You love yourself! Me, you fuck!

1272
01:13:23,161 --> 01:13:25,355
你只有不出轨时才会爱我
When you're not fucking other people, that is!

1273
01:13:25,497 --> 01:13:29,284
自由？你的意思是 要我和你一样毫不在乎尤金
Freedom? You mean I should just be like you and not give a damn, is that...

1274
01:13:30,768 --> 01:13:33,463
你和尤金上床有没想过我们？
Is that what fucking Gene means? You don't give a damn about us?

1275
01:13:33,570 --> 01:13:36,766
我不会收拾行李的，我想知道你去哪
I'm not packing my bag. I wanna know where you're going.

1276
01:13:36,839 --> 01:13:38,726
-走开… -你上哪？
- Get out of my... - Where you going?

1277
01:13:38,841 --> 01:13:40,728
-走开… -你不能…
- Get out of my... - You're not going...

1278
01:13:42,978 --> 01:13:45,901
走开！滚开！
Get away! Get out of my way.

1279
01:14:09,901 --> 01:14:12,528
-到底有多少个？ -得了吧，路易丝
- How many were there? - Come on, Louise.

1280
01:14:14,538 --> 01:14:18,234
你根本就不知道如何一起生活
You don't know the first thing about what living together means.

1281
01:14:25,780 --> 01:14:27,212
走吧，我知道你去哪
Go ahead. I know where you're going.

1282
01:14:27,315 --> 01:14:30,203
原以为你需要人一起生活 但是我错了
I thought you needed someone to share your life with. But I was wrong.

1283
01:14:30,317 --> 01:14:31,977
你只想每天成为人们关注的焦点
As long as you get your two shots of limelight every day.

1284
01:14:32,119 --> 01:14:33,608
你什么都不缺
You don't need a thing.

1285
01:14:40,959 --> 01:14:43,222
下地狱吧！你们俩都下地狱去吧！
You go to hell! Both of you!

1286
01:15:10,217 --> 01:15:14,710
当时和路易丝・拜伦有私情…
It could possibly have been a matter of prestige, you know,

1287
01:15:15,288 --> 01:15:18,142
是一件相当有面子的事
to say that you had an affair with Louise Bryant.

1288
01:15:18,891 --> 01:15:20,687
我一直都不奢望…
I haven't been spared

1289
01:15:20,826 --> 01:15:25,091
有哪个男人和我有私情
the legends about men that are supposed to have had affairs with me,

1290
01:15:25,530 --> 01:15:27,622
因为我名如其人啊
because I was known by name.

1291
01:15:29,033 --> 01:15:31,523
根本就不可能有什么私情
Affairs which never occurred at all.

1292
01:15:31,935 --> 01:15:34,596
这很难说得清楚
It's very difficult to tell, you know.

1293
01:15:34,704 --> 01:15:37,592
最让人头疼的是…
Do you know there is nothing more bewildering

1294
01:15:37,740 --> 01:15:40,572
你收到一个疯子的情书，上面写着…
than when you get a letter from a loony who says,

1295
01:15:40,675 --> 01:15:43,006
“我们在威尼斯渡过了美妙的一周”
"That marvelous week we spent in Venice."

1296
01:15:43,111 --> 01:15:46,671
-对 -每两年都会发生这种事
- Yeah. - And it happens about every two years.

1297
01:15:46,781 --> 01:15:48,668
-是的 -非常特别
- Yes. - It's most extraordinary.

1298
01:15:52,185 --> 01:15:56,814
一天，我和我的姨妈在波特兰散步
One day, I was out walking with my aunt in Portland.

1299
01:15:57,656 --> 01:16:00,783
她很漂亮，身材很高挑
And she was quite something. She was six feet tall.

1300
01:16:01,427 --> 01:16:03,986
我问她…
And I said to her,

1301
01:16:04,195 --> 01:16:07,618
“路易丝的传闻是怎么回事？”
"What is all this ado about Louise?

1302
01:16:07,932 --> 01:16:09,887
“你觉得她怎样，贝丽姨妈？”
"What do you think of her, Aunt Belle?"

1303
01:16:10,500 --> 01:16:11,557
她说…
She said,

1304
01:16:11,701 --> 01:16:15,056
[1917年，巴黎] “她这人很有吸引力”
"Well, she had something that just appeals."

1305
01:16:18,674 --> 01:16:20,197
那就是我的故事
That's my story.

1306
01:16:20,776 --> 01:16:22,731
-感觉怎样？ -好多了
- How you feeling? - Oh, better.

1307
01:16:22,811 --> 01:16:24,539
-给你 -谢谢，哈瑞
- Here you are. - Oh. Thanks, Harry.

1308
01:16:25,080 --> 01:16:26,273
谢谢
Thanks.

1309
01:16:26,681 --> 01:16:28,568
幸好摘除得及时
Well, we got it out just in time.

1310
01:16:28,749 --> 01:16:31,876
但不知道另外一个肾的情况怎样了
But since God only knows what condition the one you've got left is in,

1311
01:16:31,985 --> 01:16:33,042
你最好善待它
you better treat it well.

1312
01:16:33,419 --> 01:16:36,376
你得告诉伊斯曼你午夜前必须休息
That means, tell that goddamn Eastman you got to be in bed by midnight.

1313
01:16:36,489 --> 01:16:39,787
要是被感染的话，到时就真的没救了！
If you get an infection now, that's it! Absolutely no salt!

1314
01:16:39,891 --> 01:16:41,915
“亲爱的杰克 知道你好点了我深感欣慰”
"Dear Jack, I'm relieved you're feeling so well again.

1315
01:16:42,027 --> 01:16:43,584
“我问过巴黎的专家了”
"I talked to a specialist here in Paris.

1316
01:16:43,695 --> 01:16:46,026
“他说你可以过正常人的生活”
"And he said you can lead a perfectly normal life.

1317
01:16:46,163 --> 01:16:47,720
“希望你不要停止写作”
"I hope you're not neglecting your writing.

1318
01:16:47,865 --> 01:16:48,819
“请不要浪费精力…”
"Please don't spend your energy

1319
01:16:48,966 --> 01:16:50,489
“去捕风捉影”
"getting caught up in things you can't afford."

1320
01:16:50,634 --> 01:16:52,089
“亲爱的杰克，随附上我的作品”
"Dear Jack, I'm enclosing a piece I've written

1321
01:16:52,235 --> 01:16:53,360
“是描述一个志愿救护车司机的”
"on a volunteer ambulance driver

1322
01:16:53,470 --> 01:16:54,925
“他来自纽约警局”
"from the New York City Police Department.

1323
01:16:55,038 --> 01:16:57,665
“还有，请不要再问我是否可以过来找我”
"Also, please don't keep asking me if you can come over here.

1324
01:16:57,739 --> 01:16:59,103
“那样会让我认为你没有…”
"It just makes me think you have no..."

1325
01:16:59,208 --> 01:17:01,266
“亲爱的杰克，惠勒对我的作品很满意”
"Dear Jack, yes, Wheeler's very happy with my work.

1326
01:17:01,376 --> 01:17:04,105
“这里的生活如火如荼，我没有时间…”
"Life here is so hectic and exhilarating that I don't have a minute..."

1327
01:17:04,212 --> 01:17:05,872
“亲爱的杰克，请不要担心，我很好”
"Dear Jack, don't worry, I'm well.

1328
01:17:05,980 --> 01:17:09,210
“只是要不停满足惠勒的创作要求”
"My only problem is keeping up with Wheeler's demands for more stories."

1329
01:17:09,316 --> 01:17:11,647
“写一系列的头条时事通讯《法国来信》”
"...serial newsletter under the heading, 'Letters from France.'

1330
01:17:11,751 --> 01:17:12,978
“请不要向任何人提起”
"Please don't mention this to anyone.

1331
01:17:13,086 --> 01:17:14,518
“我答应过惠勒，我不会告诉你任何事”
"I promised Wheeler I wouldn't say anything to you."

1332
01:17:14,787 --> 01:17:17,346
“亲爱的杰克，我想我的作品 通过了惠勒的审核”
"Dear Jack, I feel I've really grown through my work for Wheeler,

1333
01:17:17,490 --> 01:17:19,411
“所以没有理由为我本人担忧”
"and there's no reason to worry about my being here alone."

1334
01:17:19,525 --> 01:17:21,651
布尔什维克，桑迪，布尔什维克人！
Bolsheviks, Sandy. The Bolsheviks!

1335
01:17:21,893 --> 01:17:23,917
天哪，要是布尔什维克介入，桑迪
Jesus Christ, if the Bolsheviks get in, Sandy,

1336
01:17:24,062 --> 01:17:26,859
你大可亲吻自己的屁股拜拜了
you can just bend right over and kiss your ass goodbye.

1337
01:17:26,964 --> 01:17:28,988
因为他们会让俄国退出战争
Because they'll pull Russia right out of the war.

1338
01:17:29,099 --> 01:17:31,362
撤出东线战场，他们会退出
Right off the Eastern Front. They quit, that's all.

1339
01:17:31,435 --> 01:17:33,231
彼得，布尔什维克不成气候的
Pete, the Bolsheviks are small potatoes.

1340
01:17:33,336 --> 01:17:35,166
俄国不会袖手旁观的
Russia isn't gonna get out of the war.

1341
01:17:35,271 --> 01:17:37,659
你想看到香谢丽舍大道上的 凯旋门那里…
You want to walk down the Champs-Elys闲s someday

1342
01:17:37,773 --> 01:17:40,900
出现五十万德国大军吗？
and see 500,000 Krauts come barreling out of Fouquet's?

1343
01:17:41,009 --> 01:17:43,932
你最好希望布尔什维克成气候吧
You better hope that the Bolsheviks are small potatoes.

1344
01:17:44,045 --> 01:17:46,774
再来一杯，侍应！
Now, let's have another drink. Waiter!

1345
01:17:47,181 --> 01:17:49,171
侍应，每人再来一杯酒
Waiter, another round here.

1346
01:17:49,283 --> 01:17:51,409
天哪，是小爱玛！
Hey! Oh, God. It's Red Emma, Jr!

1347
01:17:51,551 --> 01:17:53,142
快过来
Hey, come over here!

1348
01:17:53,286 --> 01:17:55,742
说大声点，彼得 隔壁的人听不到
Speak up, Pete, speak up. They can't hear you in the next room.

1349
01:17:56,189 --> 01:17:57,485
-你好啊，杰克 -见到你很高兴
- How are you, Jack? - Good to see you.

1350
01:17:57,656 --> 01:18:00,351
老天，摘除肾脏后你瘦了起码二十磅
God. You look 20 pounds lighter since you lost that kidney.

1351
01:18:00,459 --> 01:18:02,517
-是吗？ -我打赌你只摘除了一个吧
- Oh, yeah? - I bet you only piss about half as much.

1352
01:18:02,593 --> 01:18:04,719
是的，通常都是两个的 来杯汽水
Yeah, but twice as often. Sarsaparilla.

1353
01:18:04,896 --> 01:18:07,352
杰克，布尔什维克能打倒克伦斯基吗？ (俄国社会革命领袖)
Jack, can the Bolsheviks overthrow Kerensky?

1354
01:18:07,465 --> 01:18:10,160
你还是去找个公正的观察员问问吧
Okay. Why don't you ask an impartial observer?

1355
01:18:10,700 --> 01:18:14,226
杰克，你到底为什么反对战争呢？
Goddamn it, Jack. What the hell you got against this war anyway?

1356
01:18:14,336 --> 01:18:17,566
该死，你为何不把威尔逊 连同斧头一起埋了呢？
Shit, why don't you bury the hatchet with Wilson?

1357
01:18:17,673 --> 01:18:21,335
重新回到报社吧，我们想看你的大作
Get back into print so we can all read some decent writing, you know.

1358
01:18:21,509 --> 01:18:24,568
-为大作干杯 -你为什么都能干杯
- I'll drink to that. - You'll drink to anything.

1359
01:18:24,712 --> 01:18:28,135
没错，见到你很高兴
Well, that's right, too. It's good to see you.

1360
01:18:28,248 --> 01:18:31,671
真是太高兴了，路易丝怎样？
Jesus Christ. It's good to see you. Goddamn, how's Louise?

1361
01:18:32,051 --> 01:18:33,574
不大好吧？
Not so good.

1362
01:18:33,786 --> 01:18:35,616
-她很好 -把我的话转告她…
- She's good. - Tell her from me that I said

1363
01:18:35,688 --> 01:18:39,179
约翰・惠勒根本就不会欣赏她的作品
that John Wheeler wouldn't know a story if it fell right on top of him.

1364
01:18:39,324 --> 01:18:41,621
杰克，你到底在干嘛？
I'll tell you. Hey, Jack, what are you doing?

1365
01:18:41,726 --> 01:18:43,852
到底在干嘛？你让他们抓狂
What the hell are you doing? You're driving them crazy.

1366
01:18:43,961 --> 01:18:45,257
你意识到了吗？
You realize that?

1367
01:18:45,396 --> 01:18:47,488
他们还以为你是德国佬呢！
They think you're some kind of goddamn German!

1368
01:18:47,898 --> 01:18:50,092
我喜欢！喜欢死了！
I love it! Goddamn, I love it!

1369
01:18:50,200 --> 01:18:51,757
对他们口诛笔伐，杰克
Give them hell, Jack. Give them hell.

1370
01:18:51,868 --> 01:18:54,028
-是要加冰的汽水吗？ -是的，谢谢
- Is that a sarsaparilla with ice? - Yeah, thanks.

1371
01:18:54,270 --> 01:18:56,999
没错，就是加冰的汽水
You bet your sweet patoosie, that's sarsaparilla with ice.

1372
01:18:57,105 --> 01:19:00,164
约翰・惠勒为什么不会欣赏？
Why wouldn't John Wheeler know a story if it fell on him?

1373
01:19:00,309 --> 01:19:02,765
因为约翰・惠勒是个傻子
John Wheeler's a dumbbell, that's why.

1374
01:19:03,110 --> 01:19:04,167
他人是很厉害
No, he's all right.

1375
01:19:04,312 --> 01:19:06,734
我只是不想看到路易丝受伤而已
I just hate to see Louise get hurt. That's all.

1376
01:19:08,148 --> 01:19:09,239
这话什么意思？
What are you talking about?

1377
01:19:12,152 --> 01:19:13,584
老天
Jesus Christ.

1378
01:19:14,853 --> 01:19:16,649
别告诉她是我说的，好吗？
Don't tell her that I told you. All right?

1379
01:19:17,923 --> 01:19:19,378
告诉我什么？
Told me what?

1380
01:19:20,124 --> 01:19:22,978
本・帕森斯告诉我 惠勒不得不让她走人
Well, Ben Parsons told me that Wheeler had to let her go

1381
01:19:23,094 --> 01:19:26,881
因为她的作品惠勒根本不用
because she hadn't turned anything in that he could use,

1382
01:19:27,030 --> 01:19:28,621
除了那个关于…
other than some story about a cop

1383
01:19:28,732 --> 01:19:32,428
警察志愿者司机的作品之外
that went over there to drive a police department ambulance.

1384
01:19:33,336 --> 01:19:35,860
-他让她走人？ -炒了她
- He let her go? - Fired her.

1385
01:19:40,008 --> 01:19:42,464
-你何时听说的？ -几个星期前
- When did you hear that? - A couple of weeks ago.

1386
01:19:43,011 --> 01:19:45,672
不是，一个月前 一个半月前
No, it was a month. More than a month and a half ago.

1387
01:19:46,413 --> 01:19:49,210
杰克，惠勒就是个混蛋
Oh, look, Jack, Wheeler's a goddamn moron.

1388
01:19:49,316 --> 01:19:51,476
叫她不必为解雇的事感到惭愧
Tell her she shouldn't feel ashamed about being fired.

1389
01:19:51,584 --> 01:19:53,642
-回头见 -怎么了，杰克？
- I'm gonna see you later, huh? - Jack, what's the matter?

1390
01:19:53,753 --> 01:19:56,346
我也被解雇了，大家都被解雇了
Hell, we've all been fired. I've been fired.

1391
01:19:56,455 --> 01:19:57,409
为解雇干杯
Hell, I'll drink to it.

1392
01:19:57,990 --> 01:20:00,412
想象一下，6千5百万大军…
Imagine, 65 million

1393
01:20:01,326 --> 01:20:03,089
去打仗
go to war. Right?

1394
01:20:03,395 --> 01:20:05,488
一千万人阵亡
10 million die.

1395
01:20:05,931 --> 01:20:07,887
一千万人成为孤儿
10 million become orphans.

1396
01:20:08,200 --> 01:20:12,466
2千万人伤残
20 million become maimed, crippled, or wounded.

1397
01:20:13,372 --> 01:20:16,500
欧洲大灾难肆虐
You had catastrophe in Europe.

1398
01:20:16,908 --> 01:20:19,502
欧洲大屠杀肆虐
You had a holocaust in Europe.

1399
01:20:20,145 --> 01:20:22,272
你有转变的雄心壮志
You had a desire for change.

1400
01:20:23,015 --> 01:20:24,141
在当时革命情绪…
Who can stop them

1401
01:20:24,249 --> 01:20:27,605
异常高涨的时候，谁能阻止战争？
when there was such a revolutionary sentiment? Huh?

1402
01:20:27,819 --> 01:20:29,013
谁来阻止？
Who could stop them?

1403
01:20:39,798 --> 01:20:42,460
看来我要买一台新的打字机了…
You know, I think I'm gonna have to get a new typewriter...

1404
01:20:45,570 --> 01:20:47,435
-你怎么… -怎么了？
- What are you... - What?

1405
01:20:50,609 --> 01:20:52,440
你气色不错，完全康复了吗？
You look fine. Are you all right now?

1406
01:20:52,544 --> 01:20:55,604
人不需要两个肾的
Oh, God, yes. Nobody needs two kidneys.

1407
01:20:56,081 --> 01:20:58,276
第二个只是摆设
The second one's just for show.

1408
01:20:59,885 --> 01:21:01,944
对不起，你来得不大是时候
Sorry, this isn't a very good time.

1409
01:21:06,591 --> 01:21:09,389
他们要把我转移到 另一个通讯中心
They're moving me to another communications center.

1410
01:21:09,761 --> 01:21:12,855
现在我没时间和你叙旧了
So, I'm just not going to be able to talk to you right now, Jack.

1411
01:21:12,998 --> 01:21:15,387
能出去谈一会儿吗？就一会儿
Could we just go out here a second? Just for a second?

1412
01:21:15,867 --> 01:21:19,064
-我要去俄国了 -是嘛？你应征了吗？
- Look, I'm on my way to Russia. - Oh, really? Have you enlisted?

1413
01:21:19,171 --> 01:21:20,195
开玩笑
Very funny.

1414
01:21:20,339 --> 01:21:21,795
我知道你在这里干得很出色
I know you're doing work here that's good,

1415
01:21:21,907 --> 01:21:24,205
我也看了你的救护车作品，写得很棒
'cause I read the ambulance piece and I thought that was good.

1416
01:21:24,276 --> 01:21:25,641
-谢谢 -我知道你在写书
- Thank you. - And I know you're working on your book

1417
01:21:25,744 --> 01:21:27,109
我知道它对你很重要
and I know how important that is to you.

1418
01:21:27,212 --> 01:21:28,406
要是你想在适当时候…
But you got to have enough sense

1419
01:21:28,513 --> 01:21:30,378
在适当地点成为一名优秀记者…
if you're trying to build up your reputation as a journalist,

1420
01:21:30,482 --> 01:21:32,006
你就得增强你的使命感
to be in the right place at the right time.

1421
01:21:32,117 --> 01:21:34,574
-谢谢你的建议 -这个适当的地点就是俄国
- I appreciate your advice. - Well, the place to be now is Russia.

1422
01:21:34,686 --> 01:21:37,746
-谢谢，我会记住的 -现在是乱世，他们坚持不了多久
- Thank you. I'll remember that. - Louise, it's chaos. They can't last.

1423
01:21:37,856 --> 01:21:40,120
6个月内已经上台三个临时政府了
They're in their third provisional government in six months.

1424
01:21:40,225 --> 01:21:43,058
知道意味着什么吗？ 意味着另一场革命即将爆发
You know what that means? It means there might be another revolution.

1425
01:21:43,161 --> 01:21:46,619
工人阶级放弃工厂，士兵放弃前线
The workers are deserting the factories, the army's deserting the battlefronts.

1426
01:21:46,732 --> 01:21:50,395
流放的人都回来了 犹太人，无政府主义者，社会党
The exiles are all coming back. The Jews, the anarchists, the socialists.

1427
01:21:50,535 --> 01:21:52,264
所有的人都回来了
All of them are going back, only this time

1428
01:21:52,437 --> 01:21:53,529
这次才可能会成大气候
it might be the real thing.

1429
01:21:53,638 --> 01:21:55,799
如果俄国爆发真正的工人革命
And if they have a real workers' revolution in Russia,

1430
01:21:55,874 --> 01:21:58,172
德国就会相继爆发，一旦德国爆发…
they'd have one in Germany, and if they had one in Germany,

1431
01:21:58,276 --> 01:22:00,733
-全世界都会爆发 -有火柴吗？
- it could happen all over the world. - Got a match?

1432
01:22:00,846 --> 01:22:02,734
路易丝，然后就是战争结束
Louise, that'd be the end of the war.

1433
01:22:02,848 --> 01:22:04,543
你不必跟我说俄国发生的事
You don't have to tell me what's happening in Russia.

1434
01:22:04,649 --> 01:22:06,344
-我看过报纸了 -跟我走吧
- I read the papers. - Well, come with me.

1435
01:22:06,451 --> 01:22:08,442
作我的同志，不是别的身份
As a colleague, I'm not talking about anything else.

1436
01:22:08,587 --> 01:22:10,817
我们一起前往彼得格勒
Come with me as a colleague. You ought to be in Petrograd.

1437
01:22:10,922 --> 01:22:12,878
是吗？你在纽约也是这么说的！
Oh, yeah? Well, that's what you said about New York!

1438
01:22:12,991 --> 01:22:14,879
-我那时是对的 -不，这里有我的事业
- I was right about New York. - No, I have work I'm doing here.

1439
01:22:14,993 --> 01:22:16,017
我的事业也是…
And I happen to think my work is...

1440
01:22:16,128 --> 01:22:18,790
是很重要，但没有俄国的事业重要
It is important. But it's not important as what you could be doing in Russia.

1441
01:22:18,930 --> 01:22:20,921
我想跟你作搭档，一起奋斗
I wanna work together. As partners.

1442
01:22:21,066 --> 01:22:23,728
我不要搭档，我想去俄国就一个人去
I don't want a partner. And if I wanted to go to Russia, I'd go alone.

1443
01:22:23,869 --> 01:22:25,666
-我不会让你带我去 -路易丝
- I wouldn't need you to take me. - Louise.

1444
01:22:25,771 --> 01:22:28,695
你一个柔弱女子 不适宜单独前往俄国这种乱世
Russia is not the safest place in the world for a woman to be alone.

1445
01:22:28,774 --> 01:22:31,663
你能成为一名出色记者 但那并不意味着…
You may be a hell of a journalist. But that doesn't mean...

1446
01:22:35,847 --> 01:22:38,042
路易丝，我们要走了
Louise, we'd better hurry along.

1447
01:22:40,552 --> 01:22:42,315
要转移了？
So, moving you out of here, huh?

1448
01:22:42,421 --> 01:22:44,844
是的，我要去采访普拉默将军
Yes. I've been promised an interview with General Plumer.

1449
01:22:44,956 --> 01:22:47,151
我也得走了
Well, I've got to run along myself.

1450
01:22:48,326 --> 01:22:51,124
-对不起，我时间匆忙 -不，我不想留下你
- Sorry I don't have any time. - No. I don't want to keep you.

1451
01:22:51,263 --> 01:22:53,424
只是想…座位已经预约了
I just... Look, the seat's already reserved.

1452
01:22:53,632 --> 01:22:55,793
你这是浪费钱财，杰克，我不要
You've wasted your money, Jack. I don't want it.

1453
01:22:55,934 --> 01:22:59,358
你可以改日期自己去 什么时候去都行
Change the date. Go by yourself. You can use it whenever you want to.

1454
01:22:59,905 --> 01:23:01,395
坚持自己的创作
Keep up the good work.

1455
01:23:03,175 --> 01:23:04,335
杰克
Jack.

1456
01:23:06,178 --> 01:23:07,475
祝好运
Good luck.

1457
01:23:07,579 --> 01:23:08,671
你也是
Yeah, you, too.

1458
01:23:14,820 --> 01:23:16,685
出租车在等我
I got a taxi waiting.

1459
01:23:42,914 --> 01:23:44,609
杰克！杰克・雷德！
Jack! Jack Reed!

1460
01:23:45,317 --> 01:23:47,239
-我是乔・沃斯基 -你好吗？
- Joe, Joe Volski. - How are you?

1461
01:23:47,352 --> 01:23:50,446
很好，你也去彼得格勒？
Oh, fine, fine. Are you going to Petrograd, too?

1462
01:23:50,755 --> 01:23:53,178
-是的 -太好了！
- Yes. Yeah. - Fine. Wonderful!

1463
01:23:53,291 --> 01:23:56,920
形势真是风云变幻，你一个人吗？
Great things are happening. Are you traveling by yourself?

1464
01:23:58,697 --> 01:24:01,586
-应该是吧 -那我搬过去坐
- I think I am. - Well, then I'll switch.

1465
01:24:22,087 --> 01:24:23,714
我们在芝加哥见面过
We met in Chicago.

1466
01:24:25,190 --> 01:24:27,852
你真是个大演讲家！
Boy, oh, boy. Were you a speaker!

1467
01:24:29,261 --> 01:24:31,252
不记得我了吗？
You don't remember me, eh?

1468
01:24:32,931 --> 01:24:34,694
不是的
Well, it's not that.

1469
01:24:36,234 --> 01:24:38,759
-可能是因为帽子 -我的帽子？
- Maybe I just... Maybe it's the hat. - My hat?

1470
01:24:38,904 --> 01:24:41,634
对，你戴上这顶别致的帽子 我认不出了
Yeah. Maybe I just don't recognize you in this particular hat.

1471
01:24:41,740 --> 01:24:45,335
我现在是化妆成老百姓的革命者
Oh, then I'm a revolutionary returning in disguise.

1472
01:24:45,410 --> 01:24:48,675
等到革命胜利，我给你买顶新帽子
Well, comes the revolution, I'll buy you a new hat.

1473
01:24:48,780 --> 01:24:51,772
-你好像在学俄语 -是的，正在努力学
- I see you're studying Russian. - Yeah. I'm trying to.

1474
01:24:51,883 --> 01:24:53,111
知道吗？
Know what?

1475
01:24:55,720 --> 01:24:56,812
-什么？ -我是说…
- What? - I mean,

1476
01:24:56,922 --> 01:24:59,254
你可以问我这个俄国通
ask me anything you want in Russian.

1477
01:24:59,357 --> 01:25:01,518
谢谢，我会记住的
Thank you. I'll keep that in mind.

1478
01:25:02,360 --> 01:25:03,725
我看看…
Let's see...

1479
01:25:03,962 --> 01:25:06,487
抱歉，打搅了，我有话要说
Excuse me. Excuse me, now here's the thing.

1480
01:25:06,631 --> 01:25:09,964
我不接受你提议的话就太愚蠢了 但我有条件
I'd be a goddamned fool not to take you up on this offer. So, here's what I want.

1481
01:25:10,068 --> 01:25:11,763
我要在我自己的报道上签我的名字
I want to sign my own name to my own stories

1482
01:25:11,870 --> 01:25:13,394
我不要联名
and I don't want to use a double byline.

1483
01:25:13,538 --> 01:25:16,393
我要自行安排自己的时间和活动
I want to be responsible for my own time and my own actions.

1484
01:25:16,474 --> 01:25:18,897
我要别人称呼我拜伦小姐 而非雷德夫人
I want to be referred to as Miss Bryant, and not as Mrs. Reed,

1485
01:25:19,010 --> 01:25:20,966
我要记下我们所有的花费…
and I want to keep an account of every cent we spend

1486
01:25:21,079 --> 01:25:22,205
以便我还给你
so that I can pay you back.

1487
01:25:22,314 --> 01:25:24,544
还有，我不会再跟你上床
Now, I assume you know that I'm not going to sleep with you,

1488
01:25:24,649 --> 01:25:27,345
所以，你不要对我有非分之想
so just don't confuse the issue by bringing it up.

1489
01:25:27,452 --> 01:25:28,544
完了
That's it.

1490
01:25:29,688 --> 01:25:31,087
-好 -好
- Fine. - Good.

1491
01:25:31,423 --> 01:25:32,685
喜欢意大利香肠吗？
You like salami?

1492
01:25:36,628 --> 01:25:38,858
有个人说“等一下，我得回去”
He says, "Wait a minute, I have to go back.

1493
01:25:38,997 --> 01:25:40,988
“我把假牙落在桌子上了”
"I forgot my teeth on the table."

1494
01:25:41,299 --> 01:25:43,130
另一个人说“别管你的假牙了”
He says, "Hell with your teeth!

1495
01:25:43,234 --> 01:25:46,192
“你以为天上会掉馅饼下来给你咬吗？”
"What do you think, they're bombarding with sandwiches?"

1496
01:25:59,551 --> 01:26:02,145
革命胜利后我给你买新帽子
After the revolution, you'll buy me a new hat.

1497
01:26:02,253 --> 01:26:04,847
非常感谢，我会记住的
Thank you very much. I'll keep you by your word.

1498
01:26:05,824 --> 01:26:08,554
对了，你听过这个笑话没？一个人…
By the way, did you hear this one? A man...

1499
01:26:26,811 --> 01:26:29,609
列宁问我“为什么留胡子？”
Lenin asks, "Why do you let your beard grow?"

1500
01:26:29,714 --> 01:26:32,877
我回答到“我想记得昨天吃了什么”
I says, "I want to remember what I ate yesterday."

1501
01:26:40,725 --> 01:26:44,058
这个比较难念，意思是“我不抽烟”
This is a hard word, but it means "I don't smoke."

1502
01:26:44,162 --> 01:26:45,220
好
Okay.

1503
01:26:47,932 --> 01:26:51,129
“你是家属吗？” 他说“不是，所以我才哭”
"Are you one of the family?" He said, "No. That's why I'm crying."

1504
01:26:57,742 --> 01:27:00,575
伐木营的工头想招工
There's a foreman of a logging camp, he's trying to hire a crew.

1505
01:27:00,679 --> 01:27:02,874
许多人在排队，都是牛高马大的汉子
You know, and he goes down a long line of very big men

1506
01:27:02,981 --> 01:27:04,073
他抓住了一个小个子
and he gets to a little man in the back

1507
01:27:04,182 --> 01:27:06,104
他问到 “你是什么人？到这来干什么？”
and he says, "Who the hell are you? What're you doing here?

1508
01:27:06,217 --> 01:27:09,072
“你不知道我要的是 一天能砍上百棵树的壮汉吗？”
"Don't you know that I need men who can chop down dozens of trees a day?

1509
01:27:09,187 --> 01:27:10,745
“你以前在哪干过活？”
"Where the hell have you ever worked before?"

1510
01:27:10,855 --> 01:27:13,187
小个子说 “我以前在撒哈拉森林干活”
And the little man says, "Well, I worked in the Sahara forest."

1511
01:27:13,291 --> 01:27:14,986
工头又问了 “你指的是撒哈拉沙漠吧？”
And the foreman says, "You mean the Sahara Desert."

1512
01:27:15,093 --> 01:27:17,425
小个子回答说“是的，那里砍完了！”
And the little man says, "Yes, sure, now!"

1513
01:27:21,266 --> 01:27:23,222
一名男子敲开了邻居的门…
A woman knocks at the door of her neighbor.

1514
01:27:23,368 --> 01:27:24,460
我没说过这故事吗？
I didn't tell you that?

1515
01:27:24,602 --> 01:27:28,891
一名女子说“我丈夫刚去世 我想卖掉他的夹克”
She says, "My husband just died. I want to sell his jacket."

1516
01:27:30,041 --> 01:27:32,930
他说“裤子怎么回事？”
He says, "What's the matter with the pants?"

1517
01:27:33,144 --> 01:27:35,237
她回答说“裤子我穿过了”
She says, "The pants, I wear."

1518
01:27:43,188 --> 01:27:44,883
俄国边境到了
The Russian border.

1519
01:27:50,628 --> 01:27:52,357
俄国边境到了
The Russian border.

1520
01:28:17,489 --> 01:28:19,787
他已经打仗了三个月
He's already fighting for three months.

1521
01:28:19,891 --> 01:28:23,884
现在已经加入布尔什维克 不再打仗了
Now he joined the Bolsheviks and he's not going to fight anymore.

1522
01:28:27,599 --> 01:28:31,421
他不是怕死 军队里有很多布尔什维克人
I don't think he's afraid. There are many Bolsheviks in the army.

1523
01:28:31,536 --> 01:28:33,663
布尔什维克人会阻止战争
And the Bolsheviks will stop the war.

1524
01:28:36,975 --> 01:28:38,636
他今年才14岁
He's 14 years old.

1525
01:29:10,775 --> 01:29:13,938
显然共产党人想要和平
The Communists obviously wanted peace. Rightly so.

1526
01:29:14,546 --> 01:29:17,709
因为俄国正处于风雨飘摇的局势…
Because the country was completely unable to sustain a war.

1527
01:29:17,816 --> 01:29:20,410
到处是叛变和腐败
There was treason and there was corruption.

1528
01:29:20,518 --> 01:29:22,406
一切都是有目共睹
There was everything under the sun.

1529
01:29:22,520 --> 01:29:25,751
但那是不可能…
But certainly... There was certainly no possibility

1530
01:29:25,857 --> 01:29:28,018
操纵战争的
of conducting a war.

1531
01:29:28,193 --> 01:29:30,616
克伦斯基急于操纵战争
Kerensky was anxious to conduct it,

1532
01:29:30,728 --> 01:29:35,256
他甚至招募女兵上战场
produce some battalions of women who were going to go and fight.

1533
01:29:39,571 --> 01:29:40,902
杰克・雷德！
Jack Reed!

1534
01:29:42,841 --> 01:29:45,071
亚历克斯，你在这里干什么？
Alex, what the hell are you doing here?

1535
01:29:45,176 --> 01:29:46,939
-有人接你吗？ -没有
- You have someone to meet you? - No.

1536
01:29:47,045 --> 01:29:48,842
幸好我来了！
Then what luck I am here!

1537
01:29:49,747 --> 01:29:50,839
-洛丝？ -是的
- Lois? - Yes.

1538
01:29:50,949 --> 01:29:52,007
我是亚历克斯・冈博
Alex Gomberg.

1539
01:29:52,116 --> 01:29:54,744
-找地方长住吗？ -不，住酒店
- Looking for accommodation? - No. Just a hotel.

1540
01:29:54,886 --> 01:29:57,446
真走运，我知道一套闲置的公寓
More good luck. I know of an empty apartment.

1541
01:29:57,555 --> 01:30:00,683
有交通工具吗？没问题，跟我来
You have transportation? No problem. Follow me.

1542
01:30:01,626 --> 01:30:04,958
许多人都认为乌托邦的理念正在成熟
A lot of people had an idea that Utopia was growing up.

1543
01:30:05,062 --> 01:30:08,121
我本来该责备 这个前布尔什维克主义
I could not blame them for being pro-Bolshevik,

1544
01:30:08,265 --> 01:30:09,697
但是我没有
but I wasn't.

1545
01:30:09,800 --> 01:30:12,393
完全忽略俄国的人是…
The one person who was awfully ignorant about Russia

1546
01:30:12,535 --> 01:30:14,456
-碧翠丝・韦伯 -对，就是她
- was Beatrice Webb. - Yes, she was.

1547
01:30:14,570 --> 01:30:15,968
她真是无知
She didn't know a thing.

1548
01:30:16,105 --> 01:30:18,959
不要被街道上的宁静气氛所误导
Do not be misled by the quiet in the streets.

1549
01:30:19,074 --> 01:30:20,665
暗地里都剑拔弩张着呢
Underneath is great tension.

1550
01:30:21,543 --> 01:30:23,999
亚历克斯，克伦斯基政府 还能支撑多久？
Alex, how much time has the Kerensky government got left?

1551
01:30:24,112 --> 01:30:26,568
随时会垮台，布尔什维克就要罢工了
Any day now, the Bolsheviks will strike.

1552
01:30:31,652 --> 01:30:32,742
很美妙吧？
Fantastic, isn't it?

1553
01:30:32,852 --> 01:30:36,183
宁静的街头就是彼得格勒的中心
A quiet street, and yet we are in the heart of Petrograd.

1554
01:30:37,856 --> 01:30:39,048
给他四卢布
Give him four rubles.

1555
01:30:43,095 --> 01:30:45,653
杰克，洛丝，幸好有我在
Jack, Lois. Lucky for you, I am here.

1556
01:30:46,564 --> 01:30:49,895
是的，谢谢了
Yeah. Thanks. Thanks again.

1557
01:30:53,470 --> 01:30:55,698
只有一张床？是双人床
Only one bed? That's a double.

1558
01:30:56,539 --> 01:30:59,131
单人床！我就睡这里…
Single. That's a single! This is where I'II...

1559
01:31:00,043 --> 01:31:02,100
这里不错，我可以…
This is good for me. I can just...

1560
01:31:03,712 --> 01:31:04,802
好
Good.

1561
01:31:10,451 --> 01:31:12,076
我一点都不介意
I don't mind this at all.

1562
01:31:24,431 --> 01:31:26,226
他说这是起义，对吧？
He's calling for an insurrection, isn't he?

1563
01:31:26,333 --> 01:31:28,128
夜以继日
Day and night. Day and night.

1564
01:31:28,567 --> 01:31:30,487
“另一个起义会摧毁俄国”
"Another insurrection will ruin Russia."

1565
01:31:30,603 --> 01:31:32,159
“另一个起义会拯救俄国”
"Another insurrection will save Russia."

1566
01:31:32,271 --> 01:31:33,998
“战争在摧毁俄国”
"The war is ruining Russia."

1567
01:31:34,106 --> 01:31:37,437
“没有英格兰或者法国，俄国会孤立无助”
"Without England or France, Russia will be isolated."

1568
01:31:37,575 --> 01:31:39,370
“布尔什维克在摧毁俄国”
"The Bolsheviks are ruining Russia."

1569
01:31:39,477 --> 01:31:41,773
洛丝，幸好有我在
Lois, lucky for you, I am here.

1570
01:31:41,913 --> 01:31:43,469
我叫路易丝
Louise.

1571
01:31:44,148 --> 01:31:46,011
这一排是等面包的
- This is the line for bread. - Yes.

1572
01:31:46,150 --> 01:31:48,207
另一排是等鞋子的
There's another line for boots.

1573
01:31:48,352 --> 01:31:50,739
还有一排等卡片
And there is still another line for cards

1574
01:31:50,854 --> 01:31:53,741
凭卡片可以在两三个月内领到鞋子
on which they'll get the boots in two, three months.

1575
01:31:53,957 --> 01:31:57,516
排队领面包非得铲除掉沙皇才行吗？
Did we have to get rid of the czar to stand in line for bread?

1576
01:31:59,028 --> 01:32:01,153
-什么意思？ -不知道
- What does that mean? - I don't know.

1577
01:32:03,265 --> 01:32:06,357
沃斯塔尼意思是起义 “Kerensky”是指克伦斯基
Vosstanie means "Insurrection," and "Kerensky" means "Kerensky,"

1578
01:32:06,501 --> 01:32:08,194
布尔什维克尔是指布尔什维克
and Bolsheviki means Bolshevik.

1579
01:32:08,437 --> 01:32:11,268
所以我认为布尔什维克 是想通过起义…
So I think it calls for an insurrection by the Bolsheviks

1580
01:32:11,372 --> 01:32:13,861
反对克伦斯基政府和克尼洛夫奇
against the Kerensky government and the kornilovtsy.

1581
01:32:13,975 --> 01:32:15,964
-什么叫克尼洛夫奇？ -路易丝，我的俄语不流利
- What's a kornilovtsy? - Louise, I'm not that fluent in Russian.

1582
01:32:17,244 --> 01:32:21,030
要是他们看中你的文章
Look, if they buy this,

1583
01:32:21,314 --> 01:32:23,769
他们会把文章删减成四五百字，对吧？
they're gonna cut you down to 400 or 500 words, aren't they?

1584
01:32:23,883 --> 01:32:27,271
-你之前好像写了5千字 -你删减了哪里？
- That starts out like you got 5,000. - Where would you cut?

1585
01:32:29,154 --> 01:32:31,916
这里还有这里
I'd lose this. I'd lose this.

1586
01:32:32,690 --> 01:32:34,485
你的主线是什么？
But what's your lead?

1587
01:32:36,493 --> 01:32:38,880
我知道你想什么，你指的是中心思想
Oh, I know what you think. You think the strongman line.

1588
01:32:38,996 --> 01:32:41,383
我不认为你的这个中心思想…
Well, I just don't know if you're gonna take anybody's breath away

1589
01:32:41,498 --> 01:32:44,351
吸引不了读者，知道吗？
with that for a lead. You know?

1590
01:32:46,602 --> 01:32:49,228
没错，太长了，太空泛了
You're right. It's too long, it's too general.

1591
01:32:49,338 --> 01:32:51,998
中心思想是最好的主线
And the strongman line is the best lead.

1592
01:32:55,610 --> 01:32:58,532
有些事你也有自己的正确看法
You've been right about something else, too.

1593
01:33:00,848 --> 01:33:03,872
布尔什维克会让俄国远离战争
The Bolsheviks will take Russia out of the war.

1594
01:33:06,353 --> 01:33:08,717
-晚安 -晚安
- Good night. - Night.

1595
01:33:09,522 --> 01:33:11,818
“街上的话题是和平与面包”
"In the streets the talk is of peace and bread.

1596
01:33:11,924 --> 01:33:13,378
“克伦斯基两者都没能提供”
"Neither of which Kerensky has provided."

1597
01:33:13,493 --> 01:33:14,856
“大家都知道会有事发生”
"Everybody knows that something is going to happen,

1598
01:33:14,894 --> 01:33:15,381
“大家都知道会有事发生”
"Everybody knows that something is going to happen,

1599
01:33:15,495 --> 01:33:16,755
“只是不知道什么事”
"but nobody knows just what."

1600
01:33:19,097 --> 01:33:20,119
什么事？
Yes?

1601
01:33:20,232 --> 01:33:22,118
对不起，我不会说俄语 我说英语
I'm sorry, I don't speak Russian. I'm English.

1602
01:33:22,234 --> 01:33:23,563
“彼得格勒夜不能眠”
"Petrograd does not sleep.

1603
01:33:23,668 --> 01:33:25,964
“晚上，争论越来越大声 人群越来越汹涌”
"At night, the arguments grow louder and the crowds thicken."

1604
01:33:26,103 --> 01:33:27,534
“谁都对克伦斯基不满”
"Nobody is satisfied with Kerensky.

1605
01:33:27,638 --> 01:33:30,230
“右派需要一个强人，左派需要和平”
"The far right wants a strongman, the far left wants peace.

1606
01:33:30,374 --> 01:33:32,363
“大家都对布尔什维克的举措拭目以待”
"Everyone waits to see what the Bolsheviks will do."

1607
01:33:32,510 --> 01:33:35,272
“描写布尔什维克领导人列宁很不容易”
"It is not easy to write fairly about the Bolshevik leader Lenin.

1608
01:33:35,345 --> 01:33:37,903
“他冰冷而专注，不容忍别人打搅”
"He is absorbed, cold, impatient of interruptions."

1609
01:33:38,014 --> 01:33:40,537
-你在这里发表社论了 -我从不发表社论
- You're editorializing here. - I never editorialize.

1610
01:33:40,650 --> 01:33:43,139
-结尾 -没错，删掉
- At the end. - You're right. Cut it.

1611
01:33:45,954 --> 01:33:47,817
我不明白的是…
What I don't understand is...

1612
01:33:48,323 --> 01:33:51,154
为什么删掉枪战的报道 它很精彩啊
Why did you take out the piece about the gunshot? It was very good.

1613
01:33:51,259 --> 01:33:52,383
-是不是精彩？ -是的
- It is good, isn't it? - Yeah.

1614
01:33:52,493 --> 01:33:54,118
放回去
Put it back in for me.

1615
01:34:00,867 --> 01:34:03,390
兹诺维耶先生 您还认为布尔什维克起义…
Mr. Zinoviev, do you still feel that the timing is wrong

1616
01:34:03,537 --> 01:34:05,264
不是时候吗？
for a Bolshevik insurrection?

1617
01:34:05,372 --> 01:34:07,326
“我在斯莫尔尼宫采访了兹诺维耶”
"I interviewed Zinoviev at Smolny.

1618
01:34:07,474 --> 01:34:08,734
“他一直和列宁在躲藏”
"He'd been in hiding with Lenin."

1619
01:34:08,841 --> 01:34:11,433
“已经躲藏了十年，并非一朝一夕”
...had another whole decade, less than a day.

1620
01:34:11,510 --> 01:34:13,931
“他的性格依然是躲躲闪闪的”
"His style is still that of a man in hiding.

1621
01:34:14,046 --> 01:34:15,739
“我们听到托洛茨基在斯莫尔尼宫的讲话”
"We hear Trotsky speak at Smolny.

1622
01:34:15,848 --> 01:34:18,212
“如果列宁代表着思想 托洛茨基代表行动”
"If Lenin represents thought, Trotsky represents action.

1623
01:34:18,316 --> 01:34:19,372
“那他就是十足的煽动家”
"He is essentially an agitator."

1624
01:34:19,484 --> 01:34:20,972
“斯莫尔尼宫的会客厅济济一堂”
"The meeting hall at Smolny was packed. At one point,

1625
01:34:21,086 --> 01:34:23,382
“讲台上的人叫同志们不要吸烟”
"someone in the platform asked the comrades not to smoke,

1626
01:34:23,488 --> 01:34:25,477
“所有的人，包括抽烟的人，全都叫道…”
"and everybody, including the smokers took up the cry,

1627
01:34:25,589 --> 01:34:27,680
“同志们，不要抽烟！ 然后又继续抽烟”
"'Don't smoke, comrades! ' And then they went on smoking."

1628
01:34:27,791 --> 01:34:29,882
“此时，托洛茨基说 我们正试图避免起义”
"At the point Trotsky said, 'We are trying to avoid insurrection,

1629
01:34:29,993 --> 01:34:31,720
“但是，如果克伦斯基政府袭击我们”
"'but if the Kerensky government attacks us,

1630
01:34:31,895 --> 01:34:32,952
“我们将会以牙还牙”
"'we shall answer blow by blow,'

1631
01:34:33,096 --> 01:34:34,983
“场下的听众一片欢腾”
"the audience broke into wild cheers."

