我相信耶稣的教导 我是否对魔力感到厌倦了？
I believe in the teachings of Christ. Am I being tried for witchcraft?

1801
01:48:00,686 --> 01:48:01,845
拜伦小姐，告诉我
Miss Bryant, tell me,

1802
01:48:01,954 --> 01:48:06,346
布尔什维克人中，是否没有正统 不畏惧上帝的基督徒？
are there no decent, God-fearing Christians among the Bolsheviks?

1803
01:48:06,495 --> 01:48:09,259
谁有必要做一个畏惧上帝 又是正统的基督徒？
Does one have to be God-fearing and Christian to be decent?

1804
01:48:09,399 --> 01:48:12,823
参议员，布尔什维克相信 这是种宗教，尤其是基督教
Senator, the Bolsheviks believe that it's religion, particularly Christianity,

1805
01:48:12,938 --> 01:48:15,702
这让俄国人民倒退了好几个世纪
that's kept the Russian people back for so many centuries.

1806
01:48:15,810 --> 01:48:17,265
-拜伦小姐 -如果你们谁去过俄国
- Miss Bryant... - lf any of you'd ever been to Russia

1807
01:48:17,412 --> 01:48:19,642
见到了农民，也许你们会赞同这一点
and seen the peasants, you might think they had a point.

1808
01:48:19,749 --> 01:48:21,740
参议员，就正统这点来说
On the subject of decency, Senator,

1809
01:48:21,852 --> 01:48:24,241
布尔什维克用一个口号取得了 政权战争的结束
the Bolsheviks took power with the slogan, "An end to the war."

1810
01:48:24,356 --> 01:48:27,519
6个月内，他们对俄国人民满口承诺
Within six months, they made good their promise to the Russian people.

1811
01:48:27,729 --> 01:48:29,955
1916年，美国总统去了俄国
Now, the present President of the United States of America

1812
01:48:30,061 --> 01:48:33,389
立场是无战争
went to this country in 1916, on a "no war" ticket.

1813
01:48:33,495 --> 01:48:35,380
6个月内，他就让我们卷入了战争
Within six months, he'd taken us into the war,

1814
01:48:35,495 --> 01:48:38,551
11.5万美国年轻人命丧他乡
and 115,000 young Americans didn't come back.

1815
01:48:38,862 --> 01:48:40,815
如果这是正统，畏惧上帝的基督徒行为
If that's how decent, God-fearing Christians behave,

1816
01:48:40,929 --> 01:48:42,917
那么我随时可能会做无神论者
give me atheists anytime.

1817
01:48:45,062 --> 01:48:47,913
参议员，在俄国，女人有投票权
By the way, Senator Overman, in Russia, women have the vote,

1818
01:48:48,029 --> 01:48:49,755
这个国家远远超乎你的想像
which is more than you can say for this country.

1819
01:48:49,862 --> 01:48:51,122
拜伦小姐
Miss Bryant,

1820
01:48:51,229 --> 01:48:54,524
你是否建议我们国家 也建立苏维埃政府？
do you advocate a Soviet government for this country?

1821
01:48:54,929 --> 01:48:57,087
不，我认为在这个国家行不通
No. In this country I don't think it would work.

1822
01:48:57,197 --> 01:48:58,560
赤色份子害怕吗？
In other words, you mean the Red scare?

1823
01:48:58,664 --> 01:49:01,027
是他们害怕，还是我们害怕？
They got scared, or we got scared?

1824
01:49:01,797 --> 01:49:03,230
不，我们不怕
No, we didn't get scared.

1825
01:49:03,567 --> 01:49:07,731
他们害怕工人会强大起来
They were afraid that the unions would grow in strength.

1826
01:49:07,905 --> 01:49:11,693
他们害怕美国激进分子的运动
A radical movement in America. They were scared.

1827
01:49:11,776 --> 01:49:12,936
是的
Oh, sure.

1828
01:49:13,044 --> 01:49:16,741
美国佬会怕得要死
The Americans, they were frightened to death by it, you know.

1829
01:49:16,882 --> 01:49:18,577
担心他们国家也会如此
That it could occur here.

1830
01:49:18,717 --> 01:49:21,948
当然，大家都怕得要命
Sure. Everybody was in mortal dread

1831
01:49:22,088 --> 01:49:24,318
怕政府抛弃他们
of the government descending on them.

1832
01:49:24,424 --> 01:49:27,222
那些FBI密探，等等群体
The FBI or whatever it was, don't you know.

1833
01:49:27,361 --> 01:49:29,056
我们必须揭露他们
We had to expose them.

1834
01:49:29,163 --> 01:49:32,155
一旦他们告诉了 美国人民什么是共产主义
And once they told American people what Communism was...

1835
01:49:32,501 --> 01:49:35,026
那么现在人们不可能跟 共产主义毫无关系
People won't have nothing to do with Communism now.

1836
01:49:35,137 --> 01:49:36,331
他们知道那是什么
They know what it is.

1837
01:49:36,438 --> 01:49:39,066
不过在当时，他们不知道 那是新事物
But then, they didn't know. It was a new thing.

1838
01:49:39,208 --> 01:49:42,837
公开的观念已经深入人心
Public opinion was solidly against anyone

1839
01:49:43,146 --> 01:49:46,172
他们对俄国革命一片好评
who had a good word for the Russian Revolution.

1840
01:49:46,617 --> 01:49:51,543
但路易丝是从自己的体会来谈的
But Louise was always communicating what she had experienced.

1841
01:49:53,024 --> 01:49:54,855
我带了毛毯来
I brought blankets, here,

1842
01:49:55,561 --> 01:49:57,892
还有厚外套
and a heavy coat, here.

1843
01:49:59,497 --> 01:50:01,157
还有咖啡
Chase and Sanborn.

1844
01:50:01,633 --> 01:50:02,621
手套
Gloves.

1845
01:50:02,734 --> 01:50:05,793
谢谢，杰克 其他人都只给我带了帽子
Thank you, Jack. Everyone else brought me hats.

1846
01:50:05,903 --> 01:50:09,929
路易丝捎来了她最好的，还有这个
And Louise sends you her best and this.

1847
01:50:11,742 --> 01:50:14,801
围巾，太好了
A scarf. Very kind.

1848
01:50:15,278 --> 01:50:17,268
时间到了
I'm afraid your time is up.

1849
01:50:16,895 --> 01:50:18,063
Well,

1850
01:50:20,116 --> 01:50:22,504
我们要继续战斗下去
we're going to keep fighting this.

1851
01:50:22,852 --> 01:50:25,945
你可否告诉麦斯 我想在杂志里刊登自己的照片？
Will you tell Max I'd like a picture of myself in the magazine?

1852
01:50:26,087 --> 01:50:30,113
我希望在照片下面写上“1919年受驱逐”
And under it, I would like the words, "Deported in 1919.

1853
01:50:30,258 --> 01:50:32,054
“这个世上最为强大国家的政府…”
"The government of the most powerful country in the world

1854
01:50:32,160 --> 01:50:33,114
“竟害怕这个女人”
"is afraid of this woman."

1855
01:50:34,095 --> 01:50:36,358
我们会救你出来的，埃玛
We're going to get you back, E.G.

1856
01:50:37,131 --> 01:50:39,894
革命需要你，我们会救你出去的
The revolution needs you. We're gonna get you back.

1857
01:50:40,000 --> 01:50:42,729
同志，我不会离开革命
Comrade, I'm not leaving the revolution.

1858
01:50:42,937 --> 01:50:45,097
要是在俄国，我也会加入革命
In Russia, I'll be joining it.

1859
01:50:45,271 --> 01:50:49,297
我迫切要求驱逐…
I urged the deportation of all

1860
01:50:51,077 --> 01:50:54,409
外来共产党员 所有的外来共产党员
alien Communists. All alien Communists.

1861
01:50:54,546 --> 01:50:57,309
有本国共产党员已经够受的了
It's bad enough having a Communist with us,

1862
01:50:57,482 --> 01:51:00,279
再加上外来共产党员就更要命了
but to have alien Communists who are not citizens,

1863
01:51:00,452 --> 01:51:03,147
他们宣布我们的政府形式 和共和制是无能的
denouncing our form of government and our republic

1864
01:51:03,255 --> 01:51:05,586
他们应该被驱逐
and everything else, they should be deported.

1865
01:51:05,790 --> 01:51:08,952
长久以来，我领导着一场大战
And I led a big fight on that for a long while.

1866
01:51:09,126 --> 01:51:11,787
当时的气氛不是很健康
It wasn't a very healthy atmosphere.

1867
01:51:12,396 --> 01:51:14,625
[路易丝生日快乐] 所以当约翰・雷德来的时候
So when John Reed came along,

1868
01:51:14,731 --> 01:51:17,255
他的发言我很喜欢
well, he was a voice of what I love.

1869
01:51:17,367 --> 01:51:21,928
他能够进入最有争议的话题
He was able to go into the most controversial subject of all,

1870
01:51:22,038 --> 01:51:23,561
共产主义，布尔什维克主义
Communism, Bolshevism.

1871
01:51:23,639 --> 01:51:27,665
他是公认的唯一能够做这类事的人
He was considered one of the rare persons who could do a thing like that.

1872
01:51:27,776 --> 01:51:30,767
他知道他站在了历史的新开端
He knew he was on the threshold of history,

1873
01:51:30,880 --> 01:51:32,471
他是这么写的
and he wrote it that way.

1874
01:51:39,387 --> 01:51:42,310
-这样翻… -杰克，我回来了
- A touch of this... - Jack, I'm back!

1875
01:51:42,422 --> 01:51:44,013
我在这里，亲爱的
I'm in here, honey.

1876
01:51:44,124 --> 01:51:46,512
今天我在李莱特家跟埃蒙和埃弗德谈过了
I talked to Edmund and Alfred today at Liveright's.

1877
01:51:46,627 --> 01:51:49,618
-今天真是收获不小 -别进来，亲爱的
- What a day it's turned out to be. - Stay out, honey! Stay out, stay out.

1878
01:51:49,997 --> 01:51:53,295
你在干什么？没事吧？
What are you doing in there? Is everything okay?

1879
01:51:53,733 --> 01:51:55,359
-要帮忙吗？ -不
- Can't I help? - No, no, no, no!

1880
01:51:55,468 --> 01:51:57,332
闻起来不错，是什么？
Sure smells good. What is it?

1881
01:51:57,403 --> 01:51:58,699
别进来，亲爱的 埃蒙说了什么？
Stay out, honey. What did Edmund have to say?

1882
01:51:58,738 --> 01:51:59,396
出去，亲爱的，埃蒙说了什么？
Stay out, honey. What did Edmund have to say?

1883
01:51:59,505 --> 01:52:02,632
他说几个星期之后钢铁工人就要罢工
He said in a few weeks the steelworkers will strike.

1884
01:52:03,408 --> 01:52:07,366
他说至少有20万人，也许有30万
He thinks at least 200,000 of them, and maybe as many as 300,000.

1885
01:52:08,747 --> 01:52:11,203
他认为这次阻止不了他们了
But he doesn't think there's any stopping them this time.

1886
01:52:11,316 --> 01:52:12,339
是吗？太好了
Yeah? That's good.

1887
01:52:12,449 --> 01:52:14,336
你考虑要发表什么评论吗？
You still thinking about doing a piece on it? I am.

1888
01:52:14,451 --> 01:52:17,647
现在不好说，他说下一步要怎么办？
Well, I can't really talk now, but what does he say the next step is?

1889
01:52:17,755 --> 01:52:20,848
显然联邦政府会说 组织者一定是赤色分子
Evidently the federal government's saying the steel organizers are Reds.

1890
01:52:20,959 --> 01:52:23,483
所以，他们会成立一个调查局
So what they're doing is forming a bureau of investigation

1891
01:52:23,594 --> 01:52:25,515
调查破坏活动
just to look into subversive activity.

1892
01:52:25,664 --> 01:52:28,393
以及调查那些工会联盟领导人…
And you know, with all this talk about the leadership of the AF of L

1893
01:52:28,500 --> 01:52:30,160
与钢铁托拉斯的密谋
being in cahoots with the Steel Trust,

1894
01:52:30,236 --> 01:52:33,693
埃弗德问我是否会报道 世界产业工人组织
Alfred asked me if I was still gonna do the piece on the IWW.

1895
01:52:33,805 --> 01:52:36,398
我对埃弗德说，目前我不想再进一步
So I said, "Alfred, for the moment I don't want to go any further away

1896
01:52:36,542 --> 01:52:38,372
-我宁愿待在新泽西 -是嘛？
- "than New Jersey." - Really?

1897
01:52:38,511 --> 01:52:40,398
很好
Oh, that's good. That's good.

1898
01:52:40,980 --> 01:52:42,537
-只是… -很好
- Just... - Yeah, it is good.

1899
01:52:42,715 --> 01:52:45,603
你先坐，我马上来
Sit down. I'll just be a minute.

1900
01:52:47,387 --> 01:52:48,876
杰克，你在干什么？
Jack, what are you doing?

1901
01:52:48,989 --> 01:52:52,651
-你怎么把稿件交给了埃蒙？ -他会刊登的
- How did you leave it with Edmund? - He's gonna read the piece on Debs.

1902
01:52:53,193 --> 01:52:54,989
第一道菜
Okay, the first course.

1903
01:52:55,228 --> 01:52:56,455
-是吗？ -坐下
- Yeah? - Sit down.

1904
01:52:57,632 --> 01:53:00,589
坐下，闭上眼睛，坐下
Sit down and close your eyes. Sit down.

1905
01:53:08,042 --> 01:53:09,065
好了
Okay.

1906
01:53:12,180 --> 01:53:15,137
天哪
Oh, my.

1907
01:53:16,251 --> 01:53:17,274
天…
My...

1908
01:53:18,587 --> 01:53:20,383
吃吧
- Go ahead. - Oh.

1909
01:53:27,897 --> 01:53:29,488
怎么样？
What do you think?

1910
01:53:30,833 --> 01:53:32,788
真的？真好吃？
Really? You serious?

1911
01:53:34,971 --> 01:53:38,827
真的？感谢上帝 我刚才还打算烧烤呢
Really? Thank God. I was gonna flamb?them out here,

1912
01:53:39,042 --> 01:53:42,272
没想到肉自己在锅里烧着了
but the goddamn things flamb闲d themselves in the pan.

1913
01:53:42,579 --> 01:53:45,638
在革命运动发展的过程中…
He was certainly the main inspiration

1914
01:53:45,916 --> 01:53:48,907
他受到了很大启发
in the development of a revolutionary movement

1915
01:53:49,053 --> 01:53:50,485
他将自已经历的历史事件
through his history

1916
01:53:50,588 --> 01:53:53,181
写就了《震撼世界的十天》
of Ten Days That Shook The World.

1917
01:53:53,357 --> 01:53:56,621
《震撼世界的十天》当然是他的杰作
Ten Days That Shook The World was, of course, his masterpiece.

1918
01:53:56,728 --> 01:53:59,616
布尔什维克革命的时候他在场
He was there when the Bolshevik Revolution took place.

1919
01:54:00,165 --> 01:54:02,325
他是最佳报道者
And his was the best report of it.

1920
01:54:02,534 --> 01:54:05,331
麦斯・伊斯曼说约翰・雷德当时…
Max Eastman had this story that John Reed came down,

1921
01:54:05,605 --> 01:54:09,461
头发蓬松，在全书关注写着一本书
tousled hair all, you know... And said he was writing a book

1922
01:54:09,574 --> 01:54:11,996
十天之内没有人打扰他
and not to disturb him for ten days.

1923
01:54:12,078 --> 01:54:14,875
那本书就是《震撼世界的十天》
And that became Ten Days That Shook The World.

1924
01:54:16,082 --> 01:54:17,275
估计是这样
Supposedly.

1925
01:54:17,784 --> 01:54:20,672
他获得了巨大的成功
He was an enormous, enormous success,

1926
01:54:21,320 --> 01:54:25,608
这次成功改变了他的一生
and this success largely changed his whole life, I think,

1927
01:54:25,959 --> 01:54:28,722
因为他发现有些东西他能做好
'cause he found out there was something that he could do well,

1928
01:54:28,829 --> 01:54:30,750
比任何人都做得好
do practically better than anyone else.

1929
01:54:31,131 --> 01:54:34,224
同志们，捕捉社会主义党革命者的计划
"Comrades, we have made a great stride forward in our program

1930
01:54:34,335 --> 01:54:36,996
取得了重大的进展
"to capture the Socialist Party for Revolution.

1931
01:54:37,104 --> 01:54:40,095
右翼党派的统治已经结束
"The time of right-wing domination of the party has ended.

1932
01:54:40,208 --> 01:54:43,734
他们还没来得及 像俄国革命那样炫耀
"They have fallen before the shining example of revolutionary Russia

1933
01:54:43,845 --> 01:54:45,903
就像保龄球瓶一样倒下了
"like so many bowling pins!

1934
01:54:48,383 --> 01:54:51,374
同志们，我们比预想的还要做得好
"Comrades, we have done better than we could have dreamed.

1935
01:54:51,520 --> 01:54:54,010
在社会党执行委员会中
"The left wing has won 12 of the 15 seats

1936
01:54:54,156 --> 01:54:56,077
左翼取得15票中的12票胜出
"on the Socialist Party Executive,

1937
01:54:56,193 --> 01:55:00,084
包括我自己 埃蒙・麦阿派尼和杰克・雷德
"including myself, Edmund MacAlpine and Jack Reed."

1938
01:55:08,408 --> 01:55:11,502
他从此平步青云
He took a tremendous jump forward from there on.

1939
01:55:12,011 --> 01:55:15,037
他成了工人阶级革命者
He became a revolutionist on the workers' side,

1940
01:55:15,483 --> 01:55:18,281
对威尔逊这样的人 已经不再抱有任何幻想
and he had no more illusions about people like Wilson.

1941
01:55:18,421 --> 01:55:19,580
我们都有问题
We all have problems.

1942
01:55:19,688 --> 01:55:22,611
你不能逃避问题，是不是？
You can't escape having problems, don't you know?

1943
01:55:22,757 --> 01:55:25,782
但要从人性角度考虑这个问题
But to take on the problem of all humanity,

1944
01:55:26,128 --> 01:55:28,015
来挽救人性
to save all humanity,

1945
01:55:28,130 --> 01:55:31,257
老天，对耶稣而言，那也是天大的事
my God, that was too big even for Jesus Christ.

1946
01:55:31,399 --> 01:55:33,457
耶稣就是这样被钉死在十字架上
Don't you know he got himself crucified?

1947
01:55:33,969 --> 01:55:36,857
我们要怎么才能做到这些事情？
How the hell do we expect to do those things?

1948
01:55:42,765 --> 01:55:44,100
Oh.

1949
01:55:48,250 --> 01:55:50,444
路易丝，是你吗？
Louise. Is that you?

1950
01:55:51,052 --> 01:55:52,484
你好，哈瑞
Hello, Harry.

1951
01:55:53,454 --> 01:55:56,650
最近去哪了？好久不见
Well, where have you been lately? I haven't seen you in a long time.

1952
01:55:56,790 --> 01:55:58,814
是的，会议要开一整天吗？
That's right. Is this thing gonna last all day?

1953
01:55:58,960 --> 01:56:00,620
可能吧，我们已经被排挤出来了
It might. We've been kicked out.

1954
01:56:00,762 --> 01:56:03,218
-被排挤出哪？ -社会党
- Kicked out of what? - The Socialist Party.

1955
01:56:03,364 --> 01:56:05,786
-等等，是谁干的？ -那屋子里的每一个人
- Wait, wait. Who got kicked out? - Everybody in that room.

1956
01:56:05,900 --> 01:56:07,628
执行委员会把我们赶了出来
The Executive Committee kicked us all out.

1957
01:56:07,735 --> 01:56:11,397
-整个左翼？ -对，他们宣布投票无效
- The whole left wing? - That's right. They nullified the election.

1958
01:56:11,639 --> 01:56:13,435
-他们能这样做吗？ -已经做了
- Can they do that? - They've done it.

1959
01:56:13,541 --> 01:56:14,871
我们占多数，我们有投票权
We're the majority. We have the votes.

1960
01:56:14,975 --> 01:56:16,373
但我们却被同僚排挤了出来
We weren't expelled by the membership.

1961
01:56:16,477 --> 01:56:17,966
被执行委员踢了出来
We were expelled by the executives.

1962
01:56:18,078 --> 01:56:19,738
而你还口口声声叫我们
And you're talking about doing exactly

1963
01:56:19,847 --> 01:56:21,677
按照执行委员会的话去做
what the Executive Committee wants us to do.

1964
01:56:21,782 --> 01:56:23,578
将党拱手相让！
Give the party back to them without a fight!

1965
01:56:23,684 --> 01:56:25,947
对，我们自己组织政党
Yes! And organize our own party!

1966
01:56:26,020 --> 01:56:28,874
去你的，路易 社会党本来就是我们自己的党
Goddamn it, Louis, the Socialist Party is our own party!

1967
01:56:28,988 --> 01:56:31,217
我们是通过党员投票当权
We were voted into power by its membership

1968
01:56:31,358 --> 01:56:33,313
绝不能被执行委员赶走
and we can't be expelled by the executives.

1969
01:56:33,427 --> 01:56:36,850
这是非法的举动 如果我们据理而争，我们会赢
It's an illegal act, and if we fight it at the convention, we'll win.

1970
01:56:36,963 --> 01:56:38,088
为什么一定要争？
Why do we have to fight?

1971
01:56:38,198 --> 01:56:39,425
你这么说什么意思？
What do you mean, "Why do we have to fight?"

1972
01:56:39,532 --> 01:56:41,055
大家都是为党尽忠…
For what do we stay in a party

1973
01:56:41,168 --> 01:56:44,796
为什么非要争个你死我活？
in which we must win control from the minority, not once, but twice?

1974
01:56:44,904 --> 01:56:47,394
什么意思，路易？ 如果有些东西要争取才能得来…
Well, what is it, Louis? You mean, if we must fight for what we deserve,

1975
01:56:47,507 --> 01:56:50,304
那就不要争取是吗？ 这就是你的革命思想？
then to hell with it? Is that your idea of revolution?

1976
01:56:50,411 --> 01:56:53,106
路易，我想再听听你其他的革命理念
I'd like to hear more about your revolutionary concept, Louis.

1977
01:56:53,214 --> 01:56:56,341
我的革命思想 不是我们政党的革命思想
My idea of revolution is not a revolution in my own party!

1978
01:56:56,449 --> 01:57:00,441
我们的社会党不是唇枪舌剑的政党
And my idea of a socialist party is not a debating society!

1979
01:57:00,521 --> 01:57:02,078
是一个行动的政党！
It is a party of action!

1980
01:57:02,188 --> 01:57:04,314
好…
Fine! Fine.

1981
01:57:05,058 --> 01:57:08,015
我们能给的最好例子就是召开大会…
The best example we can give them is go to that convention

1982
01:57:08,127 --> 01:57:09,491
控制好这个党
and take control of the party!

1983
01:57:09,596 --> 01:57:11,551
不，我们自己组织党
No! We form our own party!

1984
01:57:11,664 --> 01:57:14,996
我希望相信布尔什维克的在座各位…
And I hope that everybody here who believe in Bolshevism

1985
01:57:15,101 --> 01:57:18,365
当晚能来帮助组织一个党
will be there that night to help found that party!

1986
01:57:22,976 --> 01:57:24,863
但是你错了
All right, but I say you're wrong,

1987
01:57:24,978 --> 01:57:28,242
我会支持社会党的惯例…
and I say that I'm gonna be there at that Socialist Party convention

1988
01:57:28,347 --> 01:57:31,736
争取属于自己的席位 我也敦促在座的各位
to take the seat that belongs to me, and I urge everyone here today

1989
01:57:31,818 --> 01:57:34,513
不要放弃属于自己的席位
to be there to take the seats that belong to you!

1990
01:57:35,955 --> 01:57:38,218
他们好像想脱离群众意义
It's almost like they want to be separated from the masses.

1991
01:57:38,357 --> 01:57:40,688
他们想脱离群众，就是这样
They do want to be separated from the masses. That's the point.

1992
01:57:41,126 --> 01:57:42,251
我们走
Let's go.

1993
01:57:43,963 --> 01:57:46,089
我一直都是少数派
I've been in a minority before.

1994
01:57:47,332 --> 01:57:48,457
嗨
Hello.

1995
01:57:54,973 --> 01:57:56,496
他之所以喜欢草稿宣言…
While he liked the draft manifesto,

1996
01:57:56,608 --> 01:57:58,438
是因为他有点害怕社会爱国者条款
he's a bit nervous about the social-patriot clause.

1997
01:57:58,543 --> 01:58:00,271
-打断一下 -按道理说，他要遇到麻烦了
- Excuse me. - Tactically, he's gonna be trouble.

1998
01:58:00,379 --> 01:58:02,175
他是要求他的人服从惯例 还是不服从？
Is he gonna bring his people to the convention or not?

1999
01:58:02,282 --> 01:58:03,680
这人可以跟你谈上一年的理论
The man will talk theory with you all year.

2000
01:58:03,782 --> 01:58:05,544
我不这么想，他会支持佛莱纳
Well, I don't think so. He'll go with Fraina.

2001
01:58:05,617 --> 01:58:08,449
不是很好吗？ 他喜欢那宣言，卡诺夫斯基怎么样？
Isn't that nice? He likes the manifesto. How about Carnofsky?

2002
01:58:08,587 --> 01:58:10,781
杰克，我们可能得不到 预想的那么多支持
I don't think we're gonna have as much support as we thought, Jack.

2003
01:58:10,922 --> 01:58:12,786
我们单刀直入，卡诺夫斯基会怎么说？
We're gonna get in. What did Carnofsky say?

2004
01:58:12,891 --> 01:58:14,687
-他持反对意见 -我告诉你，杰克
- Carnofsky said no. - I'm telling you, Jack...

2005
01:58:14,793 --> 01:58:16,987
-了解自己的… -一半的佛莱纳支持者会来…
- Just knowing on our own... - Half of Fraina's people would come...

2006
01:58:17,095 --> 01:58:20,086
进来！路易丝，你让它安静点行不行？
Come in! Louise, please keep her quiet, will you?

2007
01:58:20,264 --> 01:58:21,423
-嗨，埃迪 -怎么…
- Hi, Eddie. - How can...

2008
01:58:21,532 --> 01:58:24,193
-嗨，埃迪 -嗨，路易丝，本
- Hello, Eddie. - Hello, Louise, Ben.

2009
01:58:24,303 --> 01:58:25,257
嗨
Hey.

2010
01:58:26,471 --> 01:58:27,903
埃迪，列文怎么样？
Eddie, what about Levine?

2011
01:58:30,308 --> 01:58:32,400
埃迪？
- Eddie? - Yeah.

2012
01:58:33,110 --> 01:58:36,203
-列文说了什么？ -他没出现，他…
- What did Levine say? - He never showed. He...

2013
01:58:36,682 --> 01:58:38,239
我等了一个多小时
I waited over an hour.

2014
01:58:38,316 --> 01:58:40,647
-列文没有露面 -这可不像他的风格
- Levine didn't show. - That doesn't sound like Levine.

2015
01:58:40,751 --> 01:58:42,581
对，你们在哪里见面？
Sure it does. Where were you meeting?

2016
01:58:42,720 --> 01:58:43,743
在凯西家
In Casey's.

2017
01:58:43,889 --> 01:58:46,812
惊讶，真是惊讶
Now, that surprises me. That really surprises me.

2018
01:58:47,224 --> 01:58:49,088
我可能没碰着他
I could have missed him.

2019
01:58:50,428 --> 01:58:51,724
那边真的很忙
It was really busy in there.

2020
01:58:51,829 --> 01:58:53,591
-没碰着他？ -什么意思？
- You could have missed him? - What's that supposed to mean?

2021
01:58:54,865 --> 01:58:56,058
我迟到了
I was late.

2022
01:58:57,735 --> 01:58:58,962
迟了多久？
How late?

2023
01:59:01,972 --> 01:59:03,962
40到45分钟
Forty, forty-five minutes.

2024
01:59:04,975 --> 01:59:07,829
诺拉今天早上又开始吐血
Nora started spitting up blood again this morning.

2025
01:59:10,548 --> 01:59:11,809
我必须带她去诊所
I had to take her to the clinic,

2026
01:59:11,915 --> 01:59:15,441
我还要等我妈妈来接我的孩子
and I had to wait for my mother to come and pick up the kid.

2027
01:59:15,853 --> 01:59:17,774
你迟到了45分钟
So you were 45 minutes late.

2028
01:59:19,290 --> 01:59:21,883
我以为我能赶到，真的
Yeah. I thought I could make it. I really did.

2029
01:59:22,025 --> 01:59:24,151
好吧，我们要联系这人 怎么联系？
All right, we gotta get in touch with the guy. How do we do it?

2030
01:59:24,260 --> 01:59:25,749
他现在正在去芝加哥的路上
He's on his way to Chicago.

2031
01:59:25,896 --> 01:59:28,159
所以我当时还以为他还在那里
That's one of the reasons I thought he would still be there.

2032
01:59:28,265 --> 01:59:29,822
等一下，你以为他还在那里？
Wait a minute, you thought he'd still be there?

2033
01:59:31,000 --> 01:59:33,593
-是的 -埃迪，是谁要求见面的？
- Yeah. - Who asked for the meeting, Eddie?

2034
01:59:34,204 --> 01:59:36,159
-谁要求见面？ -谁要求见的面？
- Who asked for the meeting? - Who asked for the meeting?

2035
01:59:36,273 --> 01:59:38,570
-列文要见面？ -是的，我以为他想见面
- Did Levine want the meeting? - Yeah, I thought he wanted it.

2036
01:59:38,708 --> 01:59:40,197
他给我们打过电话吗？
Did he call us?

2037
01:59:40,877 --> 01:59:41,865
不，我们给他打的电话
No. We called him.

2038
01:59:41,978 --> 01:59:44,673
那他为什么还会等？ 是我们想见面
Then why would he wait? We wanted the meeting.

2039
01:59:50,720 --> 01:59:51,845
对不起
I'm sorry.

2040
01:59:51,988 --> 01:59:54,547
为何不叫我们当中一个人代替你去？
Well, why didn't you call one of us and get somebody to take your place?

2041
01:59:55,992 --> 01:59:57,913
因为我以为我能赶到
Because I thought I could make it.

2042
01:59:58,027 --> 01:59:59,516
我以为他会在那里等
I mean, I thought the man would still be there.

2043
01:59:59,662 --> 02:00:03,358
你以为…不要自以为是，埃迪
You thought, you thought, you thought. Try not to think too much, Eddie.

2044
02:00:03,466 --> 02:00:06,299
同志们指靠你的时候，不要总自以为是
Not when your comrades are depending on you.

2045
02:00:07,371 --> 02:00:08,565
要确定
Be sure.

2046
02:00:13,944 --> 02:00:15,070
好吧
All right, look.

2047
02:00:15,179 --> 02:00:17,977
我们有没办法联系到芝加哥的列文？
Do we have a contact for Levine in Chicago?

2048
02:00:18,150 --> 02:00:19,412
给辛格打电话
Let's call Singer.

2049
02:00:19,518 --> 02:00:22,043
-你有他的号码？ -可能有
- Do you have a number for him? - Yeah. Well, I've probably got it.

2050
02:00:25,323 --> 02:00:26,585
给
Here.

2051
02:00:27,894 --> 02:00:29,088
谢谢
Thanks.

2052
02:00:30,363 --> 02:00:31,523
别光是喝咖啡…
You know, they might work better

2053
02:00:31,631 --> 02:00:34,725
吃点别的东西对你的胃更好
if you put something in your stomach besides coffee.

2054
02:00:35,535 --> 02:00:38,424
现在这种情况 你对埃迪是不是太刻薄了？
You're a little hard on Eddie, aren't you, under the circumstances?

2055
02:00:38,539 --> 02:00:40,461
你认为我的同情能够帮到 埃迪的妻子？
You think my sympathies can help Eddie's wife?

2056
02:00:40,574 --> 02:00:42,132
也许能帮到埃迪
Might help Eddie.

2057
02:00:42,242 --> 02:00:45,234
听我说，组建一个政党才能帮助埃迪
Listen to me. Building a party will help Eddie.

2058
02:00:52,921 --> 02:00:54,684
4，8，12…
Four, eight, twelve...

2059
02:01:01,630 --> 02:01:04,929
我们都有相同的信仰
You know, I think we all believe in the same things.

2060
02:01:07,603 --> 02:01:09,002
我们之间
But with us,

2061
02:01:10,807 --> 02:01:13,173
或多或少都存在好的意图
it's more or less our good intentions.

2062
02:01:15,545 --> 02:01:17,740
和杰克，那是宗教信仰
And with Jack, it's a religion.

2063
02:01:27,091 --> 02:01:29,946
我们的老朋友杰克对我们太认真了
Our old friend Jack's getting serious on us.

2064
02:01:32,498 --> 02:01:34,955
[1919年，芝加哥]

2065
02:01:35,000 --> 02:01:36,592
你好，弗兰克
Okay. Hey, Frank, how are you?

2066
02:01:36,735 --> 02:01:38,032
你好
How are you?

2067
02:01:41,474 --> 02:01:43,430
请问发生什么事了？
Excuse me. What's happening here?

2068
02:01:43,543 --> 02:01:46,376
执行委员会有令，没有红本本不准入内
No one's admitted without a red card. That's the order of the Executive.

2069
02:01:46,479 --> 02:01:48,777
我也是执行委员，他也是，他也是…
Well, I'm on the Executive, so is he, so is he...

2070
02:01:48,882 --> 02:01:51,373
-没有红本本不准入内 -哪里能弄到红本本？
- No one's admitted without a red card. - Where do we get the red cards?

2071
02:01:51,484 --> 02:01:53,349
找资格审查委员会
You'll have to take that up with the Credentials Committee.

2072
02:01:53,454 --> 02:01:54,682
资格审查委员会在哪？
And where's the Credentials Committee?

2073
02:01:54,722 --> 02:01:55,051
资格审查委员会在哪？
And where's the Credentials Committee?

2074
02:01:55,155 --> 02:01:56,588
不知道
I don't know.

2075
02:01:57,091 --> 02:01:59,116
我看他不希望我们进去
I don't think he wants us to go in there.

2076
02:01:59,193 --> 02:02:01,081
与高层人谈话就是难
Well, the way to take the hall is to take the hall.

2077
02:02:01,195 --> 02:02:02,492
埃蒙！
Edmund!

2078
02:02:02,597 --> 02:02:04,030
埃蒙！杰克！
Edmund! Jack!

2079
02:02:04,766 --> 02:02:08,156
好了，我们走，快来，这边
Okay. Let's go. Let's go. Come on, this way!

2080
02:02:11,706 --> 02:02:14,903
在提出议程之前，我先宣布…
To propose the agenda, I would like to read a message

2081
02:02:15,011 --> 02:02:18,640
资格审查委员会致台下各位的通告
from the Credentials Committee to the floor.

2082
02:02:18,781 --> 02:02:21,841
请后边肃静一下好吗？
May we please have order back there?

2083
02:02:22,552 --> 02:02:24,645
大厅后边的先生们，请…
In the back of the hall, could we have...

2084
02:02:24,755 --> 02:02:28,247
警官，请过去后面看看发生什么事
Sergeant-at-arms, would you see what's going on back there?

2085
02:02:28,692 --> 02:02:32,150
女士们先生们，看来有一群擅闯者…
Ladies and gentlemen, it seems we have a group of intruders

2086
02:02:32,229 --> 02:02:34,595
试图接管此次会议
who are trying to take over this conference.

2087
02:02:34,832 --> 02:02:36,823
我们不会让他们得逞
We're not going to let them.

2088
02:02:36,935 --> 02:02:40,701
请坐下，清理通道
Now, please, please sit down. I need these aisles clear.

2089
02:02:40,805 --> 02:02:43,968
警官，清理通道
Sergeant-at-arms, I must have these aisles clear!

2090
02:02:44,075 --> 02:02:45,940
各位请坐下
Please, everyone, sit down.

2091
02:02:46,178 --> 02:02:49,033
这些布尔什维克支持者…
Now, these are Bolshevik sympathizers

2092
02:02:49,148 --> 02:02:53,244
试图篡夺党政，我们绝对不容许
who are trying to take over this party, and we're not going to let them.

2093
02:02:53,452 --> 02:02:55,283
警察马上就到
The police are coming.

2094
02:02:56,222 --> 02:03:01,046
那些人不是社会主义者，而是暴徒
These people aren't socialists. These people are just thugs!

2095
02:03:01,428 --> 02:03:03,760
看到了吗？这就是布尔什维克的勾当！
Now you see? That is Bolshevik tactics!

2096
02:03:03,830 --> 02:03:05,821
代表们，这些人是冒名顶替者
Come on, delegates. These people are imposters!

2097
02:03:05,933 --> 02:03:08,060
他们并不是我们选举出来的领导人
They were not elected to the leadership of this party.

2098
02:03:08,169 --> 02:03:10,262
女士们先生们，警察来了
Ladies and gentlemen, the police are coming!

2099
02:03:11,706 --> 02:03:14,038
-看到了吗，警官？ -怎么回事？
- You see? The police. - What the hell is this?

2100
02:03:14,141 --> 02:03:17,099
执行委员会能够当权的唯一伎俩…
That's the only way the Executive Committee can stay in power,

2101
02:03:17,245 --> 02:03:18,974
就是利用资本主义警察
is by the use of the capitalist police.

2102
02:03:19,081 --> 02:03:20,309
把红本本拿出来
Flash your red cards!

2103
02:03:20,415 --> 02:03:22,838
他们不择手段让工人阶级…
They'll resort to any tactics to keep the working class

2104
02:03:22,951 --> 02:03:26,307
远离真正的领导人，因为他们害怕革命
away from its true leadership because they're afraid of revolution!

2105
02:03:26,421 --> 02:03:30,710
警官，没有红本本的人不是这里的人
Officers, whoever has no red card does not belong in this room.

2106
02:03:30,827 --> 02:03:31,919
举起红本本
Hold up your red cards.

2107
02:03:32,028 --> 02:03:34,656
好吧，我们走，不用你们赶
It's all right. We're going. You don't have to throw us out.

2108
02:03:34,764 --> 02:03:36,459
如果你们想知道
If you want to know where the true leadership

2109
02:03:36,566 --> 02:03:38,193
美国社会党真正领袖在哪里
of the Socialist Party of America is,

2110
02:03:38,268 --> 02:03:41,157
五分钟之后在大楼地下室见
it'll be in the basement of this building in five minutes...

2111
02:03:41,271 --> 02:03:44,035
-出示红本本 -欢迎你们加入
- Red cards, everybody! ...and you're welcome to join us.

2112
02:03:44,174 --> 02:03:47,962
没有红本本的人通通出去
I want anybody who does not have a red card to be out of this hall.

2113
02:04:35,531 --> 02:04:38,625
主席同志，我提议 我们该马上组建一个…
Comrade Chairman, I move that we immediately constitute ourselves

2114
02:04:38,734 --> 02:04:40,395
真正的共产党
as the bona fide Communist party,

2115
02:04:40,503 --> 02:04:42,767
名字叫美国共产主义劳工党
and that we call ourselves the Communist Labor Party of America.

2116
02:04:42,872 --> 02:04:43,861
赞成！
I second that motion!

2117
02:04:43,940 --> 02:04:46,067
如果我们要组建一个真正的革命党
Well, look, if we're gonna have a really revolutionary party,

2118
02:04:46,176 --> 02:04:48,838
那么我们应该向美国工人征求意见
I think what we have to do is to find out from the American worker

2119
02:04:48,945 --> 02:04:51,675
然后我们再把信息反馈给他们
what he wants the most and then we have to translate it back to him

2120
02:04:51,816 --> 02:04:53,681
通过劳工运动的方式
in terms of the labor movement as a whole.

2121
02:04:53,784 --> 02:04:55,308
我们要做的就是让工人想了解更多
What we have to do is make him want more.

2122
02:04:55,453 --> 02:04:58,183
让他们迫切要求一场全面革命
We have to make him want the whole goddamn revolution.

2123
02:04:58,289 --> 02:05:00,814
楼上的那些人认为卡尔・马克思 只是一个…
Those people upstairs think that Karl Marx was somebody

2124
02:05:00,925 --> 02:05:02,552
擅长编写反托拉斯法案的人
who wrote a good antitrust law.

2125
02:05:02,661 --> 02:05:04,822
不管我们自己的党叫社会主义劳工党
And whether we call our party the Socialist Labor Party

2126
02:05:04,930 --> 02:05:07,160
还是真正社会主义党，不管叫什么
or the Real Socialist Communist... Whatever we call the party,

2127
02:05:07,265 --> 02:05:09,460
都不重要，因为…
it doesn't matter because it...

2128
02:05:10,502 --> 02:05:12,231
路易，你迷路了吗？
Hello, Lou, are you lost?

2129
02:05:12,338 --> 02:05:15,296
没有，我是来告诉朋友们
No. I'm not lost. I'm here to tell my friends

2130
02:05:15,408 --> 02:05:17,968
这个新组建的美国共产党
that the newly-formed Communist Party of America

2131
02:05:18,044 --> 02:05:21,275
将要在蓝岛大街会见苏联代表
is meeting at the Russian Federation on Blue Island Avenue.

2132
02:05:21,380 --> 02:05:23,473
欢迎大家报名参加
We welcome your applications.

2133
02:05:23,650 --> 02:05:26,141
新党员将会基于个人成份来判定
They will be judged on an individual basis.

2134
02:05:26,286 --> 02:05:27,913
你要判定我们的申请人？
You're gonna judge our applications?

2135
02:05:28,055 --> 02:05:29,977
我们要向你申请党员资格？
We're gonna apply to you for membership?

2136
02:05:30,090 --> 02:05:32,479
主席同志，我要重申这个问题
Comrade Chairman, I'd like to call that question, please.

2137
02:05:32,626 --> 02:05:34,321
前面的提议已经得到通过
The motion has been made and seconded that

2138
02:05:34,429 --> 02:05:37,887
我们要立即组建一个真正的共产党
we immediately constitute ourselves as the bona fide Communist party

2139
02:05:37,999 --> 02:05:41,025
称之为美国共产主义劳工党
and that we call ourselves the Communist Labor Party of America.

2140
02:05:41,136 --> 02:05:43,525
赞成的人请表个态
All those in favor, please signify by saying aye.

2141
02:05:43,639 --> 02:05:44,663
赞成！
Aye!

2142
02:05:44,774 --> 02:05:46,662
有无人反对？提议通过
Opposed? Motion is carried.

2143
02:05:48,277 --> 02:05:49,904
同志们…
Comrades! Comrades!

2144
02:05:50,012 --> 02:05:53,778
同志们，内部斗争是个错误
Comrades, this is the wrong time to be fighting against one another.

2145
02:05:53,850 --> 02:05:56,875
我们应该联合起来对付资本主义
We should be united in our struggle against the capitalists.

2146
02:05:57,019 --> 02:05:59,043
路易，我们6周前就已经考虑过
You should have thought of that six weeks ago, Louis.

2147
02:05:59,188 --> 02:06:01,678
如果你的人支持我们，我们早已占大多数
If your people had stayed with us, we'd have had a majority,

2148
02:06:01,823 --> 02:06:03,585
我们早就当政
and we'd be in control of that convention upstairs.

2149
02:06:03,691 --> 02:06:05,385
我们的成员是你的五倍
We have five times your membership!

2150
02:06:05,492 --> 02:06:07,982
路易，你的算法跟你的政策一样愚蠢
Louis, your arithmetic's something like your politics.

2151
02:06:08,095 --> 02:06:11,655
我们要去蓝岛大街会见苏联代表
We will be at the Russian Federation on Blue Island Avenue.

2152
02:06:11,798 --> 02:06:13,458
希望到时能见到你们
I hope to see some of you there.

2153
02:06:13,566 --> 02:06:15,988
主席同志 我建议马上派出代表去莫斯科
Comrade Chairman, I move we immediately send a delegate to Moscow

2154
02:06:16,102 --> 02:06:17,625
为美国共产主义劳工党…
to gain recognition by the Comintern

2155
02:06:17,736 --> 02:06:19,293
争取国际共产主义的承认
for the Communist Labor Party of America,

2156
02:06:19,404 --> 02:06:22,031
-这个代表就是杰克・雷德 -赞同！
- and that delegate be Jack Reed. - Second the motion!

2157
02:06:22,140 --> 02:06:24,164
提议通过，同意派遣杰克・雷德…
The motion has been made and seconded to send Jack Reed

2158
02:06:24,241 --> 02:06:26,231
作为国际共产主义代表前往莫斯科
to Moscow immediately as the international delegate

2159
02:06:26,343 --> 02:06:28,298
为美国共产主义劳工党…
to obtain recognition of the Comintern

2160
02:06:28,411 --> 02:06:30,605
争取国际共产主义的承认
for the Communist Labor Party of America.

2161
02:06:30,747 --> 02:06:32,737
赞同的请表态
All those in favor, please signify by saying aye.

2162
02:06:32,882 --> 02:06:33,836
赞成
Aye!

2163
02:06:33,983 --> 02:06:36,007
有无人反对？提议通过
Opposed? Motion is carried.

2164
02:06:37,252 --> 02:06:39,845
既然第一条提议…
Since the first question I'm going to be asked...

2165
02:06:39,954 --> 02:06:41,181
好了，谢谢
All right, thank you.

2166
02:06:41,289 --> 02:06:43,711
同志们 既然共产国际对我的第一个要求…
All right, comrades, since the first question I'm gonna be asked

2167
02:06:43,825 --> 02:06:46,588
是关于党员的适合性
by the Comintern is gonna be about membership eligibility,

2168
02:06:46,693 --> 02:06:49,388
那么我会很清楚我们的地位…
I think I'm gonna have to be very clear what our position is

2169
02:06:49,496 --> 02:06:51,417
与国外语言联盟有重要关系
in relation to the Foreign Language Federation.

2170
02:06:51,530 --> 02:06:53,759
我要准确说出我们的要求就是…
I'm gonna have to say exactly what our requirements are

2171
02:06:53,866 --> 02:06:55,127
反对任何其他的群体
as opposed to any other group,

2172
02:06:55,234 --> 02:06:57,895
我想在我们的党章中 应该明确规定…
and I think we'll have to make it clear on our Platform Committee

2173
02:06:57,969 --> 02:06:59,333
在宣言里要说明
and be very clear in the manifesto.

2174
02:06:59,437 --> 02:07:00,664
-杰克，祝你莫斯科好运 -好，哈瑞
- Good luck in Moscow, Jack! - Okay, Harry.

2175
02:07:00,772 --> 02:07:03,535
你的人认为没有我你同样可以运作报社
Well, I guess you boys think you can run a newspaper without me.

2176
02:07:17,519 --> 02:07:18,974
嗨，杰茜
Hello, Jessie.

2177
02:07:22,022 --> 02:07:23,045
乖孩子
Good girl.

2178
02:07:25,693 --> 02:07:27,387
-嗨 -嗨
- Hello. - Hello.

2179
02:08:04,424 --> 02:08:07,881
我跟你直说吧，杰克 我不会跟你去的
Let me make it easy for you, Jack. I'm not going with you.

2180
02:08:14,799 --> 02:08:17,824
如果你要去 我不知道我会不会等你回来
And if you go, I'm not sure I'll be here when you get back.

2181
02:08:19,203 --> 02:08:23,992
路易丝，共产国际并不认识 埃蒙或者埃弗德…
Louise, you know, the Comintern doesn't know Edmund or Alfred

2182
02:08:24,107 --> 02:08:26,097
这些纽约来的北方佬 他们只认识我
from the New York Yankees. They know me.

2183
02:08:26,209 --> 02:08:28,733
要去那里的人一定要有背景
Somebody's got to go over there who's got a background.

2184
02:08:32,547 --> 02:08:34,502
我们圣诞节就回来
We'd be back by Christmas.

2185
02:08:38,753 --> 02:08:40,185
我们不能跟佛莱纳合并
We can't merge with Fraina.

2186
02:08:40,288 --> 02:08:42,152
不可能在成员适应性 跟他取得共识
We can't deal with him on membership eligibility.

2187
02:08:42,255 --> 02:08:44,347
他不会接受我们一半的党员
He wouldn't accept half of our people.

2188
02:08:44,491 --> 02:08:46,720
这人不会干别的事 只会让自己远离那些…
The man is gonna do nothing but alienate himself

2189
02:08:46,859 --> 02:08:49,315
潜在的广阔的支援基础
from any potential broad base of support.

2190
02:08:49,428 --> 02:08:50,883
他是个社会独立份子
He's sociologically isolated,

2191
02:08:51,030 --> 02:08:52,519
从程序上说，他根本处理不了…
programmatically he's impossible to deal with...

2192
02:08:52,664 --> 02:08:54,619
你是说他是外国人？
You mean he's a foreigner?

2193
02:08:54,966 --> 02:08:56,364
别这样，路易丝
Don't do that, Louise.

2194
02:08:56,467 --> 02:08:57,831
六个月前，你们还是朋友
Six months ago, you were friends.

2195
02:08:57,936 --> 02:08:59,392
这些人根本就不会说英语
These people can barely speak English.

2196
02:08:59,504 --> 02:09:01,961
他们甚至不想融入美国生活
They don't even want to be integrated into American life.

2197
02:09:02,373 --> 02:09:04,568
外语联盟也不会在 美国创造布尔什维克语
The Foreign Language Federations aren't gonna create Bolshevism

2198
02:09:04,676 --> 02:09:07,338
只不过是照搬俄国人的规矩
in America any more than eating borscht will.

2199
02:09:07,445 --> 02:09:09,003
做俄国人，不一定要革命
Being Russian doesn't make a revolution.

2200
02:09:09,113 --> 02:09:10,239
你以为美国工人…
Do you think the American workers

2201
02:09:10,315 --> 02:09:11,873
会被苏联同盟所领导？
are gonna be led by the Russian federations?

2202
02:09:11,983 --> 02:09:14,008
或者像佛莱纳那样的意大利人？
Or an insular Italian like Louis Fraina?

2203
02:09:14,118 --> 02:09:16,575
他也不可能在这个国家领导革命
He has no possibility of leading a revolution in this country.

2204
02:09:16,721 --> 02:09:17,847
你会有所不同吗？
Unlike you?

2205
02:09:17,989 --> 02:09:19,752
我只是说这个国家的革命…
I'm just saying that the revolution in this country

2206
02:09:19,891 --> 02:09:21,188
不会被移民者所领导
is not gonna be led by immigrants.

2207
02:09:21,292 --> 02:09:25,786
革命？在这个国家？ 什么时候？圣诞之后吗？
Revolution? In this country? When, Jack? Just after Christmas?

2208
02:09:26,097 --> 02:09:28,019
就算我们准备好了，你以为我们这次…
Well, what do you think we could've done with the steel strike

2209
02:09:28,132 --> 02:09:29,156
钢铁罢工就能成功？
if we'd been ready?

2210
02:09:29,267 --> 02:09:32,657
区区3万用理论武装头脑的党员
30,000 party members all armed with a unified theory and program

2211
02:09:32,770 --> 02:09:35,102
就能领导36.5万的钢铁工人罢工？
leading 365,000 steelworkers?

2212
02:09:35,206 --> 02:09:36,969
关键在于领导
What it takes is leadership.

2213
02:09:37,075 --> 02:09:39,407
我们要获得莫斯科那边的认可
And we gotta get it by getting recognition from Moscow.

2214
02:09:39,510 --> 02:09:40,943
-我一定要去 -你不一定要去
- I have to go. - You don't have to go.

2215
02:09:41,045 --> 02:09:43,809
是你想要去，你想要征服整个世界…
You want to go. You want to go running all over the world ranting and raving

2216
02:09:43,881 --> 02:09:46,247
组织高加索人领导革命
and making resolutions and organizing caucuses.

2217
02:09:46,351 --> 02:09:48,148
共产党与共产主义劳工党…
What's the difference between the Communist Party

2218
02:09:48,252 --> 02:09:49,549
有何区别？
and the Communist Labor Party

2219
02:09:49,687 --> 02:09:51,882
除了你跟他各自为政之外 还有区别吗？
except that you're running one and he's running the other?

2220
02:09:52,023 --> 02:09:54,150
-我已经答应了 -答应什么？
- I've made a commitment. - To what?

2221
02:09:55,193 --> 02:09:57,889
找到四分之一左翼 与二分之一左翼的区别
To the fine distinction between which half of the left of the left

2222
02:09:57,996 --> 02:10:01,295
就能让莫斯科认可真正的 美国共产主义劳工党？
is recognized by Moscow as the real Communist Party in America?

2223
02:10:01,399 --> 02:10:04,596
无耻的政治家与卑鄙的政治家争论不休
To petty political squabbling between humorless and hack politicians

2224
02:10:04,702 --> 02:10:06,863
只是在左翼教条上浪费时间吗？
just wasting their time on left-wing dogma?

2225
02:10:07,638 --> 02:10:09,697
获得苏联那边的认可…
To getting the endorsement of a committee in Russia

2226
02:10:09,807 --> 02:10:10,933
就能说明共产国际承认下的…
you call the International

2227
02:10:11,042 --> 02:10:13,567
你和地下室那14个朋友…
for your group of 14 intellectual friends in the basement

2228
02:10:13,678 --> 02:10:15,976
就能让工人对这个国家提出要求？
who are supposed to tell the workers of this country what they want,

2229
02:10:16,080 --> 02:10:17,604
就能说明他们要否执政？
whether they want it or not?

2230
02:10:25,390 --> 02:10:26,755
写作吧，杰克
Write, Jack.

2231
02:10:29,060 --> 02:10:31,119
你不是政治家，你是作家
You're not a politician, you're a writer.

2232
02:10:31,262 --> 02:10:32,991
你的写作成就已经超过…
And your writing has done more for the revolution

2233
02:10:33,097 --> 02:10:35,827
20年混战的成就，你知道的
than 20 years of this infighting can do, and you know it.

2234
02:10:36,901 --> 02:10:38,766
杰克，你是文学家
You're an artist, Jack.

2235
02:11:01,292 --> 02:11:02,486
别去
Don't go.

2236
02:11:03,661 --> 02:11:06,391
别放弃你的长处
Don't run away from what you do the best.

2237
02:11:09,934 --> 02:11:10,992
杰克
Jack.

2238
02:11:20,712 --> 02:11:22,373
我会在圣诞节前回来
I'll be back by Christmas.

2239
02:11:48,376 --> 02:11:51,106
我要去市里，你什么时候走？
I'm going into the city. When do you leave?

2240
02:11:51,214 --> 02:11:52,442
明天
Tomorrow.

2241
02:11:53,116 --> 02:11:55,505
-知道了 -我会在圣诞节前回来
- I see. - I'll be back by Christmas.

2242
02:11:56,486 --> 02:11:58,078
你会在家吗？
Will you be here?

2243
02:12:00,991 --> 02:12:03,824
不知道，见面的时候自然能见到你
I don't know. I'll see you when I see you.

2244
02:12:20,412 --> 02:12:24,234
你的护照和证件，你叫詹姆斯・格雷
Here. Your passport and papers. Your name's James Gormley.

2245
02:12:26,019 --> 02:12:27,179
快去吧
Go now!

2246
02:13:11,536 --> 02:13:15,165
雷德太太，请坐
Well, Mrs. Reed. Sit down.

2247
02:13:16,074 --> 02:13:17,803
有什么事吗？
What can I do for you?

2248
02:13:17,909 --> 02:13:20,901
你好吗，尤金？
Hello, Gene. How are you?

2249
02:13:22,048 --> 02:13:24,937
我很好，你呢？
Fine. And you?

2250
02:13:25,785 --> 02:13:27,013
我很好
I'm fine.

2251
02:13:39,934 --> 02:13:41,162
坐
Sit down.

2252
02:13:47,176 --> 02:13:50,566
-杰克怎么样？ -他很好，他去了俄国
- How's Jack? - He's fine. He's in Russia.

2253
02:13:50,679 --> 02:13:51,805
-是吗？ -是的
- Is he? - Yes.

2254
02:13:51,914 --> 02:13:53,677
他要为共产主义劳工党…
He's trying to get recognition from the Comintern

2255
02:13:53,782 --> 02:13:55,909
争取共产国际的认可
for the Communist Labor Party.

2256
02:13:56,019 --> 02:13:58,874
他们的政党已经一分为二
You see, they've split into two different factions.

2257
02:13:59,155 --> 02:14:02,818
你呢？又是一个人孤单工作？
And you? Left alone with your work again?

2258
02:14:04,662 --> 02:14:05,651
不
No.

2259
02:14:06,063 --> 02:14:08,452
事实上是的，但我现在的工作不一样了
Well, actually, yes, but my work is different now.

2260
02:14:08,566 --> 02:14:11,364
我到处演讲我在俄国的经历
I do a lot of lecturing about what I saw in Russia.

2261
02:14:11,435 --> 02:14:12,993
哦，俄国
Ah, yes, Russia.

2262
02:14:14,106 --> 02:14:16,563
俄国对你跟杰克都很好
Russia's been good for you and Jack.

2263
02:14:16,875 --> 02:14:20,800
给你理由去约会，给他理由离开家
Given you a way to meet people, given him a reason to leave home.

2264
02:14:22,649 --> 02:14:23,775
俄国
Russia.

2265
02:14:25,084 --> 02:14:26,210
俄国
Russia.

2266
02:14:26,319 --> 02:14:29,015
你是偏激还是在生我气？
Are you really that cynical, or are you angry with me?

2267
02:14:29,122 --> 02:14:31,852
我真的很偏激，我干嘛要生你的气？
I'm really that cynical. Why would I be angry with you?

2268
02:14:31,959 --> 02:14:33,392
尤金，如果你去过俄国…
Gene, if you'd been to Russia,

2269
02:14:33,494 --> 02:14:35,519
那么你对任何事情都不会再偏激
you'd never be cynical about anything again.

2270
02:14:35,629 --> 02:14:38,427
你会看到寻常百姓都在转变
You would have seen people transformed. Ordinary people.

2271
02:14:38,532 --> 02:14:43,128
路易丝，当一个美国人的智慧双眼 闪闪发亮时我会很紧张
Louise, something in me tightens when an American intellectual's eyes shine

2272
02:14:43,405 --> 02:14:46,465
尤其是他们吹捧俄国人的时候
and they start to talk to me about the Russian people.

2273
02:14:46,608 --> 02:14:48,473
-等等… -我会说留意了
- Wait... - Something in me says, "Watch it.

2274
02:14:48,576 --> 02:14:52,637
一个新版的爱尔兰天主教 已经提供给你新的信仰
"A new version of Irish Catholicism is being offered for your faith."

2275
02:14:52,815 --> 02:14:54,339
-不是的 -我就是不清楚…
- It's not like that. - And I wonder why

2276
02:14:54,483 --> 02:14:59,079
为什么见惯世面的路易丝・雷德…
a lovely wife like Louise Reed who's just seen the brave new world

2277
02:14:59,189 --> 02:15:01,555
会和我这么一个偏激狂坐在一起
is sitting around with a cynical bastard like me

2278
02:15:01,658 --> 02:15:05,583
而不是跟随理想主义的老公 在俄国驰骋疆场？
instead of trotting all over Russia with her idealistic husband.

2279
02:15:06,196 --> 02:15:09,825
这样的转变是值得的
It's almost worth being converted.

2280
02:15:13,071 --> 02:15:14,959
我来错地方了
Well, I was wrong to come.

2281
02:15:15,773 --> 02:15:19,698
你和杰克因为激进而拥有许多 中产阶级的梦想
You and Jack have a lot of middle-class dreams for two radicals.

2282
02:15:20,579 --> 02:15:23,969
杰克的梦想是能够领导美国工人
Jack dreams that he can hustle the American working man,

2283
02:15:24,116 --> 02:15:26,846
而工人的梦想是不劳而获，坐享其成
whose one dream is to be rich enough not to have to work,

2284
02:15:26,986 --> 02:15:29,443
所以才加入了他所领导的政党
into a revolution led by his party.

2285
02:15:29,656 --> 02:15:32,489
你的梦想就是 在你跟某个男人上床之前…
And you dream that if you discuss the revolution with a man

2286
02:15:32,592 --> 02:15:34,287
如果你跟他讨论革命
before you go to bed with him,

2287
02:15:34,394 --> 02:15:36,726
那么你是在传教而非在做爱
it'll be missionary work rather than sex.

2288
02:15:37,398 --> 02:15:40,788
看到你跟你杰克这么认真对待 你的运动我深感难过
I'm sorry to see you and Jack so serious about your sports.

2289
02:15:40,901 --> 02:15:43,358
也对你感到失望，路易丝
It's particularly disappointing in you, Louise.

2290
02:15:43,471 --> 02:15:47,134
一享受到自由恋爱时，你就欲火焚身
You had a lighter touch when you were touting free love.

2291
02:15:49,711 --> 02:15:52,509
看不出来你已经成评论家了，尤金
Boy, you've become quite the critic, haven't you, Gene?

2292
02:15:52,615 --> 02:15:55,175
背靠椅子就能分析透彻我们
Just leaned back and analyzed us all.

2293
02:15:55,485 --> 02:15:58,113
被灌输自由恋爱思想的女人结了婚
Duplicitous women who tout free love and then get married,

2294
02:15:58,254 --> 02:16:00,449
盲从的记者加入了革命…
power-mad journalists who join the revolution

2295
02:16:00,590 --> 02:16:01,818
而不是袖手旁观
instead of observing it,

2296
02:16:01,958 --> 02:16:04,051
中产阶级激进分子来寻欢作乐…
middle-class radicals who come looking for sex

2297
02:16:04,193 --> 02:16:05,649
顺便谈谈俄国革命
and then talk about Russia.

2298
02:16:05,762 --> 02:16:07,923
你这样的人真可悲
It must seem so contemptible to a man like you

2299
02:16:08,030 --> 02:16:10,954
竟然还有勇气端坐在这里…
who has the courage to sit on his ass and observe human inadequacy

2300
02:16:11,067 --> 02:16:12,762
坐视人性的缺陷
from the inside of a bottle.

2301
02:16:12,869 --> 02:16:15,064
但我从未见你帮过任何人
Well, I've never seen you do anything for anyone.

2302
02:16:15,171 --> 02:16:16,627
也从未见你给别人任何东西
I've never seen you give anything to anyone,

2303
02:16:16,739 --> 02:16:20,129
所以我能理解你会怀疑 别人动机不良
so I can understand why you might suspect the motives of those who have.

2304
02:16:20,243 --> 02:16:22,609
不管杰克的动机是什么…
But whatever Jack's motives are, how...

2305
02:16:24,247 --> 02:16:26,442
我似乎触及到了你的伤口
I seem to have touched a wound.

2306
02:16:28,951 --> 02:16:30,350
你是个受伤的王八蛋
You're a wounding son of a bitch,

2307
02:16:30,486 --> 02:16:33,819
不管我给你带来什么伤害 你已经让我付出了代价
and whatever I've done to you, you've made me pay for it.

2308
02:16:35,658 --> 02:16:36,920
路易丝
Louise.

2309
02:17:06,055 --> 02:17:07,181
杰茜！
Jessie!

2310
02:17:07,790 --> 02:17:10,782
嗨，杰茜，快回来
Hey, Jess, come on! Come here, Jess.

2311
02:17:11,194 --> 02:17:12,752
杰茜，回来
Jessie, come here.

2312
02:17:18,301 --> 02:17:19,461
杰茜
Jessie.

2313
02:17:56,472 --> 02:17:57,632
杰茜？
Jessie?

2314
02:18:15,591 --> 02:18:16,546
杰茜？
Jessie?

2315
02:18:16,692 --> 02:18:18,148
晚上好
- Oh! - Good evening.

2316
02:18:18,294 --> 02:18:20,421
经美国司法部长授权…
By the order of the Attorney General of the United States,

2317
02:18:20,530 --> 02:18:22,225
米切尔・帕默探长奉命前来搜查
A. Mitchell Palmer, I have a warrant here

2318
02:18:22,331 --> 02:18:24,060
并逮捕约翰・雷德
for the arrest of one John Silas Reed.

2319
02:18:24,166 --> 02:18:25,929
弗兰克，上楼看看
Look upstairs, Frank.

2320
02:18:32,975 --> 02:18:35,102
-以什么罪名逮捕？ -煽动暴乱
- Arrest for what? - Sedition.

2321
02:18:35,845 --> 02:18:37,938
-他在哪里？ -什么煽动暴乱？
- Where is he? - What do you mean by sedition?

2322
02:18:38,014 --> 02:18:40,312
女士，别问我，问伍德洛・威尔逊
Lady, don't ask me. Ask Woodrow Wilson.

2323
02:18:40,416 --> 02:18:42,145
告诉我他在哪里
Just tell me where he is.

2324
02:18:47,657 --> 02:18:48,817
我看你不像是什么…
I don't suppose there's a chance

2325
02:18:48,958 --> 02:18:51,415
布尔什维克煽动家，是不是？
of you being a Bolshevik agitator, is there?

2326
02:18:52,228 --> 02:18:55,425
你干嘛不找找看 有什么煽动你的东西？
Why don't you just look around, and see how agitated you get?

2327
02:18:55,865 --> 02:18:57,821
在1919年
In 1919,

2328
02:18:58,401 --> 02:19:00,460
只有不到…
there were no more

2329
02:19:00,570 --> 02:19:04,097
四五个美国人…
than four or five Americans

2330
02:19:04,373 --> 02:19:06,238
进入到苏联
who got into Russia

2331
02:19:06,442 --> 02:19:11,300
因为整个国家周边都被包围着
because the country was surrounded on all sides.

2332
02:19:11,681 --> 02:19:15,572
当时有禁令，所以我们只能非法偷渡
You were actually forbidden to go, and you could only go illegally.

2333
02:19:15,785 --> 02:19:18,640
穿过芬兰是非常危险的
It was very dangerous to go through Finland.

2334
02:19:19,021 --> 02:19:21,478
因为芬兰是白色政权统治
Because the Finns were a White government,

2335
02:19:21,624 --> 02:19:24,548
那里反对红色政权
and they were bitterly opposed to the Reds.

2336
02:19:24,927 --> 02:19:26,724
他们决定将…
They decided to strangle

2337
02:19:26,829 --> 02:19:30,185
布尔什维克扼杀在摇篮之中
the revolutionary Bolshevik infant in its cradle.

2338
02:19:30,299 --> 02:19:34,429
16支部队从东西两路进逼苏联…
And 16 armies went into Russia from the east and from the west,

2339
02:19:34,670 --> 02:19:36,934
为了消灭布尔什维克势力…
for the purpose of wiping out the Bolsheviks

2340
02:19:37,039 --> 02:19:38,927
以及镇压革命
and wiping out the revolution

2341
02:19:39,041 --> 02:19:43,364
让基督教文明恢复到公正的地位
and restoring Christian civilization to its rightful place.

2342
02:20:09,138 --> 02:20:10,469
说英语吧
Speak English.

2343
02:20:10,573 --> 02:20:12,803
吃柠檬吧，很难吃得到的
Have a lemon. You won't see one for a long time.

2344
02:20:12,908 --> 02:20:16,332
谢谢，我只想知道你是否觉得…
Thank you. I just want to know if you think that I was clear

2345
02:20:16,445 --> 02:20:18,640
-我刚才说的已然清楚… -非常清楚
- in what I said about... - Eminently clear.

2346
02:20:18,714 --> 02:20:19,772
加盐吗？
Salt?

2347
02:20:21,450 --> 02:20:23,213
-加盐？ -用来配柠檬
- Salt? - For the lemon.

2348
02:20:23,819 --> 02:20:25,116
谢谢
Thank you.

2349
02:20:27,223 --> 02:20:29,748
我看见你吃柠檬皮
I see you eat the peel with the lemon.

2350
02:20:30,059 --> 02:20:33,017
抵抗坏血病，洋葱也行
Fights the scurvy. So does the onion.

2351
02:20:33,829 --> 02:20:36,161
一起吃抵抗力更强
Together, they fight better.

2352
02:20:38,367 --> 02:20:40,892
我真正想知道的是…
You see, what I really wanted to do

2353
02:20:41,003 --> 02:20:43,563
您能不能坦率地回答…
was ask your frank opinion whether we...

2354
02:20:43,673 --> 02:20:46,767
我们党是否会得到委员会的认可
You think we'll get the endorsement from the committee.

2355
02:20:46,909 --> 02:20:49,833
-当然是非正式的问 -非正式？
- I ask unofficially, of course. - Unofficially?

2356
02:20:53,115 --> 02:20:55,106
非正式地，我不知道
Unofficially, I don't know.

2357
02:20:56,252 --> 02:20:58,584
这是一个…
Yeah, well, it's such a...

2358
02:20:58,888 --> 02:21:02,051
美国式的问题，我…
It's a peculiarly American problem and I...

2359
02:21:02,525 --> 02:21:05,187
-我说得够清楚吗？ -非常清楚
- You do think I was clear? - Quite clear.

2360
02:21:05,461 --> 02:21:09,488
但你的提议不一定能保证得到认可
In this case, however, clarity does not necessarily guarantee endorsement.

2361
02:21:09,699 --> 02:21:12,691
我不知道，也许会如此
Well, I don't know. In this case, I think perhaps it might.

2362
02:21:12,802 --> 02:21:16,568
实际上，我不…
You know, in fact, I don't...

2363
02:21:16,672 --> 02:21:19,561
我其实是想做一个详细的报告
What I really want to do is to make a detailed report

2364
02:21:19,675 --> 02:21:22,508
让执行委员会了解美国的情况
for the Executive Committee to read on conditions in America.

2365
02:21:22,611 --> 02:21:25,671
我想把美国劳工联合会的整个历史…
You see, I'd like to deal in that report with the entire history

2366
02:21:25,748 --> 02:21:27,375
写在报告里面
of the American Federation of Labor.

2367
02:21:27,483 --> 02:21:29,644
我想写明它支持革命战争的立场
I'd like to deal with its support of the war, you see.

2368
02:21:29,752 --> 02:21:33,017
我要检举世界产业工人组织的迫害
And I'm gonna talk about the persecution of the IWW,

2369
02:21:33,155 --> 02:21:35,646
还要反映爱国社团的崛起
I'm gonna deal with the rise of the patrioteering societies,

2370
02:21:35,791 --> 02:21:37,656
以及举报社会党领导人的叛变
and the capitulation of leading socialists.

2371
02:21:37,760 --> 02:21:40,251
-我要…我说得太快了吗？ -不，继续说
- I'm gonna... Am I speaking too quickly? - No, no. Go on.

2372
02:21:40,463 --> 02:21:45,162
我要反映美国劳工崛起的战斗性
And so I will deal with the rising militancy of American labor.

2373
02:21:45,334 --> 02:21:49,065
还有西雅图和温尼伯湖的罢工
I'll talk about the general strikes in Seattle and Winnipeg,

2374
02:21:49,171 --> 02:21:50,536
以及波士顿警察罢工
the Boston police strike.

2375
02:21:50,639 --> 02:21:53,699
我要讨论普拉姆计划 以及左派的特殊态度和政策
I'm gonna discuss the Plumb Plan, and particularly the attitude

2376
02:21:53,809 --> 02:21:56,573
世界产业工人组织对他们的影响
and the policies of the AF of L and IWW toward them.

2377
02:21:56,679 --> 02:21:58,670
之后，我想重要的是…
Now, after that, I think it's important...

2378
02:22:06,021 --> 02:22:08,478
雷德同志，共产国际执行委员会…
Comrade Reed, the Executive Committee of the Comintern

2379
02:22:08,691 --> 02:22:11,922
决定对共产主义工党和美国共产党…
has decided against endorsing either the Communist Labor Party

2380
02:22:12,027 --> 02:22:13,983
不予承认
or the Communist Party of America,

2381
02:22:14,096 --> 02:22:17,020
随即命令两个政党马上合并
and instructs the two parties to merge forthwith.

2382
02:22:22,505 --> 02:22:23,733
这里坐，雷德同志
Sit here, Comrade Reed.

2383
02:22:23,839 --> 02:22:25,795
你的座位之所以被占用…
This time, your usual chair, as you can see,

2384
02:22:25,908 --> 02:22:28,866
是因为我们现在要详细研究美国的形势
is now occupied by your detailed report on American conditions.

2385
02:22:28,978 --> 02:22:31,469
一个非常深入的研究，非常清晰
A most penetrating study. Very, very clear.

2386
02:22:31,580 --> 02:22:32,774
谢谢
Thank you.

2387
02:22:33,315 --> 02:22:35,476
显然，还不够清楚
Obviously, it wasn't clear enough.

2388
02:22:36,485 --> 02:22:37,611
拉德克同志
Comrade Radek,

2389
02:22:37,753 --> 02:22:40,244
我想，你们肯定搞错了…
I think there must have been some mistake

2390
02:22:40,389 --> 02:22:43,449
我回美国的旅程安排
about my travel arrangements about my return to the United States.

2391
02:22:44,393 --> 02:22:48,750
我好像还要去宣传部那里报到
Well, it seems as if I've been asked to report to the Propaganda Bureau.

2392
02:22:48,864 --> 02:22:49,990
没错
That is right.

2393
02:22:50,099 --> 02:22:53,455
雷德同志，执行委员会决定…
Comrade Reed, the Executive Committee has decided

2394
02:22:53,569 --> 02:22:56,163
宣传部非常需要你
you are very much needed at the Propaganda Bureau.

2395
02:22:56,272 --> 02:22:58,934
我们要你留在苏联工作，直到7月
We plan for you to remain in Soviet Russia until July.

2396
02:22:59,041 --> 02:23:01,100
宣传部非常欢迎你的到来
You're very welcome to the Bureau of Propaganda.

2397
02:23:01,210 --> 02:23:02,507
非常感谢
Well, thank you very much,

2398
02:23:02,611 --> 02:23:05,341
可是我的旅程已经安排好了
but I thought that these travel arrangements had been made.

2399
02:23:05,414 --> 02:23:07,712
我要去拉脱维亚或者芬兰边境
I have to get to the Latvian or the Finnish border.

2400
02:23:07,817 --> 02:23:09,978
你建议去哪个边境，雷德同志？
And to which border would you suggest, Comrade Reed?

2401
02:23:10,119 --> 02:23:12,576
我明白火车旅行此刻很危险
Well, I understand that train travel is very dangerous at the moment...

2402
02:23:12,721 --> 02:23:14,279
他为何要坐火车？
Why does he need a train?

2403
02:23:15,391 --> 02:23:18,690
因为我有很紧急的私人事项…
Because I have urgent personal considerations and responsibilities

2404
02:23:18,794 --> 02:23:20,955
-要回美国… -什么事项呢？
- in the United States and I... - Of what nature?

2405
02:23:21,864 --> 02:23:23,786
-你说什么？ -什么要事呢？
- Excuse me? - Of what nature?

2406
02:23:28,070 --> 02:23:30,698
-我有家庭 -我们大家都有家庭
- I have a family. - We all have families.

2407
02:23:32,208 --> 02:23:36,599
我只能代表我自己说话 我要见我的妻子
Well, I can speak only for myself and I must see my wife.

2408
02:23:36,712 --> 02:23:38,145
这非常紧急
It's very urgent,

2409
02:23:39,348 --> 02:23:43,239
我只需要火车上一个座位
and I ask only for a single place on a train.

2410
02:23:43,352 --> 02:23:44,717
可你已经有座位了
But you have a place on the train!

2411
02:23:44,854 --> 02:23:46,845
你在这革命的火车上有座位了
You have a place on the train of this revolution.

2412
02:23:46,989 --> 02:23:49,321
你和其他革命者一样，都是最优秀的
You have been like so many others, the best revolutionaries.

2413
02:23:49,425 --> 02:23:51,757
你是这火车机车上的一个工程师
One of the engineers on the locomotive of this train

2414
02:23:51,861 --> 02:23:55,683
要让革命在党的领导下 顺着历史的轨迹…
that pulls this revolution on the tracks of historical necessity

2415
02:23:55,798 --> 02:23:57,390
全速前进
laid out for it by the party.

2416
02:23:57,499 --> 02:23:59,330
你现在不能离开，我们找不到人替代你
You can't leave us now. We can't replace you.

2417
02:23:59,435 --> 02:24:01,130
-你有什么权利离开… -我不确定
- What right do you have you to leave... - I'm not sure.

2418
02:24:01,237 --> 02:24:03,262
做什么？去见你的妻子？
To do what? To see your wife?

2419
02:24:03,372 --> 02:24:04,999
去年在国际议会上…
Last year at the International Congress

2420
02:24:05,107 --> 02:24:06,734
我得知我的儿子得了斑疹伤寒症…
I learned that my son was very ill of typhus.

2421
02:24:06,842 --> 02:24:08,366
我都没去看我的儿子
I didn't go to see my son

2422
02:24:08,477 --> 02:24:11,571
因为我知道政党需要我
because I knew I was needed where I was placed by the party.

2423
02:24:11,647 --> 02:24:12,636
你不明白的是…
What you don't understand is...

2424
02:24:12,748 --> 02:24:15,239
你想放弃这个重要时刻吗？
Would you like to abandon this moment in your life?

2425
02:24:15,351 --> 02:24:16,716
你还会得到这个时刻吗？
Would you ever get this moment again?

2426
02:24:16,819 --> 02:24:19,913
-我不会放弃革命！ -雷德同志，你是一名作家
- I am not abandoning the revolution! - Comrade Reed, you're a writer.

2427
02:24:20,055 --> 02:24:21,511
人们知道和尊重你的工作
People know and respect your work.

2428
02:24:21,624 --> 02:24:24,855
-你说话很有权威 -兹诺维耶同志
- You speak with authority of feeling. - Comrade Zinoviev,

2429
02:24:24,960 --> 02:24:26,325
在过去的八个星期…
for the past eight weeks,

2430
02:24:26,428 --> 02:24:29,420
我完全不能和我妻子取得联系
I've been completely unable to communicate with my wife

2431
02:24:29,531 --> 02:24:32,022
或者和我在美国的朋友联系
or with my comrades in the United States.

2432
02:24:32,134 --> 02:24:33,897
我要回去，我想要你的帮助
I need to go back. I would like your help.

2433
02:24:34,003 --> 02:24:37,769
雷德同志，你可以回去做你的私事
Comrade Reed, you can always go back to your private responsibilities,

2434
02:24:37,873 --> 02:24:38,862
我也可以
so can I.

2435
02:24:38,974 --> 02:24:43,729
但你永远不会有这次历史性的机会了
You can never, never come back to this moment in history.

2436
02:24:44,446 --> 02:24:45,401
对不起
I'm sorry.

2437
02:24:45,514 --> 02:24:47,641
我无权牵扯到你的私生活
I have no right to tell you about your own life.

2438
02:24:47,750 --> 02:24:49,775
你比我更清楚
You know it better than I do.

2439
02:25:12,574 --> 02:25:14,769
逃离苏联可以说是难上加难
Maybe it was impossible to get out of Russia.

2440
02:25:14,877 --> 02:25:17,175
到处都是白军
There was White armies all around,

2441
02:25:17,246 --> 02:25:19,941
要成功逃亡简直就像做梦
so escape was not dreamt of.

2442
02:26:16,600 --> 02:26:19,432
我们接到杰克的消息
We had a communication from Jack.

2443
02:26:19,536 --> 02:26:23,062
他在芬兰的监狱里，不能自由通话
He was in prison in Finland where he couldn't communicate freely.

2444
02:26:23,172 --> 02:26:25,560
但他传话给我…
But he got word out to me

2445
02:26:25,908 --> 02:26:28,364
让我捎口信给路易丝
to take a message to Louise.

2446
02:26:28,478 --> 02:26:31,503
我记得去到路易丝家，她就住在我附近
And I remember walking over to Louise, she lived right near me.

2447
02:26:31,814 --> 02:26:34,976
我去到路易丝在帕特森的公寓
I walked over to Louise's apartment on Patson Place,

2448
02:26:35,351 --> 02:26:38,308
跟她谈了一个晚上杰克的事
and spent an evening with her talking about Jack,

2449
02:26:38,420 --> 02:26:42,480
她对杰克被困的消息非常激动
and she talked very earnestly about Jack's plight.

2450
02:26:54,368 --> 02:26:56,790
雷德夫人，美国政府无权干涉…
Mrs. Reed, the United States cannot involve itself

2451
02:26:56,904 --> 02:26:58,336
芬兰的内部事务
in the internal affairs of Finland.

2452
02:26:58,406 --> 02:27:00,134
难道美国领事…
Are you trying to tell me the American Consul

2453
02:27:00,241 --> 02:27:02,834
-不能给出任何消息？ -恐怕不能
- can't give you any information? - I'm afraid that there's nothing

2454
02:27:02,942 --> 02:27:05,398
-国务院对此无能为力 -别跟我说废话
- that the State Department can do. - Don't give me that garbage.

2455
02:27:05,512 --> 02:27:07,877
如果他的名字是洛克菲勒 那情况就会大不相同
If his name were Rockefeller, there'd be something you could do.

2456
02:27:07,981 --> 02:27:10,369
雷德夫人 如果你丈夫的名字是洛克菲勒
Mrs. Reed, if your husband's name were Rockefeller,

2457
02:27:10,483 --> 02:27:12,245
那他都不会背负上…
I think he would hardly be under indictment

2458
02:27:12,352 --> 02:27:14,876
阴谋推翻美国政府的罪名
for a conspiracy to overthrow the United States Government.

2459
02:27:14,988 --> 02:27:17,820
他只有一个肾脏，他会病重的
He has only one kidney. He could be dangerously ill.

2460
02:27:17,923 --> 02:27:20,447
那是你丈夫自己冒的险，雷德夫人
That is a chance that your husband took, Mrs. Reed,

2461
02:27:20,559 --> 02:27:24,756
他离开美国时，都没有签证或者护照
when he left the United States without an exit visa or a passport.

2462
02:27:24,863 --> 02:27:26,887
再见，雷德夫人
Good day, Mrs. Reed.

2463
02:27:27,833 --> 02:27:30,494
美国和联盟国都参加了…
The United States participated with the Allies

2464
02:27:30,568 --> 02:27:33,559
反对苏联的军事行动
in military expeditions against the Soviet Union

2465
02:27:33,671 --> 02:27:37,026
试图战胜他们，侵略他们
in an attempt to overcome them, invade them,

2466
02:27:38,009 --> 02:27:40,568
建立另一个政府
and set up another government. Oh, yes. Yes.

2467
02:27:40,711 --> 02:27:42,234
有这么一个陷阱…
There was a noose

2468
02:27:42,712 --> 02:27:45,976
设在苏联周围
to be pulled around Russia

2469
02:27:46,083 --> 02:27:51,042
让你知道整个国家…
which gave you an idea of how a whole country

2470
02:27:51,154 --> 02:27:55,647
会陷入四面楚歌的境地
can be surrounded east, west, south, and north.

2471
02:28:04,300 --> 02:28:06,927
你的名字，以及芬兰联络员的名字
Your name, and the name of your contact in Finland.

2472
02:28:24,918 --> 02:28:27,579
你的名字，以及芬兰联络员的名字
Your name, and the name of your contact in Finland.

2473
02:28:27,955 --> 02:28:29,285
我不知道是什么颜色
I don't know what color...

2474
02:28:30,257 --> 02:28:31,587
我自己拿吧
I'll just get it myself.

2475
02:28:31,692 --> 02:28:34,148
-你会得到… -你要我们现在做吗？
- Would you get some... - Would you like us to do it now?

2476
02:28:34,260 --> 02:28:35,624
-好 -好的
- Okay. - Oh, okay.

2477
02:28:35,862 --> 02:28:36,816
-好了 -我明白
- All right. - I understand.

2478
02:28:37,396 --> 02:28:38,350
从上面？
From the top?

2479
02:28:39,198 --> 02:28:41,461
知道，然后他们画了一幅地图
Oh, I see. Then they made a map.

2480
02:28:42,902 --> 02:28:44,061
泰瑞跟我谈过了
Terry spoke to me.

2481
02:28:44,203 --> 02:28:47,365
路易丝，你根本不知道这次旅行 对一个女人来说有多困难
Louise, I don't think you realize how difficult this trip to be for a woman.

2482
02:28:47,506 --> 02:28:48,494
你必须偷渡出去
You'd have to stow away.

2483
02:28:48,707 --> 02:28:51,266
就算你到了那里，也需要六个月…
If you got there at all, it would take you six months to...

2484
02:28:51,409 --> 02:28:53,672
泰瑞说你能给我安排一条货船
Terry said that he thought that you could arrange a freighter for me

2485
02:28:53,778 --> 02:28:55,438
-一直到挪威 -不知道你为什么这样说
- as far as Norway. - Don't know why you're saying it.

2486
02:28:55,547 --> 02:28:57,241
你知道我的意思吗？
You know what I mean?

2487
02:28:57,649 --> 02:28:58,876
坐下
Sit down.

2488
02:29:00,818 --> 02:29:03,377
我想跟你谈一些事
I want to talk to you about something.

2489
02:29:04,722 --> 02:29:05,676
…说明地图
...indicates the map.

2490
02:29:05,823 --> 02:29:07,346
我可以去
I could go.

2491
02:29:07,458 --> 02:29:10,813
我能以海员的身份去，不需要审查
I can sign on as a seaman. There'd be no questions asked.

2492
02:29:10,895 --> 02:29:12,919
在这种情况下…
I think under the circumstances...

2493
02:29:16,633 --> 02:29:19,965
别这样看我 杰克・雷德也算是我的朋友
Don't look at me like that. Jack Reed's a friend of mine.

2494
02:29:20,103 --> 02:29:22,900
我不会让那王八蛋死在监狱里的
I'm not gonna let the son of a bitch rot in jail.

2495
02:29:23,006 --> 02:29:24,836
只是好像我没兴趣…
Just seemed to me that I'm not as interested...

2496
02:29:29,745 --> 02:29:31,541
这样的话…
...and at this point...

2497
02:29:32,447 --> 02:29:33,743
好了
Okay.

2498
02:29:33,849 --> 02:29:36,214
他不是要来找我谈这事吗？
Wasn't he supposed to come over to me on this?

2499
02:29:36,318 --> 02:29:38,683
我明早就跟泰瑞谈
I'll talk to Terry in the morning.

2500
02:29:38,787 --> 02:29:40,913
在那里放个十字架
Where the cross is made...

2501
02:29:41,022 --> 02:29:43,285
希望那些王八蛋能合作
I wish these son-of-a-bitches could act.

2502
02:29:51,199 --> 02:29:53,154
约翰雷德:正尝试所有解决办法

2503
02:29:53,200 --> 02:29:57,192
停止活动，坚持住 爱你的路易丝

2504
02:30:29,033 --> 02:30:31,357
你的血压非常高
Your blood pressure is very high.

2505
02:30:31,994 --> 02:30:34,738
他们只给我吃咸鱼
They only give me some kind of salted fish.

2506
02:30:34,844 --> 02:30:37,848
你嘴巴里的血是从牙龈里出来的
The blood in your mouth is from the gums.

2507
02:30:38,026 --> 02:30:39,572
你得了坏血症
You have scurvy.

2508
02:30:41,040 --> 02:30:43,813
深刻的红印，同志
An impressive shade of red, comrade.

2509
02:30:50,056 --> 02:30:51,339
可以帮我发电报给我妻子吗？
Could you send a cable to my wife?

2510
02:31:52,759 --> 02:31:55,763
雷德先生，我有东西给你
Mr. Reed, I have something for you.

2511
02:31:59,620 --> 02:32:02,397
-有电报吗？ -还没有
- Is there a cable? - There's nothing yet.

2512
02:32:02,800 --> 02:32:06,865
你要用温水服这些药粉 每天一次
You should take one of these powders in a glass of water, once a day.

2513
02:32:07,104 --> 02:32:10,012
她有消息捎给我吗？
Has she sent word to me here?

2514
02:32:10,125 --> 02:32:13,663
他们不会说的 我们的人什么都找不到
They won't say. Our people can find out nothing.

2515
02:32:38,858 --> 02:32:40,438
你被释放了
You are being released.

2516
02:32:44,459 --> 02:32:49,317
我要告诉你 我完全忘记了约翰・雷德
You know, I must tell you, I lost sight of John Reed completely.

2517
02:32:50,193 --> 02:32:52,010
但我听说…
But what I heard was

2518
02:32:52,215 --> 02:32:56,609
布尔什维克通过收买几个芬兰教授…
the Bolsheviki traded some Finnish professors

2519
02:32:56,622 --> 02:32:59,162
[1920年，彼得格勒] 来释放约翰・雷德
for the release of John Reed.

2520
02:32:59,974 --> 02:33:01,295
约翰・雷德
John Reed.

2521
02:33:01,663 --> 02:33:03,741
我们是来欢迎你的
We are here to welcome you.

2522
02:33:05,674 --> 02:33:08,046
能带我去电报局吗？
Could you take me to the telegraph office?

2523
02:33:08,159 --> 02:33:10,203
-好的，上车吧 -谢谢
- Yes. Get in. - Thank you.

2524
02:33:18,997 --> 02:33:22,995
路易丝・拜伦，克洛顿…
"Louise Bryant, Croton-on..."

2525
02:33:23,106 --> 02:33:24,552
哈森
Hudson.

2526
02:33:24,663 --> 02:33:27,498
哈森…纽约…美国
"...Hudson, New York, USA.

2527
02:33:27,646 --> 02:33:28,797
“我很安全，句号”
"I'm safe. Stop."

2528
02:33:29,071 --> 02:33:30,922
“请联系…”
"Please contact..."

2529
02:33:31,424 --> 02:33:33,366
“联系，请联系…”
Contact. Please contact.

2530
02:33:33,512 --> 02:33:36,416
“联系彼得格勒电报局，句号”
"Contact Petrograd telegraph office. Stop.

2531
02:33:36,527 --> 02:33:38,740
“没收到你的消息，句号”
"Have received no word from you. Stop.

2532
02:33:39,279 --> 02:33:42,521
“请原谅…”
"Please for... Forgive..."

2533
02:33:42,658 --> 02:33:44,341
“请原谅圣诞节的事”
Please forgive Christmas.

2534
02:33:44,480 --> 02:33:49,044
“请原谅圣诞节的事，句号 爱你的杰克”
"Please forgive Christmas. Stop. Love, Jack."

2535
02:33:51,606 --> 02:33:52,858
可以马上发送吗？
Could you send that right away?

2536
02:33:57,174 --> 02:33:59,647
列宁同志说…
Comrade Lenin said

2537
02:33:59,758 --> 02:34:03,893
他会为约翰・雷德收买50位教授
he would trade, for John Reed, fifty professors.

2538
02:34:05,591 --> 02:34:08,766
路易丝・拜伦，克洛顿-哈森
"Louise Bryant, Croton-on-Hudson,

2539
02:34:08,872 --> 02:34:10,452
纽约，美国
"New York, USA."

2540
02:34:10,529 --> 02:34:13,601
-美国 -“美国，立刻…”
- USA. - "USA. Immediate."

2541
02:34:13,711 --> 02:34:16,083
-“速回…” -“速回…”
- Immediate return... - "Immediate return..."

2542
02:34:16,228 --> 02:34:17,978
-“美国…” -“美国…”
- ... United States... - "...United States..."

2543
02:34:18,118 --> 02:34:19,235
-“不可能” -“不可能”
- ... impossible. - "...impossible."

2544
02:34:19,377 --> 02:34:21,986
-路易丝・拜伦，克洛顿… -克洛顿
- Louise Bryant, Croton... - Croton.

2545
02:34:22,128 --> 02:34:24,670
-克洛顿… -克洛顿-哈森
- "Croton-on..." - Croton-on-Hudson.

2546
02:34:24,779 --> 02:34:28,574
克洛顿-哈森，纽约，美国
"Croton-on-Hudson, New York, USA.

2547
02:34:28,689 --> 02:34:33,614
“还没收到你的消息，句号 没有固定的地址，句号”
"Still no word from you. Stop. Have no fixed address. Stop."

2548
02:34:34,323 --> 02:34:39,248
路易丝・拜伦，克洛顿-哈森，美国纽约
"Louise Bryant. Croton-on-Hudson, New York, USA.

2549
02:34:40,951 --> 02:34:44,193
“要知道，你还好吗？句号”
"Must know, are you well? Stop."

2550
02:34:44,266 --> 02:34:46,581
-“不…” -“不明白…”
- "Do not..." - Do not understand.

2551
02:34:46,684 --> 02:34:51,609
“不明白为何没有你的消息，句号”
"Do not understand why no word from you. Stop."

2552
02:34:52,782 --> 02:34:57,673
路易丝・拜伦，克洛顿-哈森，美国纽约
"Louise Bryant. Croton-on-Hudson, New York, USA.

2553
02:34:57,787 --> 02:34:59,242
-“需要…” -“需要消息”
- "Need..." - Need word.

2554
02:34:59,354 --> 02:35:04,244
“需要你的消息，句号 不明白你为何沉默，句号”
"Need word from you. Stop. Do not understand your silence. Stop"

2555
02:35:04,359 --> 02:35:07,713
路易丝・拜伦，克洛顿-哈森
"Louise Bryant. Croton-on-Hudson,

2556
02:35:07,829 --> 02:35:12,094
-美国纽约 -你查了“里德”吗？
- "New York, USA." - Did you check R-E-A-D?

2557
02:35:12,200 --> 02:35:13,496
是的
Yes. Yes.

2558
02:35:13,600 --> 02:35:14,759
也查了“莱德”吗？
And you checked R-E-l-D also?

2559
02:35:14,869 --> 02:35:17,598
我查过了“莱德”
I have looked R-E-l-D,

2560
02:35:17,671 --> 02:35:19,500
“里德”
R-E-A-D,

2561
02:35:19,606 --> 02:35:23,665
“瑞德”，我查过高曼和拜伦
R-E-D. I have looked Goldman and Bryant.

2562
02:35:24,944 --> 02:35:26,638
我只是…对不起，请等一下
I'm just... Excuse me. One second.

2563
02:35:27,947 --> 02:35:29,470
如果…
Lf, if...

2564
02:35:29,616 --> 02:35:32,947
我想可能有一些字拼错了
I thought maybe there's some other way of misspelling the name.

2565
02:35:33,052 --> 02:35:36,646
-也查了“莱德”吗？ -是的，雷德同志
- You also looked under R-E-l-D? - Yes, Comrade Reed.

2566
02:35:36,755 --> 02:35:41,077
-你还想怎么样？ -很多人在等
- Yes, yes. What do you want? - There's many people wait.

2567
02:35:41,193 --> 02:35:44,286
-对不起 -有消息，我们会通知你
- Excuse me. - Lf something come, we'll notify you.

2568
02:35:49,667 --> 02:35:51,293
你听到什么？
What have you heard?

2569
02:35:51,369 --> 02:35:53,198
没什么，你呢？
Not much. What have you heard?

2570
02:35:53,338 --> 02:35:56,261
我没听见，我在等 他们监禁了更多无政府主义者
I don't hear. I wait. They've jailed more anarchists.

2571
02:35:56,373 --> 02:35:59,227
但他们让比尔・莎托夫 做西伯利亚铁路的领导
But they made Bill Shatoff head of the Siberian railway.

2572
02:35:59,877 --> 02:36:03,039
他们对我很好 我保存着自己的判断力
They treated me very well, and I'm reserving my judgment.

2573
02:36:03,146 --> 02:36:06,603
-聪明 -有很多事情我不明白
- Well, that's wise. - There's so much I don't understand.

2574
02:36:06,716 --> 02:36:08,307
森林离彼得格勒很近
There are forests within easy reach of Petrograd.

2575
02:36:08,418 --> 02:36:10,009
城市为什么还这么冷？
Why is this city freezing?

2576
02:36:10,119 --> 02:36:11,517
我问了兹诺维耶
I asked Zinoviev.

2577
02:36:11,621 --> 02:36:14,111
他说敌人破坏了所有运输通道
He said our enemies have destroyed all the means of transportation

2578
02:36:14,223 --> 02:36:15,814
杀光了我们的马，还有我们的人
and killed off our horses as well as our men.

2579
02:36:15,925 --> 02:36:16,913
我们怎么运输？
How would we get at it?

2580
02:36:17,026 --> 02:36:18,481
我说，彼得格勒的人呢？
I said, "What about the people of Petrograd?

2581
02:36:18,594 --> 02:36:21,220
他们可以一起走路去 用绳子把木头拖回来
"They could go there together on foot and haul the wood back with ropes."

2582
02:36:21,329 --> 02:36:22,852
他说“是的，那会让人更暖和”
He said, "Oh, yes, it would make the people warmer,

2583
02:36:22,964 --> 02:36:25,659
“但会耽误政策的施行”
"but it would interfere with the carrying out of the main political policy."

2584
02:36:25,734 --> 02:36:28,463
-你收到美国埃玛的来信？ -是的
- You get letters from America, E. G? - Oh, yes.

2585
02:36:28,602 --> 02:36:32,196
全都被司法局拆开 希望他们喜欢看，我可不喜欢
All opened by the Justice Department. I hope they enjoy what they read. I don't.

2586
02:36:32,339 --> 02:36:34,704
所以我问他“政策是什么？”
So I asked him, "What are the main political policies?"

2587
02:36:34,808 --> 02:36:37,469
他说“集中无产阶级先锋派…”
He said, "Concentration of all power in the hands

2588
02:36:37,578 --> 02:36:39,101
“手中的所有权力”
"of the proletarian avant-garde.

2589
02:36:39,212 --> 02:36:43,237
“革命先锋派是共产党”
"The avant-garde of the revolution, which is the Communist Party."

2590
02:36:43,683 --> 02:36:46,242
有人提到路易丝吗？
Anybody mention Louise?

2591
02:36:46,352 --> 02:36:49,240
没有，你没有她的消息吗？
I don't think so. You haven't heard from her?

2592
02:36:49,755 --> 02:36:52,609
我给她发了电报，但没有回复
I've sent her cables, but I don't get any answer.

2593
02:36:52,724 --> 02:36:55,180
-多久了？ -很久了
- For how long? - A long time.

2594
02:36:56,194 --> 02:36:57,387
等等
Wait.

2595
02:36:57,462 --> 02:37:00,294
莱斯・威廉姆斯在信中提到她
Rhys Williams mentioned her in his letter.

2596
02:37:00,399 --> 02:37:02,730
他也没收到她的消息
He hasn't heard from her, either.

2597
02:37:02,868 --> 02:37:03,992
他怎么说的？
What'd he say?

2598
02:37:05,370 --> 02:37:08,634
他说他想联系她
I think he said that he'd tried to reach her

2599
02:37:08,740 --> 02:37:11,867
在圣诞节后，但她离开纽约了
sometime after Christmas, but she'd left New York.

2600
02:37:15,580 --> 02:37:17,638
多久前的事？
How long ago was that?

2601
02:37:17,748 --> 02:37:20,170
信怎么也要花两个月才到这里
Well, you know how these letters take a couple of months to get here.

2602
02:37:20,283 --> 02:37:25,105
等到我看到时 寄信的人要么坐牢，要么被驱逐
By the time I get them, whoever sent it is either in jail or deported.

2603
02:37:25,221 --> 02:37:26,915
-就是那样 -是哪封？
- That's it. - Which?

2604
02:37:27,023 --> 02:37:28,421
-那封 -莱斯・威廉姆斯
- There. - Rhys Williams.

2605
02:37:28,568 --> 02:37:29,527
Oh.

2606
02:37:31,226 --> 02:37:33,887
-要三思而后行 -是的
- First the eyes go, then the legs. - Yeah.

2607
02:37:34,663 --> 02:37:37,324
我也不清楚燃料的情况
Yeah, I don't understand the fuel situation, either.

2608
02:37:39,001 --> 02:37:41,025
我不知道…
I don't know...

2609
02:37:45,106 --> 02:37:47,562
他说她离开了城市
He says she seems to be out of town.

2610
02:37:47,675 --> 02:37:49,005
他只那样说？
That's all he said?

2611
02:37:50,477 --> 02:37:51,534
是的
Yeah.

2612
02:37:52,146 --> 02:37:54,170
他说了奥尼尔什么？
What did he say about O'Neill?

2613
02:37:54,281 --> 02:37:55,872
奥尼尔？没说什么
O'Neill? Nothing.

2614
02:37:56,383 --> 02:37:58,111
拜托，他说了什么？
Come on, what did he say?

2615
02:37:59,319 --> 02:38:00,615
没什么
Nothing.

2616
02:38:00,720 --> 02:38:02,152
可以看看吗？
Can I see it?

2617
02:38:08,328 --> 02:38:09,589
对不起
I'm sorry.

2618
02:38:17,870 --> 02:38:20,030
我只是不知道她去了哪…
I just don't know where...

2619
02:38:23,808 --> 02:38:25,968
杰克，坐吧
Jack, sit down.

2620
02:38:37,621 --> 02:38:39,450
如果路易丝来这里
If Louise were to come here,

2621
02:38:39,555 --> 02:38:41,977
她就要非法偷渡出国
she'd have to leave the United States illegally,

2622
02:38:42,125 --> 02:38:44,353
然后和你过流亡的生活 再也回不了家
then live in exile with you, and never go home again.

2623
02:38:45,428 --> 02:38:48,725
这一切都是为了不属于她的革命
All for the sake of a revolution she was never any part of.

2624
02:38:48,831 --> 02:38:50,627
她为什么要那样做？
Why should she?

2625
02:38:51,266 --> 02:38:53,722
是你选择了革命的生活道路
You chose the life of a revolutionary.

2626
02:38:53,835 --> 02:38:55,165
她没有
She didn't.

2627
02:38:56,038 --> 02:39:00,633
你的电报只会让司法部监视她
Your cables only focus the Justice Department's attention on her,

2628
02:39:00,742 --> 02:39:03,301
对她最不利的就是…
and the most seditious thing they can accuse her of

2629
02:39:03,412 --> 02:39:05,106
她是你的妻子
is being your wife.

2630
02:39:06,114 --> 02:39:08,240
放过她吧
Leave her alone.

2631
02:39:08,350 --> 02:39:10,146
让她选择自己的未来
Let her choose her own future.

2632
02:39:11,318 --> 02:39:13,410
但她为什么不回电报？
Why hasn't she answered me?

2633
02:39:13,520 --> 02:39:15,349
我想这也算是一种回复
I think she has answered you.

2634
02:41:31,714 --> 02:41:34,952
他被释放了，没说他在哪里
He's been released. They won't tell me where he is.

2635
02:41:57,240 --> 02:42:00,537
你知道，她很讨厌…
Do you know, she was much hated

2636
02:42:00,643 --> 02:42:02,768
衣服的奢华
for her extravagance in clothes.

2637
02:42:02,912 --> 02:42:07,267
很久以前，有人跟我说…
Well, a long time ago, somebody said to me,

2638
02:42:08,717 --> 02:42:09,704
那些…
"People who...

2639
02:42:09,852 --> 02:42:12,739
那些处于危险中的女人
"Women whose lives have been in danger

2640
02:42:13,122 --> 02:42:16,578
在很长时期都总是很奢侈
"over a long period are always the most extravagant."

2641
02:42:17,092 --> 02:42:19,820
同志们，和许多被误导的政策一样
Comrades, as wrong-headed as many of its policies are,

2642
02:42:19,929 --> 02:42:22,316
世界产业工人组织是革命的联盟
the IWW is a revolutionary union

2643
02:42:22,431 --> 02:42:24,454
而美国劳工联合会不是
and the American Federation of Labor is not.

2644
02:42:24,566 --> 02:42:27,590
想打入美国劳工联合会内部…
To think we can infiltrate the American Federation of Labor

2645
02:42:27,703 --> 02:42:29,931
将它转变成革命联合是没有希望的
and convert it to revolutionary policies is hopeless.

2646
02:42:30,039 --> 02:42:31,163
翻译
Translation.

2647
02:42:34,076 --> 02:42:36,634
同志们，错误翻译
Comrades, that's the wrong translation.

2648
02:42:44,386 --> 02:42:46,147
他不是那样说的
That's not what he said.

2649
02:42:46,789 --> 02:42:47,879
他在说什么？
What's he saying?

2650
02:42:48,424 --> 02:42:50,481
为了能和大会与会者达成一致
For us to make a point on the floor of the Congress,

2651
02:42:50,592 --> 02:42:52,148
我们必须…
we have to go

2652
02:42:52,261 --> 02:42:54,989
从英语转译为德语
from our own English language into the official German language

2653
02:42:55,097 --> 02:42:57,689
再到意大利语 或者西班牙语，或者法语
to the Italian, or Spanish, or French language.

2654
02:42:57,800 --> 02:43:01,564
-当反应… -你有什么问题？
- And then, when the response from... - What is your question, please?

2655
02:43:01,670 --> 02:43:04,057
为了工会的事宜…
Simply for the labor union issue,

2656
02:43:04,139 --> 02:43:06,560
我们能让英语成为大会的…
could we have the English language as an official language

2657
02:43:06,675 --> 02:43:08,595
官方语言吗？
on the floor of the Congress?

2658
02:43:11,080 --> 02:43:14,206
雷德同志，你已经第三次提这个建议了
Comrade Reed, this is the third time you have raised this proposal!

2659
02:43:14,350 --> 02:43:15,474
这个问题早已有了结果
The issue has been decided.

2660
02:43:15,617 --> 02:43:17,947
我们必须推进到国家和殖民的事宜
We must move on to the national and colonial issues!

2661
02:43:22,658 --> 02:43:25,352
美国真正的工人革命者
Real revolutionary workers in the United States

2662
02:43:25,461 --> 02:43:28,587
很久前就放弃了工会联盟…
quit the AF of L a long time ago

2663
02:43:28,697 --> 02:43:30,720
然后加入了世界产业工人组织
and joined the IWW.

2664
02:43:30,833 --> 02:43:33,061
我们要让苏联人明白这一点
We have to make the Russians understand this,

2665
02:43:33,168 --> 02:43:35,896
所以我们需要你们的支持
and that's why we want your support

2666
02:43:36,005 --> 02:43:40,861
延长会议，让辩论公开化
to extend the session of congress and to keep the debate open.

2667
02:43:52,054 --> 02:43:53,485
杰克，你没事吧？
Jack, are you okay?

2668
02:43:53,589 --> 02:43:55,350
-你跟萨多谈过吗？ -谈过
- Did you talk to Sadoul? - Yes, I did.

2669
02:43:55,457 --> 02:43:58,788
同志们，我仍然反对结束讨论
Comrades, I'm still opposed to closing the discussion here.

2670
02:43:58,894 --> 02:44:01,315
我想之所以讨论结束…
I think that this discussion is being closed

2671
02:44:01,430 --> 02:44:04,659
是为了避免听到美英代表团的心声
to avoid hearing the American and the British delegations.

2672
02:44:04,767 --> 02:44:07,029
如果不是出于这个原因的话
And if for no other reason than that,

2673
02:44:07,136 --> 02:44:09,090
那么讨论就应该继续
it shows that discussion should continue.

2674
02:44:09,204 --> 02:44:11,466
拉德克同志用这个评论…
Comrade Radek uses this sort of remark

2675
02:44:11,540 --> 02:44:14,530
代替争论，结果他想不了了之
in place of an argument and as a result, he doesn't want to talk about it.

2676
02:44:14,676 --> 02:44:19,270
雷德是不怕区别歪曲的事实的
What Reed says is not distinguished by excessive fear of distorting the truth.

2677
02:44:19,415 --> 02:44:21,802
他日夜都在努力，声称…
He goes on day and night and has the cheek to claim

2678
02:44:21,917 --> 02:44:23,644
讨论被人为中断
that the discussion is being broken off

2679
02:44:23,752 --> 02:44:26,207
因为有些人害怕伟大的约翰・雷德
because of fear of the great might of John Reed.

2680
02:44:43,038 --> 02:44:46,096
雷德同志 你这样谈到明天早上都完不了
Comrade Reed, you may have time to discuss it until tomorrow morning.

2681
02:44:46,175 --> 02:44:47,538
别人没有这个时间
Other people do not have the time.

2682
02:44:47,643 --> 02:44:51,338
拉德克同志，没时间讨论这事的人
Comrade Radek, other people that don't have the time for this discussion

2683
02:44:51,480 --> 02:44:54,538
是世界产业工人组织的101个领导
are 101 leaders of the IWW

2684
02:44:54,683 --> 02:44:56,546
而今他们正在美国的监狱坐牢
who are in jail today in the United States

2685
02:44:56,652 --> 02:44:58,447
仅仅因为他们持有革命观点
because of their revolutionary views.

2686
02:44:58,554 --> 02:45:01,476
如果我们出卖这些同志…
And if we turn our back on these comrades

2687
02:45:01,590 --> 02:45:05,285
不能带领激进的美国劳工联合会…
out of some pipe dream to radicalize the American Federation of Labor

2688
02:45:05,394 --> 02:45:06,552
忘记这个白日梦，那就是羞耻
which cannot be done, it is a disgrace.

2689
02:45:06,662 --> 02:45:09,254
我们在本届六次会议上 讨论过这个问题
We've discussed this during six sessions of this commission.

2690
02:45:09,364 --> 02:45:10,989
今天一天都在讨论这个问题
We spent whole day today discussing it,

2691
02:45:11,100 --> 02:45:13,293
而你竟然说是我们 想停止讨论这个问题？
and you insinuate we are trying to dismiss the issue?

2692
02:45:18,974 --> 02:45:20,735
我们还没讨论充分
We haven't had enough discussion...

2693
02:45:20,843 --> 02:45:23,230
我们没有为我的朋友讨论充分
We haven't had enough discussion for my friend here

2694
02:45:23,378 --> 02:45:26,868
路易斯・佛莱纳和我在这个问题上 想法一致
to realize that Louis Fraina and I think alike on this problem.

2695
02:45:27,015 --> 02:45:28,708
我们代表团的每个美国人
Every American on our delegation,

2696
02:45:28,817 --> 02:45:31,409
-英国代表团的每个人… -你是这个委员会的一员
- every man on the English delegation... - You are a member of this committee.

2697
02:45:31,520 --> 02:45:33,042
你不是独立的政党代表
You are not an independent political party.

2698
02:45:33,155 --> 02:45:36,452
兹诺维耶同志 我不会被这个委员会所压制
Comrade Zinoviev, I will not be steamrollered by this committee

2699
02:45:36,558 --> 02:45:39,389
在这个问题上 我们还没有一个正确的认识
that has not had a proper education on this problem.

2700
02:45:39,495 --> 02:45:41,017
实际上…
On the fact...

2701
02:45:48,871 --> 02:45:50,200
讨论结束了
The discussion is closed.

2702
02:45:50,272 --> 02:45:52,966
如果雷德同志希望作陈述
However, if Comrade Reed wishes to make a statement,

2703
02:45:53,075 --> 02:45:55,405
他有两分钟的时间
he will have two minutes to do so.

2704
02:45:56,043 --> 02:45:59,465
我谨代表美国代表团在此声明…
I would merely want to say that on behalf of the American delegates,

2705
02:45:59,614 --> 02:46:02,001
我方拒绝在此事上投票
that we will refuse to vote on these theses,

2706
02:46:02,116 --> 02:46:05,743
我本人辞去在委员会的职位
and that I myself will resign my seat on this committee.

2707
02:47:11,312 --> 02:47:13,232
杰克，我想我们必须面对…
Jack, I think we have to face it.

2708
02:47:13,347 --> 02:47:16,439
我们的梦在苏联破灭了
The dream that we had is dying in Russia.

2709
02:47:16,550 --> 02:47:19,005
如果布尔什维克意味着 农民占领土地
If Bolshevism means the peasants taking the land,

2710
02:47:19,119 --> 02:47:20,550
工人占领工厂
the workers taking the factories,

2711
02:47:20,654 --> 02:47:24,008
那苏联就不是布尔什维克的天下了
Russia's one place where there's no Bolshevism.

2712
02:47:24,123 --> 02:47:27,648
我可以和警察争，可以和将军打
You know, I can argue with cops, I can fight with generals.

2713
02:47:27,760 --> 02:47:29,714
就是不能和官僚主义者斗
I can't deal with a bureaucrat.

2714
02:47:29,829 --> 02:47:32,455
你觉得兹诺维耶 不比官僚主义者坏吗？
You think Zinoviev is nothing worse than a bureaucrat?

2715
02:47:32,931 --> 02:47:34,988
苏联人不再有地方自治权了
The Soviets have no more local autonomy.

2716
02:47:35,133 --> 02:47:36,758
都成了中央集权
The central state has all the power.

2717
02:47:36,902 --> 02:47:38,595
所有的权利掌握在少数人手里
All the power is in the hands of a few men

2718
02:47:38,737 --> 02:47:40,362
他们在破坏革命
and they are destroying the revolution.

2719
02:47:40,505 --> 02:47:43,768
他们在破坏苏联共产主义的希望
They are destroying any hope of real Communism in Russia.

2720
02:47:43,874 --> 02:47:46,432
他们在把像我这样的人关进监狱
They're putting people like me in jail.

2721
02:47:46,544 --> 02:47:48,601
我对革命的理解是…
My understanding of revolution

2722
02:47:48,713 --> 02:47:51,805
它不是对政治异己的连续消灭
is not a continual extermination of political dissenters,

2723
02:47:51,916 --> 02:47:53,870
我不想参与其中
and I want no part of it.

2724
02:47:54,585 --> 02:47:56,744
每个报社要么关门大吉
Every single newspaper's been shut down

2725
02:47:56,853 --> 02:47:58,216
要么被政党控制
or taken over by the party.

2726
02:47:58,321 --> 02:48:01,345
任何一个被怀疑是反革命的人…
Anyone even vaguely suspected of being a counter-revolutionary

2727
02:48:01,458 --> 02:48:04,914
都有可能被就地正法 这何时才是个头？
can be taken out and shot without a trial. Where does that end?

2728
02:48:04,995 --> 02:48:07,325
以防御为名义
Is any nightmare justifiable

2729
02:48:07,429 --> 02:48:10,282
就有理由掀起反对反革命的恶梦？
in the name of defense against counter-revolution?

2730
02:48:10,432 --> 02:48:12,352
梦会在苏联破灭，但我不会
The dream may be dying in Russia, but I'm not.

2731
02:48:12,468 --> 02:48:15,026
或许过一段时间，我要逃离这里
It may take some time. I'm getting out.

2732
02:48:15,170 --> 02:48:17,966
好像你对运动中的革命感到很迷惑
You sound like you're a little confused by the revolution in action, E.G.

2733
02:48:18,072 --> 02:48:20,368
直到现在，你只在理论上说
Up to now, you've only dealt with it in theory.

2734
02:48:20,475 --> 02:48:21,735
你觉得事情会怎样？
What did you think this thing was gonna be?

2735
02:48:21,843 --> 02:48:23,297
难道是舆论的革命
A revolution by consensus

2736
02:48:23,411 --> 02:48:25,832
大家围坐一起 喝着咖啡侃侃而谈吗？
where we all sat down and agreed over a cup of coffee?

2737
02:48:25,947 --> 02:48:28,106
什么都没用
Nothing works.

2738
02:48:28,215 --> 02:48:30,238
去年死了四百万人
Four million people died last year.

2739
02:48:30,350 --> 02:48:31,508
不是死于打仗
Not from fighting a war,

2740
02:48:31,618 --> 02:48:34,471
而是死于饥荒和斑疹伤寒症 军国极权的国家…
they died from starvation and typhus in a militaristic police state

2741
02:48:34,588 --> 02:48:36,110
镇压了自由和人权
that suppresses freedom and human rights

2742
02:48:36,223 --> 02:48:37,347
什么都没用
where nothing works.

2743
02:48:37,424 --> 02:48:39,947
死人是因为法国，英国和美国的封锁
They died because of a French, British and American blockade

2744
02:48:40,059 --> 02:48:42,423
所有食物和药物的供应被切断
that cut off all food and medical supplies

2745
02:48:42,561 --> 02:48:44,618
因为反革命分子破坏工厂
and because counter-revolutionaries have sabotaged the factories

2746
02:48:44,764 --> 02:48:47,720
铁路和电话，因为那些…
and the railroads and the telephones, and because the people,

2747
02:48:47,833 --> 02:48:50,527
贫穷无知迷信文盲的人
the poor, ignorant, superstitious, illiterate people,

2748
02:48:50,635 --> 02:48:53,898
想自己做主主持大局，就像你说的那样做
are trying to run things themselves, just as you always said that they should,

2749
02:48:54,005 --> 02:48:55,095
但他们不知道怎么主持大局
but they don't know how to run them yet.

2750
02:48:55,206 --> 02:48:57,297
你真的觉得日子会立刻好起来吗？
Did you really think things would work right away?

2751
02:48:57,442 --> 02:48:59,499
你真的期望社会改革…
Did you really expect social transformation

2752
02:48:59,611 --> 02:49:01,770
和谋杀过程一样快速吗？
to be anything other than a murderous process?

2753
02:49:01,879 --> 02:49:04,801
这是战争，埃玛 我们必须把它看作战争去打
It's a war, E.G., and we gotta fight it like we fight a war,

2754
02:49:04,915 --> 02:49:06,972
有纪律，有恐惧，有战火
with discipline, with terror, with firing squads,

2755
02:49:07,084 --> 02:49:09,073
否则我们就放弃算了
or we just give it up.

2756
02:49:09,186 --> 02:49:11,550
四百万人不是死于战争
Those four million people didn't die fighting a war.

2757
02:49:11,622 --> 02:49:14,316
他们死于一个无法起效的制度！
They died from a system that cannot work!

2758
02:49:23,399 --> 02:49:25,353
这才刚开始，埃玛
It's just the beginning, E.G.

2759
02:49:26,134 --> 02:49:28,794
不会跟我们想象的那样可怕
It's not happening the way we thought it would.

2760
02:49:28,904 --> 02:49:30,597
不会跟我们想象的那样发生
It's not happening the way we wanted it to,

2761
02:49:30,706 --> 02:49:32,160
但肯定会发生
but it's happening.

2762
02:49:36,777 --> 02:49:38,697
如果你现在放弃…
If you walk out on it now,

2763
02:49:39,113 --> 02:49:41,272
那么你的生命还有什么意义？
what's your whole life meant?

2764
02:49:45,785 --> 02:49:48,581
我的辞职申请书批了吗？
Could you tell me if my resignation is ready for signature yet?

2765
02:49:48,722 --> 02:49:49,914
-批了 -很好
- It is. - Good.

2766
02:49:50,056 --> 02:49:51,612
可以看看吗？
May I see it?

2767
02:49:52,792 --> 02:49:54,087
谢谢
Thank you.

2768
02:50:00,499 --> 02:50:03,125
-谢谢，雷德同志 -欢迎回来，雷德同志
- Thank you, Comrade Reed. - Welcome back, Comrade Reed.

2769
02:50:03,235 --> 02:50:05,623
现在你可以代表美国工人…
Now you'll be able to represent the American workers

2770
02:50:05,738 --> 02:50:07,102
在即将举行的巴库会议上
at the forthcoming congress at Baku

2771
02:50:07,206 --> 02:50:10,766
鼓励中东人发起革命
to inspire revolution among the peoples of the Middle East.

2772
02:50:10,875 --> 02:50:11,863
准备迎接艰难的旅行吧
Prepare for a difficult trip.

2773
02:50:11,976 --> 02:50:14,000
我们唯一的路线是 穿越分隔的领土
Our only route is through divided territory.

2774
02:50:54,851 --> 02:50:58,411
一些知识分子散布谣言…
Some of these intellectuals spread rumors

2775
02:50:58,555 --> 02:51:01,216
说他改变了主意
that he changed his mind afterwards,

2776
02:51:01,358 --> 02:51:03,188
企图改变主意…
trying to, you know,

2777
02:51:06,462 --> 02:51:09,589
证明他醒悟了
show that he came to his senses.

2778
02:51:10,934 --> 02:51:13,197
那是荒谬的
It's preposterous.

2779
02:51:13,603 --> 02:51:17,629
这些人，我都不记得了
These men, well, I don't even remember them.

2780
02:51:18,040 --> 02:51:20,269
我也不想记住他们
I don't want to remember them.

2781
02:54:17,281 --> 02:54:20,044
所有通往巴库的列车都已取消
All trains to Baku canceled because of attacks

2782
02:54:20,184 --> 02:54:21,445
因为受到了反革命分子的袭击
by counter-revolutionaries.

2783
02:54:21,552 --> 02:54:22,813
肯定有去巴库的列车
There must be some train to Baku.

2784
02:54:24,887 --> 02:54:26,342
所有通往巴库的列车取消
All trains to Baku canceled

2785
02:54:26,490 --> 02:54:28,821
因为受到反革命分子的袭击
because of attacks by counter-revolutionaries.

2786
02:54:29,827 --> 02:54:32,681
肯定有去巴库的车
There has to be something to Baku.

2787
02:54:34,497 --> 02:54:35,758
路易丝？
Louise?

2788
02:54:39,369 --> 02:54:40,528
埃玛？
Emma?

2789
02:54:40,970 --> 02:54:42,027
埃玛
Emma.

2790
02:54:43,140 --> 02:54:44,197
埃玛
Emma.

2791
02:54:46,442 --> 02:54:49,774
你是怎么到苏联的？
How in the name of God did you get into Russia?

2792
02:54:51,914 --> 02:54:54,768
-我不知道要多久 -你要等一会儿
- I had no idea how long it would take. - So, you'll wait for a while.

2793
02:54:55,918 --> 02:54:59,341
没准你刚到那里，他就已经回来了
By the time you got there, he'd be back here anyway.

2794
02:54:59,455 --> 02:55:00,910
进来，快请进
Go on in. Go on in.

2795
02:55:01,024 --> 02:55:02,684
对不起
Oh, I'm sorry.

2796
02:55:02,792 --> 02:55:05,351
没事的，没事
It's all right. It's all right.

2797
02:55:10,333 --> 02:55:13,529
来，路易丝，坐吧
Here. Louise, sit down. Sit down.

2798
02:55:23,514 --> 02:55:25,674
我想告诉你事情
I want to tell you something.

2799
02:55:27,751 --> 02:55:29,342
这或许有点晚了
It's late, I know.

2800
02:55:34,025 --> 02:55:35,889
谢谢你送的围巾
I want to thank you for that scarf.

2801
02:55:37,027 --> 02:55:38,254
是的
Oh, yes.

2802
02:55:39,496 --> 02:55:41,326
我错看你了
I was wrong about you.

2803
02:55:42,132 --> 02:55:43,359
我也是
So was I.

2804
02:55:45,836 --> 02:55:48,395
美国石油公司想建立…
The American oil companies are trying to establish

2805
02:55:48,505 --> 02:55:50,096
对世界石油的垄断
a world monopoly of oil.

2806
02:55:52,844 --> 02:55:57,735
1898年，菲律宾人民推翻 西班牙殖民政府的残酷统治
In 1898, the Filipinos rebelled against the cruel colonial government of Spain.

2807
02:56:01,119 --> 02:56:03,609
西班牙人被驱逐后
But after the Spaniards had been driven out...

2808
02:56:22,174 --> 02:56:25,529
美国人承认了菲律宾的独立
The Americans have promised the Filipinos independence.

2809
02:56:25,611 --> 02:56:29,307
很快宣布菲律宾共和国的成立
Soon an independent Filipino republic will be proclaimed.

2810
02:56:33,719 --> 02:56:37,210
美国政府随即派军队去那里驻扎
The government of United States sent soldiers and sailors there...

2811
02:56:40,227 --> 02:56:44,117
比英国暴君还专权
...under a dictatorship worse than the British tyrants.

2812
02:56:52,639 --> 02:56:54,037
他们这是干嘛？
What's that for?

2813
02:56:54,141 --> 02:56:56,631
他们支持你，因为你发起圣战
They are supporting you for your call for a holy war

2814
02:56:56,744 --> 02:56:59,507
伊斯兰人民反对西方非信教徒的圣战
of Islamic people against the western infidels.

2815
02:57:20,668 --> 02:57:22,123
打搅了，雷德同志
Excuse me, Comrade Reed.

2816
02:57:22,270 --> 02:57:24,965
他们说你不满意你演讲的翻译稿
They said you are not happy with the translations of your speech.

2817
02:57:25,072 --> 02:57:26,504
我把德语翻成了土耳其语
I did the German into Turkic

2818
02:57:26,607 --> 02:57:28,836
奥辛斯基同志把俄语翻译成德语
and Comrade Ossinsky did the Russian into German.

2819
02:57:28,944 --> 02:57:31,468
俄语？
Russian?

2820
02:57:31,547 --> 02:57:33,173
谁一开始就翻译成了俄语？
Who turned it into Russian in the first place?

2821
02:57:33,282 --> 02:57:34,714
我不知道
Well, I don't know.

2822
02:57:34,817 --> 02:57:36,545
从兹诺维耶同志办公室拿到的演讲稿…
They were already in Russian when we got them

2823
02:57:36,685 --> 02:57:38,208
就是俄语的
from the office of Comrade Zinoviev.

2824
02:57:40,555 --> 02:57:42,510
-很抱歉我英语不好 -你的英语不错，同志
- I'm sorry for my English. - Your English is fine, comrade.

2825
02:57:49,932 --> 02:57:53,355
兹诺维耶，是你翻译了我的演讲稿吗？
Zinoviev, did you do the translations of my speech?

2826
02:57:54,069 --> 02:57:55,729
在我的监督下翻译的
I supervised it. Yes.

2827
02:57:55,871 --> 02:57:58,634
我没说圣战，我说的是阶级战争
I didn't say "holy war." I said "class war."

2828
02:57:58,740 --> 02:58:01,071
我冒昧修改了一两个短语
I took a liberty of altering a phrase or two.

2829
02:58:01,544 --> 02:58:04,706
我不允许别人冒昧修改我的作品
Yes, well, I don't allow people to take those liberties with what I write.

2830
02:58:05,315 --> 02:58:08,340
你不知道如何宣传才能感动人吗？
Aren't you propagandist enough to utilize what moves people most?

2831
02:58:08,451 --> 02:58:10,907
我要用真相来宣传
I'm propagandist enough to utilize the truth.

2832
02:58:11,020 --> 02:58:14,580
谁定义真相？是你还是党？
And who defines this truth? You or the party?

2833
02:58:14,724 --> 02:58:16,054
你只需要致力于演讲…
Is your life dedicated to speaking for...

2834
02:58:16,159 --> 02:58:18,285
不用你说我要致力于什么！
You don't talk about what my life is dedicated to!

2835
02:58:18,395 --> 02:58:20,954
你连这辈子致力于什么事业都还没决定
Your life? You haven't resolved what your life is dedicated to.

2836
02:58:21,064 --> 02:58:23,987
你把自己看作艺术家，同时也是革命家
You see yourself as an artist and at the same time as a revolutionary.

2837
02:58:24,133 --> 02:58:26,862
看作是你妻子的爱人 也是代表美国阶级的发言人
As a lover to your wife, but also as a spokesman for the American classes.

2838
02:58:26,970 --> 02:58:28,800
兹诺维耶，你根本不知道一个人…
Zinoviev, you don't think a man can be an individual

2839
02:58:28,905 --> 02:58:30,394
是可以对集体忠诚的
and be true to the collective,

2840
02:58:30,506 --> 02:58:33,861
可同时代表自己国家和共产国际说话
or speak for his own country and the International at the same time,

2841
02:58:33,978 --> 02:58:37,037
既忠于妻子，依然对革命忠诚
or love his wife and still be faithful to the revolution,

2842
02:58:37,114 --> 02:58:38,239
而你根本就没有什么可以奉献！
you don't have a self to give!

2843
02:58:38,349 --> 02:58:40,213
你愿意把自己献身给革命吗？
Would you ever be willing to give yourself to this revolution?

2844
02:58:40,317 --> 02:58:42,113
当你把一个人和他最爱的东西分开时
When you separate a man from what he loves the most,

2845
02:58:42,253 --> 02:58:44,709
你要做的就是净化他的心灵
what you do is purge what's unique in him.

2846
02:58:44,822 --> 02:58:46,846
当你净化了他的心灵
And when you purge what's unique in him,

2847
02:58:46,991 --> 02:58:48,912
-你就消除了异议 -雷德同志
- you purge dissent. - Comrade Reed.

2848
02:58:49,026 --> 02:58:51,448
当你消除了异议，你就扼杀了革命
And when you purge dissent, you kill the revolution!

2849
02:58:51,563 --> 02:58:52,995
革命就是异议！
Revolution is dissent!

2850
02:58:53,098 --> 02:58:55,088
-雷德同志 -你别重写我写的东西
- Comrade Reed. - You don't rewrite what I write!

2851
02:59:02,806 --> 02:59:05,296
是反革命份子
Comrade Reed, counter-revolutionaries!

2852
02:59:05,844 --> 02:59:08,504
是反革命份子
Counter-revolutionaries, Comrade Reed!

2853
03:01:42,357 --> 03:01:43,584
爸爸
Papa!

2854
03:01:46,394 --> 03:01:47,792
爸爸！
Papa!

2855
03:03:59,327 --> 03:04:00,816
别离开我
Don't leave me.

2856
03:04:03,698 --> 03:04:05,096
请别离开我
Please don't leave me.

2857
03:04:20,381 --> 03:04:24,373
同志，医生现在想见你
Comrade, the doctor would like to see you now.

2858
03:04:39,167 --> 03:04:42,124
医生觉得还需要进一步分析
The doctor thinks that we must do more analysis.

2859
03:04:42,237 --> 03:04:45,262
几天后他的情况会更明朗
And a picture of his illness will be clearer in a few days.

2860
03:04:45,340 --> 03:04:46,601
他想要你知道
And he wants you to know

2861
03:04:46,708 --> 03:04:49,403
我们会给雷德同志最好的医治
that we shall do the best conditions for Comrade Reed

2862
03:04:49,544 --> 03:04:51,932
以防高血压…
to prevent possibility of high blood pressure

2863
03:04:52,046 --> 03:04:53,000
引起中风
to cause a stroke.

2864
03:05:08,162 --> 03:05:11,289
我真的…我知道…
I really... I know...

2865
03:05:12,634 --> 03:05:13,691
什么？
What?

2866
03:05:15,103 --> 03:05:16,501
你好吗？
How are you?

2867
03:05:20,809 --> 03:05:21,763
不
No.

2868
03:05:22,378 --> 03:05:23,435
杰克？
Jack?

2869
03:05:47,402 --> 03:05:51,258
我没有…
You know, I don't... I don't...

2870
03:06:00,382 --> 03:06:01,746
你听见吗？
You hear it?

2871
03:06:02,584 --> 03:06:04,312
什么？
- Huh? - What was that?

2872
03:06:05,087 --> 03:06:07,213
水在叮咚响
The water plays little songs.

2873
03:06:24,305 --> 03:06:27,569
现在不是12月吗？
It's not December, is it?

2874
03:06:45,693 --> 03:06:47,284
天哪
My, my, my, my.

2875
03:06:59,474 --> 03:07:02,328
天哪，几点了？
God. What a time it was, huh?

2876
03:07:18,494 --> 03:07:20,791
-想跟我去纽约吗？ -纽约？
- Want to come to New York with me? - New York?

2877
03:07:21,163 --> 03:07:22,390
有出租车在等我
I got a taxi waiting.

2878
03:07:25,800 --> 03:07:27,528
我不介意
I wouldn't mind.

2879
03:07:30,037 --> 03:07:31,594
以什么身份？
What as?

2880
03:07:32,673 --> 03:07:33,866
什么身份？
What as?

2881
03:07:35,843 --> 03:07:37,002
什么身份？
What as?

2882
03:07:39,514 --> 03:07:41,140
不知道
Gee, I don't know.

2883
03:07:49,490 --> 03:07:50,615
同志身份？
Comrades?

2884
03:07:56,964 --> 03:07:58,191
同志
Comrades.

2885
03:08:03,738 --> 03:08:05,602
我想回家
Well, I want to go home.

2886
03:08:11,312 --> 03:08:12,335
是的
Yeah.

2887
03:08:51,586 --> 03:08:53,075
我去给你倒水
I'll get you some water.

2888
03:10:36,691 --> 03:10:38,715
天哪
Oh, God.

2889
03:12:04,376 --> 03:12:06,105
那是在下午
It was in the afternoon,

2890
03:12:06,245 --> 03:12:09,305
好像是在秋天的时候
sometime in the fall, I think.

2891
03:12:09,715 --> 03:12:11,273
好像是10月
October, I think.

2892
03:12:12,151 --> 03:12:14,073
有人来告诉我
Somebody came to tell me

2893
03:12:14,753 --> 03:12:16,482
杰克・雷德死了
that Jack Reed died.

2894
03:12:16,955 --> 03:12:19,913
可以想象…
You can imagine how...

2895
03:12:23,162 --> 03:12:24,857
我当时的感受
How I felt.

2896
03:12:28,434 --> 03:12:30,493
我把他们全都忘了
I'd forgotten all about them.

2897
03:12:30,636 --> 03:12:32,399
他们是社会主义者吗？
Were they socialists?

2898
03:12:34,406 --> 03:12:36,772
他们很多人都是理想主义者
Many of them were idealists.

2899
03:12:38,244 --> 03:12:41,805
你知道，事情去了又来
You know, things go and come back again.

2900
03:12:43,717 --> 03:12:46,982
我不知道外界怎么看他们
I don't know what the outside world thought of them,

2901
03:12:47,220 --> 03:12:49,484
但他们是一对夫妇
but they were a couple.

2902
03:12:49,589 --> 03:12:53,252
人们总是提起 路易丝・拜伦和杰克・雷德
I mean, you always spoke of Louise Bryant and Jack Reed.

2903
03:12:55,628 --> 03:12:58,552
他只是一个普通的年轻人
He was just a man in the prime of life.

2904
03:12:59,666 --> 03:13:02,726
我都不知道他们有没有孩子
I don't even know. Did they ever have any children?

2905
03:13:03,903 --> 03:13:06,292
可能没有
They probably didn't have any children,

2906
03:13:06,639 --> 03:13:08,095
他和路易丝
he and Louise.

2907
03:13:10,810 --> 03:13:13,768
有孩子的时候…
Again, you can't tell, when you have children,

2908
03:13:14,748 --> 03:13:18,570
他们可能就不会从事革命了
whether they will carry on your revolutionary tradition or not.

2909
03:13:22,021 --> 03:13:23,909
他为什么那样做？
Why did he do it?

2910
03:13:24,257 --> 03:13:27,181
这就好像在问爱迪生为什么发明…
Well, it's impossible to say

2911
03:13:27,327 --> 03:13:28,760
或是高利科奇为何唱歌…
why Edison invented,

2912
03:13:28,862 --> 03:13:32,559
永远不会有答案
or why Galli-Curci sang...

2913
03:13:33,099 --> 03:13:36,921
他是个热血男儿
He was definitely a stirrer-up of people.

2914
03:13:37,772 --> 03:13:39,467
那是他的天地
That was his field.

2915
03:13:40,674 --> 03:13:43,268
那就是他要从事的事业
That's what he came to do, apparently.

2916
03:13:44,578 --> 03:13:49,504
他出名，但不是很出名
He's well-known amongst a few, but not everybody.

2917
03:13:49,817 --> 03:13:52,342
很多人不知道他是谁
They don't know who in heck he is.

2918
03:13:53,888 --> 03:13:57,551
我期待自己某天死去
I look for myself to die any day.

2919
03:14:02,163 --> 03:14:04,529
列宁问他是不是美国人
He was asked by Lenin, "Are you an American?"

2920
03:14:05,499 --> 03:14:06,454
他说是
He said, "Yes."

2921
03:14:06,567 --> 03:14:09,263
列宁问是美国人中的美国人吗？
And Lenin said, "An American American?"

2922
03:14:10,337 --> 03:14:11,827
雷德说是
And Reed said, "Yes."

2923
03:14:14,642 --> 03:14:19,033
当然，没有人想死
Of course, nobody goes with the idea of dying.

2924
03:14:19,146 --> 03:14:22,104
每个人都想活着
Everybody wants to live.

2925
03:14:24,151 --> 03:14:27,575
我不记得他确切的话语了
I don't remember his exact words,

2926
03:14:27,688 --> 03:14:29,553
大意是…
but the meaning was

2927
03:14:30,691 --> 03:14:34,582
大事业在前方…
that grand things are ahead,

2928
03:14:36,998 --> 03:14:41,196
值得为之生为之死
worth living and worth dying for.

2929
03:14:41,770 --> 03:14:44,364
他自己那样说的
He himself said that.

